English.1:
A Puppet Digimon that has concealed itself inside 
a stuffed animal shaped like Tyrannomon. Why 
exactly this mysterious Digimon chose a stuffed
Tyrannomon is unclear, but it probably just hid 
inside whatever plush toy was nearby. Whatever 
the explanation, this stuffed Tyrannomon has all 
the offensive and defensive power of Monzaemon, 
meaning no ordinary Digimon can stand up to it.
However, just like Monzaemon, it's nothing more 
than an ornament without someone to pull its 
strings. Its special move is Pretty Attack, which
emanates from its adorable body.
English.2:
A Mammal Digimon resembling a rabbit, born from 
the fusion of moon observation data. Its large ears 
can recognize sounds from any distance. Although 
timid, Lunamon often gets lonely and easily grows 
attached to others. It uses its special move 
Tearing Shot to concentrate power into the antenna 
on its forehead to shoot a beautiful orb of water at 
the enemy.
English.3:
A Beast Man Digimon with astounding jumping 
capabilities that likes to toy with its foes using 
speedy movements. Lekismon's nature is as 
ephemeral as the phases of the moon, and its 
appearance is somewhat mystical. It uses its 
special move Moon Night Bomb to hurl hypnotic
water bubbles generated from the Moon Gloves 
on its hands and put the enemy to sleep.
English.4:
A Wizard Digimon with a flexible body, enabling it 
to dispatch foes with graceful movements. It
specializes in highly fluid fighting styles, and is 
said to double in power when bathed in the light of
the moon. Its special move, Lunatic Dance, entrances
opponents with rhythmic steps, allowing it to close
in and deliver a two-handed slash with its weapons
Nova Luna.
English.5:
A Rock/Mineral Digimon discovered when 
performing digital analysis of an ancient curse. It 
has forbidden incantations in an archaic script
signifying "plague," "curse" and "evil" inscribed on
its back, apparently meant to safeguard it from
the gas it emits. Approximately 90% of its body is
composed of rock data, and it survives by binding
up its limbs. An emotionless Digimon that doesn't
act unless so ordered.
English.6:
The decrepit ruins of what was once a Dark Angel 
Digimon that fell into the Dark Area in its pursuit of 
strength and destruction. There, SkullSatamon's 
wicked nature intensified, and its dark powers are
now unfathomable. Its DigiCore, concentrated with 
these dark powers, has transformed into a DarkCore,
something only possessed by Evil-species Digimon.
SkullSatamon's special move Nail Bone is a horrifying
technique that unleashes an intense light from the
jewel on the tip of its staff, disrupting and
obliterating its opponent's data.
English.9:
A mutant Machine Digimon shaped like a gear. 
There are also countless other gears built into its 
body that are constantly turning. If even one gear 
is removed, all of the others stop spinning and 
Hagurumon ceases to function. Hagurumon possesses
the ability to infect foes with a computer virus that
allows it to control them. Thus, Digimon of wicked
intent often seek to exploit Hagurumon's powers.
But since it lacks any sense of self, it has no way
of knowing it's being used for evil. Its special move
is Cog Crusher, which implants a black gear
loaded with a computer virus into its opponent's
body, causing them to go berserk.
English.10:
A Fire Digimon whose body is cloaked in crimson 
flames. Generated of the Firewall built to defend 
against illegal intrusions from the Internet, this 
Digimon has a violent temperament that reflects 
its blazing appearance and seeks to incinerate
anything it touches. Its flames burn more intensely 
than those of its kindred on File Island, making it
an extremely difficult Digimon to tame. But even if 
tamed, there's no telling when Meramon will turn 
on its master. Meramon uses its special move 
Burning Fist to cause its arms to flare up before 
punching its foe.
English.11:
A Mythical Beast Digimon with gigantic wings. 
Airdramon is an exceptionally valuable monster,
thought to be near in stature to a god. It specializes
in aerial combat, invoking storms with its roar and
creating colossal whirlwinds by flapping its wings.
Though quite vicious by nature, Airdramon is also
very intelligent. Nevertheless, any average Tamer
would find it nearly impossible to control. Airdramon
beats its huge wings to unleash a cutting vacuum
blade with its special move Spinning Needle.
English.12:
A wolf-like Beast Digimon with a pale silver pelt. 
Garurumon's fur is said to be as hard as the 
legendary rare metal Mithril, and the blades
extending from its shoulders are sharp enough to 
slice through anything they touch. Possessed of a
physique honed in the frozen tundra and a fierce 
instinct for conflict, Garurumon is feared by other 
Digimon for its predatory agility and unerring 
accuracy in bringing down its prey. However, it's 
also incredibly intelligent and steadfastly loyal to 
any it acknowledges as its leader. Garurumon uses 
its special move Fox Fire to breathe out a stream 
of intense blue flames.
English.13:
A Ghost Digimon with a cloth draped over it. 
Bakemon is a wicked being born of darkness, and 
is said to instantly destroy the systems of any 
computers it possesses. What lies beneath the 
cloth is a complete mystery, and there are theories 
that the shadow cast under its body is a black hole. 
Bakemon lacks combat power and thus prefers not 
to attack its foes directly. Its special move 
Death Charm casts a powerful curse. Those lacking 
strong mental fortitude die in a matter of seconds 
under its effect.
English.14:
A star-shaped Digimon discovered by chance in 
planetary analysis software at a space development
center. Starmon is a space warrior with stellar armor,
wearing gloves and boots emblazoned with stars. Its
tattered yellow scarf speaks to the many battles it's
survived, and its eyes burn with fighting spirit. Its
eyes can even be used in a more advanced manner
to hypnotize opponents. This hot-blooded Digimon
has a fierce admiration for the brave Leomon.
Starmon's special move Meteor Shower rains down
small meteors upon the heads of its foes.
English.15:
A Giant Bird Digimon with a pair of enormous horns 
on its head. Known as the "Great Eagle of the Desert,"
Aquilamon soars through the sky at Mach speed and
can spot distant foes with its keen eyesight. Its horns
display tremendous force when Aquilamon swoops
down to ram into enemies. While many Bird Digimon
are savagely brutal, Aquilamon values decorum and
obeys those it pledges allegiance to without fail.
It slams into foes from above with its special move
Glide Horn.
English.16:
A "Commando Dragon" that seeks to become a 
Virus Buster. While Strikedramon still has many 
vestiges of Monodramon, such as the horn jutting 
out of the back of its head, it has so transformed 
its appearance into a Commando-Mode Digimon 
covered in metal plating that it now resembles a 
completely different species. Despite being an 
inherently kindhearted Digimon, should it happen
upon a Virus-attribute type, Strikedramon becomes 
consumed by an instinct to exterminate and 
doesn't stop fighting until its opponent's data has 
been reduced to dust. It uses its special move 
Fang Strike to heat its metal plating to red-hot 
levels, turning itself into a mass of flame and 
tackling the opponent in a fearsome maneuver.
English.17:
A Dark Digimon possessing strong Dark Side 
Power. Minotarumon's movements are slow, but it 
has an extremely tough hide that leaves it unfazed 
by regular attacks. Its special move Darkside Quake
uses the Demon Arm attached to its left arm to
cause a massive earthquake. The attack sends
shockwaves over a wide area, making escape
impossible no matter how far enemies run.
English.19:
An imaginary Digimon born from the daydream of 
a DigiCore. The interface on Dorugoramon's 
forehead miraculously unlocked the creative 
power of its own DigiCore, causing it to Digivolve 
into this form. Perhaps because this DigiCore 
already contained powerful draconic data, the 
form it dreamed up was that of an avatar of 
powerful destruction and the very incarnation of 
the "ultimate enemy." Dorugoramon uses its 
special move Brave Metal to unleash a dreadful 
charge with all the power of body and soul, and 
DORU-Din to release a shockwave of destruction.
English.20:
A mouse-like Digimon that's always filling Sukamon's
head with shady ideas. Chuumon has a solid
friendship with Sukamon (although perhaps
it's only Chuumon that sees things that way).
The relationship started when Chuumon was nearly
caught in a network system trap named "Carnivore,"
only to be rescued by Sukamon, who just happened
to be passing by. Fundamentally a coward,
Chuumon is unrivaled in its slyness and takes
off like a shot at the slightest hint of danger. 
Its special move Cheese Bomb hurls a cheese-shaped
explosive. Anyone who makes the mistake of
eating one of these is in for a nasty surprise.
English.21:
A gigantic Digimon that dwells in the depths of the 
Net Ocean. Its huge size ranks it among the largest 
of all Digimon in the Digital World. In fact, Whamon
is so enormous that normal computers can't process
the sheer volume of data that it's comprised of.
Similar species have been confirmed in the waters
near File Island, but Whamon, which lives along the
coast of the Folder Continent, boasts attack strength
and vitality superior to its kin, having Digivolved to its
Ultimate form. Its special move Tidal Wave creates a
massive tsunami that destroys everything in its path.
English.23:
A Mutant Digimon that DNA Digivolved from 
Stingmon and ExVeemon. A chimera of a dragon 
and an insect, this Digimon is known as the 
"Terrible Bee." While Dinobeemon can't be easily 
classified as either a Dragon or an Insectoid type, 
its insect qualities are quite prominent. Flying 
through the air on its four wings, this Digimon 
tracks its foes unerringly with its compound eyes
before choking the life out of them with harsh 
certainty. Dinobeemon is also exceedingly
barbaric by nature. It uses its special move
Hell Masquerade to perform a "dance of Hell,"
cutting through foes with movements fast
enough to leave afterimages.
English.24:
A seldom-seen Pixie Digimon that dwells in the
Net Ocean. Despite the "Angemon" in its name, it's
actually completely distinct from the Angemon
species in terms of its ecosystem. The ring around
MarineAngemon's neck is called a Holy Ring,
causing speculation that it has some relation to
Holy Digimon such as Gatomon or Angewomon,
who also wear such rings. The characters inscribed
on its ring have yet to be deciphered.
Though MarineAngemon generally avoids combat,
its special move Ocean Love causes foes to lose
the will to fight, thereby guaranteeing victory.
English.25:
An Android Digimon modeled after a feral Digimon 
with predatory instincts that enable it to reliably
bring down prey. Raptordramon boasts an incredibly
tough body as well as uncontrollable savagery, and
so it has been remodeled with pure Chrondigizoid
Metal of considerable weight to restrict its mobility.
Nevertheless, it still possesses exceptional explosive
power and flight capabilities, largely due to the feral
Digimon it used to be prior to remodeling.
Though small, Raptordramon is capable of taking
down even ultra-large Digimon in a single blow if
it can gradually unlock its abilities.
It performs its special move Ambush Crunch by
pouncing on the enemy and biting vitals with its
sharp fangs.
English.26:
Grademon is a Warrior Digimon known as the 
"Golden Meteor," due to the courageous way it 
smashes through the vanguard of the enemy. It 
exhibits blazing speed when using its "Twin Blade 
of the Dragon King" in tandem, but the truth is, the 
swords bear an irrepressible curse that forces the
wielder into a berserker frenzy. Though not as
powerful overall, Grademon's swordsmanship is 
believed to surpass that of LordKnightmon of the 
Royal Knights. The royal blue cape Grademon wears is
also a badge of honor bestowed for its meritorious 
deeds in many battles. Its special move is Cross Blade, 
a swift sword technique that cleaves through the
enemy in a cross-shaped pattern.
English.27:
The strongest dragon warrior, wearing armor 
crafted from the super-metal Chrondigizoid, 
WarGreymon is the ultimate form of the Greymon 
species. It sports a more humanoid physique than 
the typical large bodies of other Greymon types, 
but possesses vastly improved power and speed. 
It may be impossible to defeat with the attacks of 
Ultimate-level Digimon. The "Dramon Killers" 
attached to WarGreymon's arms deal massive 
damage to Dramon-species Digimon, but also 
expose WarGreymon to danger, making them 
double-edged swords. WarGreymon can also 
combine the exoskeleton parts on its back to form 
the hardest of shields, "Brave Shield." It's said that 
even among the most battle-hardened of veterans, 
it's only when one of true valor realizes its own 
destiny that it Digivolves into a WarGreymon. 
WarGreymon's special move is the super dense, 
high temperature energy beam Terra Force, with 
which it concentrates all the energy in the 
atmosphere into a single point before blasting it
forward. It also uses Great Tornado to join the 
Dramon Killers on its arms above its head to 
perform a spinning, high-speed charge that
pierces the enemy.
English.28:
A Mutant Digimon that acts as the boss of the 
Mamemon, and sometimes referred to as the
"Smiley Bomber." Some believe that BigMamemon
is actually an aggregation of Mamemon. Though
normal Mamemon are about the same size as
In-Training Digimon, they pack more power into
their small frames than appearances would imply. 
BigMamemon, on the other hand, lives up to its 
name by being dozens, if not hundreds, of times 
larger than its smaller kin. At this size, why it's 
still referred to as "Mamemon," named for its small 
stature, is unclear. BigMamemon has a warm, 
gentle personality, and isn't fond of conflict or 
battle. It can always be found playing with its 
Mamemon followers. Its special move 
Big Smiley Bomber uses the Mamemon under its 
command as weapons. BigMamemon is said to 
shrink in size after using this technique.
English.30:
Sangloupmon is a bloodsucking wolf Digimon with 
a noble demeanor. It's one of the oldest species of 
Digimon, said to have survived since the dawn of 
the Digital World. Digimon who have their blood 
sucked by Sangloupmon have all the data drained
from their DigiCores, causing them to perish, as 
they can no longer maintain vital functions. 
Sangloupmon is capable of teleporting to other 
locations instantly by disassembling its own data 
into packets and sending them across the Net. Its 
special move is Sticker Blade, which fires off a 
spray of thousands of minute blades to skewer 
opponents in the blink of an eye.
English.31:
A bloodsucking martial artist Digimon that performs
a magnificent dance. Said to have been born in
the folk dance database of a certain museum,
Matadormon is a master of the Bulldog Dance,
performing it with a unique arrangement of rhythmic
movements. It uses its fluttering garments to
befuddle foes, slashing those who let their guard
down with the countless rapiers hidden inside the
deceptively soft cloth of its sleeves. As a vampire,
Matadormon must sustain itself by drinking Digimon
blood, but not just any will do, and so it wanders
from land to land in search of strong Digimon to
feed upon. Its special move is Earth-Shattering Stomp,
a vicious kicking attack drawing upon Matadormon's
own original martial arts style.
English.32:
A Dark Beast Digimon known as the king of all
vampire Digimon. GranDracmon has long
maintained its own castle in the Dark Area, and is
said to boast such immense might that not even the
Seven Great Demon Lords dare meddle with it. With
a well-bred demeanor and a voice laced with
bewitching glamor, GranDracmon can be devilishly
charming, and there are numerous tales of Angel
Digimon sent to slay it that ended up being seduced
to the dark side. Its special moves are Crystal
Revolution, which flash-freezes all foes into ice
crystals, and Eye of the Gorgon, which turns its evil
gaze on the enemy, trapping its heart in darkness.
English.33:
A bipedal Ceratopsian Digimon resembling a 
triceratops, with all the combat power of that 
mighty herbivorous dinosaur. Its hide is among the 
toughest of all biological Digimon. Similarly, the 
two ultra-hard horns on its forehead are much 
more solid than Monochromon's horn. Though 
generally placid by nature, Triceramon's charging 
attack belies its slow movements, and packs 
enough destructive force to shatter even the 
sturdy bodies of Mineral Digimon. It uses its 
special move Tri-Horn Attack to ram into enemies
with the horns on its forehead and snout.
English.34:
One of the Seven Great Demon Lords, this Evil King
Digimon takes the form of a woman. Believed to
have at one time been an Ophanimon, Lilithmon
fell from grace and became what's known as the
"Goddess of Darkness." Beguiling and beautiful, it
seduces its foes, with certain death said to await all
who accept its invitation. In keeping with its
"Goddess of Darkness" moniker, Lilithmon rewards
vice with generosity and virtue with cruel indignities.
The fiendish "Nazar Nails" on its right hand corrode
anything they touch. Lilithmon's special move is
Phantom Pain, a dark breath attack that eats away
at foes' bodies. Those afflicted by this curse find
their data eroding, starting with their extremities,
and they suffer painfully even after their inevitable
demise.
English.35:
Beelzemon is an Evil King Digimon that prizes its 
independence, despite having the ability to rule over
many Evil-species Digimon. One of the Seven Great
Demon Lords, Beelzemon is said to be capable of
becoming the foremost Nightmare Soldier should it
so desire, but it's also rumored that there's another
Evil King Digimon whose power surpasses even
Beelzemon's. Beelzemon always keeps its beloved
shotguns, the Berenjena, close at hand, and it rides
around on its giant motorcycle machine Behemoth.
It has a cruel and ruthless personality, but due to its
pride, it never appears in groups or attacks the weak.
Its signature move is Darkness Claw, with which it
raises its sharp claws into the air and then slices
through its foe. Its special move, Double Impact,
involves firing twin blasts from its two shotguns.
English.36:
One of the Seven Great Demon Lords, this Evil King
Digimon resembles an old man with a long beard.
Barbamon exists in the heart of the den of evil known
as the Dark Area, controlling Dark Angel Digimon and
causing them to engage in all sorts of wickedness.
It's obsessed with all the treasures of the Network,
using every means at its disposal to sate its greed.
This rapacious and ruthless creature would kill a
Digimon for even a scrap of treasure. The most
cunning tactician of the Seven Great Demon Lords,
it controls not only Dark Angel Digimon, but even the
Mega-level Ghoulmon with ease. Barbamon's special
moves are Death Lure, a demonic staff that tempts
Digimon into an inescapable living hell and converts
them to wickedness, and Pandemonium Lost, which
releases all the evil energy of the Dark Area at once,
burning everything with a super high-temperature
explosion. Even MaloMyotismon's special move
Pandemonium Flame releases only the smallest
fraction of this energy.
English.37:
Fear of the excessive power in Leviamon's
possession has earned it the moniker of "Devil
Beast," and it's counted among the Seven Great
Demon Lords. A grand creature with a maw large
enough to swallow the entire Digital World, it's said
to sleep in the Net Ocean near the Dark Area. If
awoken, Leviamon looks down on any Digimon in
positions of might, causing not only other Evil King
Digimon to flee in terror, but even Angel Digimon as
well. There are limits to what can be determined
about this Digimon, however, and it almost never
appears. It's considered a primordially evil existence
that has taken up residence in the Digital World. It
can use its special move Biting Crush to destroy
everything in its path with its massive jaws, or Tail
Strike to pulverize enemies with its long tail.
English.38:
An Evil King Digimon with many Evil-species and 
Dark Angel Digimon under its command. 
Creepymon was originally an Angel Digimon, and 
one of quite high rank at that. However, it resorted
to rebellion—or perhaps violence—against the 
personifications of the Digital World's goodness
(which may have been the very humans who built it), 
and was thus deleted to the Dark Area (the 
graveyard of erased data). Creepymon and its ilk 
have vowed to one day subjugate the Digital World 
and exact revenge upon these personifications of
goodness. It uses its special move Flame Inferno to 
blast enemies with superheated hellfire. Anyone hit 
by this attack is incinerated without a trace.
English.39:
Both divine and diabolical, this Ultimate Evil King
Digimon is the strongest of the Seven Great Demon
Lords. Lucemon: Chaos Mode instigated a rebellion
in ancient times, and was sealed away in the Dark
Area along with many other Evil King Digimon. Its
power exceeds that of Mega Digimon, so much so
that it even rivals the entities called "gods." Although
it has a godlike side that cherishes all living things, it
also has a demonic side that wants to annihilate the
world itself. This is why it aims to destroy this world
and build a new one in its stead. Its special move
Paradise Lost launches its enemy high into the air
with a wild barrage before it grabs its limbs and
slams it into the ground, while Dead or Alive seals
the enemy within a three-dimensional magic circle
made from holy and evil spheres. Those caught in
this magic circle have a 50/50 chance of either being
completely obliterated or taking heavy damage.
English.40:
Belphemon awakes from its constant slumber once
every thousand years and returns to its original form.
It transforms into an avatar of rage once awakened,
and everything in its field of vision is subject to
destruction. Digimon of Ultimate level or lower who
hear Belphemon: Rage Mode's roar face instant
death from data fragmentation, and not even Mega
Digimon can escape unharmed. It uses its special
move Lampranthus to shoot black flames from the
chains coiled around its body, and Gift of Darkness
to cleave with claws enveloped in infernal flames.
Also, the data of Digimon killed by that which rules
over the Seven Great Demon Lords isn't reincarnated,
going instead to the Dark Area to act as flesh and
blood for Evil Kings.
English.41:
A Puppet Digimon that resembles a panda. 
Pandamon's expressionless gaze, together with its 
abrupt and dismissive personality, rob it of any
cuteness it might otherwise have. It likes to think 
of itself as a lone wolf, but it's secretly jealous of
Monzaemon, a popular Digimon with a similar look.
Still, Pandamon is surprisingly capable in battle,
and is quick to send any who disturb it packing.
The Pandamon population is small, making it a
rare sight. Its special move is Animal Nail, an
attack with the claws normally kept hidden in
its paws.
English.42:
An Insectoid Digimon affiliated with the mysterious
Royal Base, a secret floating honey base.
While its daily life may differ from that of other
Insectoid Digimon, FunBeemon has a cheery
disposition and is a hard worker of considerable
strength. It always gets along with Vegetation
Digimon like Palmon or Lillymon. The Royal Base
is under constant construction, and Funbeemon's
mission requires it to collect field data such as
flowers or plants a little at a time as building
materials. It's therefore classified as having the
Virus attribute. The base is also guarded by
powerful Digimon that prevent any from drawing
near, so the purpose of the construction remains
a mystery. FunBeemon's special move is Gear
Stinger, an attack that fires off a rapid volley of
tiny, serrated stingers.
English.43:
A Virus Gatomon with striking black fur. 
BlackGatomon is the quintessential child of evil, 
spendings its days wandering through eerie 
darkness. An extremely rare mutation of Gatomon, 
very few are thought to exist. BlackGatomon is
malicious and prideful and loves picking on the 
weak—all in all a problematic Digimon. As a Dark
Digimon, it generally Digivolves into a Dark Angel 
Digimon. Just like Gatomon, BlackGatomon's 
special move is Lightning Paw.
English.44:
CatchMamemon is a Mutant Digimon that Digivolved 
from Mamemon when it fused with data from file 
management software. Purposeful and sometimes
obstinate, CatchMamemon considers caring for 
Digi-Eggs to be its chief task. If need be, it can move 
around without floating by using its giant arms to 
walk. If the slot machine on CatchMamemon's 
chest rolls a triple seven as it grabs onto a foe, it 
transforms that Digimon into a bomb using Miracle 
Bomb, then uses the transformed enemy to attack. 
The force of the resulting explosion is said to be 
equal to the strength of the captured Digimon.
English.45:
A Deity Digimon said to be a materialization of the
system that governs time. The flow of time in the
Digital World is truly vague, and some conflicts
between powerful Digimon or cataclysms have
been known to cause space-time disturbances.
It's Chronomon that appears on such occasions,
bearing the responsibility of mending space-time.
Once it makes such a restoration, even the fact
that Chronomon appeared disappears alongside
said disturbance itself, thus no one has ever laid
eyes on this Digimon. This is why its existence is
only spoken of in a scant few legends. Chronomon's
special moves are Holy Flare, a blast of holy flame
that burns away the very existences of any who
maliciously seek to warp space-time, and
Chronos Crop, an unblockable attack in which it
swings its wings like blades, cleaving its foe from
the fabric of time and space itself.
English.46:
The form Chronomon takes when it goes berserk,
Chronomon: Destroy Mode is a legendary monster 
that has renounced its duty of maintaining the
peaceful order of space-time and has instead risen in
revolt against the very time-governing system itself.
While repairing space-time, all of the variformed
malice existing in the Digital World flowed into
Chronomon all at once, causing it to spin out of
control, much as if it had been infected with a virus.
Exploiting the innate temporal powers Chronomon
originally possessed, Chronomon: Destroy Mode
hacks into the memories etched into the Digital
World and downloads a diverse arsenal of skills
into itself for use in its rampages. Despite its berserk
state, Chronomon: Destroy Mode still has the ability
to burn foes to nothing with Holy Flare. It also
possesses Chrono Devolution, which converts the
Digital World's time data into energy that instantly
ages any who touch it, reducing their data to dust.
English.47:
The most atrocious and evil of Dragon Digimon. 
Counted among the Four Great Dragons along with 
Azulongmon, Goldramon and Magnadramon,
Megidramon's fiendish nature trumps even that of 
its three brethren. It's rarely encountered, to the 
point that its existence itself is in question.
Megidramon is considered a Digital Hazard, but 
its power is being sealed by some unknown force. 
They say that awakening that power would cause 
the Digital World's greatest crisis. Its body is 
composed of Chrondigizoid. One theory states that
Megidramon and ChaosGallantmon were once the
same entity, and whether it appears as a Dark Knight
or a Dark Dragon depends on how you observe this
virtual wave of terror. Its signature move Hell Howling
unleashes a powerful shockwave, while its special
move Megiddo Flame turns all things to ash.
English.48:
Goldramon is a Holy Dragon Digimon with six 
hardened wings and a body of glittering gold. 
Since it wears one of the Holy Rings—the symbol 
of Holy Digimon—upon its arm, it's believed to be 
a kind of Sacred Digimon. Goldramon is one of the 
Four Great Dragons, and it wears vambraces with
small Dragon Digimon sealed within them upon its 
arms: Amon of Crimson Flame, which governs 
destruction, on its left, and Umon of Blue Thunder,
which governs regeneration, on its right. Goldramon's 
special move is God Flame, which involves detonating
its Holy energy to instantly fell enemies in all
directions.
English.49:
BanchoLeomon is a Beast Man Digimon that 
answers only to its own sense of justice. It's said 
that only Digimon that have continued to triumph 
over incredibly powerful foes without having their 
spirits broken earn the title of "Bancho"—a term
that loosely translates to "ringleader." In all the 
recorded history of the Digital World, only five 
Digimon have ever been confirmed to have this in 
their names. BanchoLeomon opposes anything 
that stands in the way of its justice. Even if it's one 
of the Royal Knights or one of the Three Celestial
Digimon, BanchoLeomon won't hesitate to brand 
them as an evil foe that must be destroyed. 
BanchoLeomon also boasts a powerful defense, 
as it can use the GAKU-RAN draped over its 
shoulders to negate 89.9 percent of the damage 
caused by an opponent's physical attacks. 
BanchoLeomon's special moves include Lion Slash, 
an attack with its beloved shortsword Otokodama, 
and Flashy Boss Punch, which involves channeling 
all of its considerable energy into a single punch.
English.50:
A small, dinosaur-like Reptile Digimon that has 
developed the ability to walk on two legs. Since it
hasn't fully matured, it still lacks strength, but its 
fierce disposition makes it reckless. Hard, sharp 
claws grow from its hands and feet, and it makes 
full use of them in battle. Agumon shows much 
potential, promising Digivolution into a great and 
powerful Digimon. Its special move is Pepper 
Breath, spitting flames at its foes.
English.51:
An Android Digimon born from the fusion of the 
data from a portable music player and that of the 
mythical "kappa" river creature. Gawappamon is 
almost always cheerful as it listens to its favorite 
tunes, but it also sometimes weeps if the disc on 
top of its head gets scratched. It uses its special 
move DJ Shooter to spin its disc at high speed 
and launch it at the enemy.
English.52:
An Android Digimon that wears a shell like a computer
mouse. Kamemon uses its special move Pointer Arrow
to fire an arrow-shaped missile that it guides to strike
the enemy.
English.53:
A Holy Beast Digimon that's always wrapped around
a holy ammunition cartridge. Kudamon is constantly
building up holy power within the earring on its left 
ear, and the amount it accumulates affects the
course of its next Digivolution. Calm and collected 
by nature, it can assess any situation—even combat
—with accuracy, ensuring the advantage in battle. 
If things ever go south, though, Kudamon enters 
its cartridge to strengthen its defensive position.
Its special move Blinding Ray dazzles the enemy
with a glaring flash emitted from its earring.
English.54:
A unique Digimon thought to be a subspecies of
Greymon. GeoGreymon sports a deadlier frame
than ever, with the shell on its head as well as its
entire body having developed into living weapons.
It can charge up a Mega Flame in its mouth to
maximize its destructive power and then unleash
it as a Mega Burst.
English.55:
A Beast Digimon thought to be a subspecies of
sharp-clawed Gazimon. Gaomon specializes in
hit-and-run attacks using agile movements. The
gloves on its hands are apparently to protect its
claws until they grow in properly. Gaomon uses
its powerful legs to spin and unleash its special
move Double Backhand.
English.56:
A Vegetation Digimon resembling a flower bud,
Lalamon drifts through the sky by rotating the
leaves on its head. Despite its lack of expression,
it has a great deal of charm. Its special move
Seed Blast shoots hard seeds from its mouth with
a surprising degree of accuracy.
English.57:
A Pixie Digimon with rose-like features, Rosemon is 
known as the queen of flowers. With the appearance 
of a lovely woman, this Digimon desires eternal 
beauty. Though somewhat overly self-conscious, 
Rosemon's abilities are a match for the other Megas. 
It wears on its chest a Tifaret, a jewel engraved with 
the symbols for love and beauty. It's said that those 
who bear this Tifaret are promised eternal beauty
and strength. One of Rosemon's special moves is 
Thorn Whip, with which it uses a whip of thorns
charged with an electric current to tame even the 
fiercest of Digimon. It's rumored that anyone struck 
by this whip becomes captivated by Rosemon, 
body and soul. Also, any Digimon subjected to 
Rosemon's Forbidden Temptation is surrounded by
countless rose blossoms and has its data destroyed 
in a flash of beauty.
English.58:
A Vegetation Digimon resembling a sunflower. 
Sunflowmon gets a real energy boost when it's 
exposed to sunlight, which makes its attacks more 
powerful. On sunny days, it may even fly around by 
flapping the two leaves growing from its back. Its
special move is Sunshine Beam, which releases 
a blast of sunlight from its petals.
English.59:
An Android Digimon with a huge and powerful body. 
The namesake volcano on its back erupts when its 
anger peaks and its tension voltage exceeds its 
limits. Volcanomon shares a friendly rivalry with 
Etemon. Its booming voice shakes both heaven 
and earth. Its special move Big Bang Voice dazzles 
enemies with an ultra-deep bass mic performance.
English.60:
One of the rumored seven Digivolutions from
Volcanomon. Possessing immense strength and
destructive power, PileVolcanomon is well-versed in
all manner of hand-to-hand fighting techniques,
including pro wrestling moves. During the process of
Digivolution, it sculpted its once-massive physique
into a leaner form more suitable for melee fighting.
Its special moves are Volcanic Driver, which
leverages the power generated by the erupting
volcanoes on its shoulders to smash opponents
head-first into the ground, and Diamond Fist, an
ultimate punch capable of rending even Chrondigizoid.
English.61:
A Digimon shrouded in mystery, Monzaemon looks 
like an ordinary stuffed bear, but rumor has it that
someone—or something—has climbed in through 
the zipper on its back. It makes its opponent feel 
happy by wrapping it in the love that overflows from 
its adorable body (although its eyes are pretty scary).
Its special move Hearts Attack flings hearts at the
enemy.
English.68:
This Beast Digimon is the result of Gaomon's 
physique developing and the claws that were once 
protected by gloves finally growing in properly.
Although GaoGamon is a quadruped, its hind legs 
are strong enough for it to stand like a bear while 
it attacks. GaoGamon unleashes its special move
Spiral Blow to shoot a powerful vortex of wind 
from its mouth in one breath.
English.69:
An extremely rare Numemon that first discovered
the Platina Mine in the Digital World, taking in those
components to Digivolve. From that point on,
PlatinumNumemon's personality did a complete
about-face as it scraped together any jewelry data
it could find, decorating itself like a nouveau riche.
It's quite the "gorgeous" Digimon, despite its nature.
Outfitting itself with golden wings and jewelry grants
it considerable defense, but its attack power is
middling at best. PlatinumNumemon uses its special
move Platinum Excrement to hurl the dregs
(excrement) produced during the platina refinement
process in rapid succession. It also uses Platinum
Burp to release a putrid belch that saps the enemy's
fighting spirit.
English.70:
A slug-like Mollusk Digimon. Fond of damp, dark 
environments, Numemon lacks both offensive 
power and intelligence. Any Digimon can become
a Numemon if it isn't raised properly, but perhaps 
it has hidden depths? Then again, even its attacks
are bottom-tier, flinging its own poop to defend 
against enemies.
English.71:
An Android Digimon with more than half of its body 
mechanized. Despite RizeGreymon's massive frame, 
it can still take to the skies to defeat foes. The 
destructive force it can blast from the giant revolver 
on its left arm is said to be as powerful as a nuclear 
warhead, but the combination of this force with the
recoil it generates means it generally can't fire more
than one shot at a time, and to withstand the
explosive power, the gun barrel has to be made of 
Chrondigizoid. RizeGreymon's special move 
Trident Revolver pushes the limits of Chrondigizoid's 
durability by firing a three-round burst.
English.72:
This Beast Man Digimon is known as the 
"King of Beasts," and also the "Noble Hero." 
Standing out amidst the many savage Digimon 
out there, Leomon possesses both strength of will 
as well as a sense of justice, which it has wielded 
to defeat scores of villains. It has a rival in the
"Digimon Hunter" Ogremon, which devotes itself 
entirely to acts of destruction. Leomon hones its
formidable physique with daily training so that 
it can withstand all attacks, and it kills foes with 
its ultimate technique, the special move Fist of 
the Beast King. From Leomon's waist hangs 
Shishiou-maru, the Beast Sword with a will of 
its own.
English.73:
A Pixie Digimon resembling the beloved lilac flower. 
Though innocent and pure of heart, Lilamon's 
beauty is deceptive, as it's said to have power over 
death and rebirth. Its leaves are poisonous, and 
doing battle with this Digimon sometimes proves 
fatal. Lilamon's special move is Lila Shower, which 
fires countless slender beams from its petal-like
fingers.
English.74:
MachGaogamon is an Android Digimon with 
immensely powerful rocket engines on its back. 
While it never stays in the air long, it excels at
hit-and-run combat that can make full use of its 
propulsive bursts of speed. Its special move is 
Winning Knuckle, a single powerful punch that
packs quite a wallop.
English.75:
One of the Olympos XII, Neptunemon is a marine 
god Digimon that governs all Aquatic-species 
Digimon. The scale mail covering its body is a 
Chrondigizoid alloy called Blue Digizoid that 
facilitates mobility and speed, allowing it to move 
at a fearsome pace underwater. Its castle Abyss 
Sanctuary was built in a deep underwater trench, 
and only those who can withstand the water 
pressure of the extreme depths can enter. Its 
special moves include Vortex Penetration, with 
which it strikes with King's Bite, its sentient 
spear, and Wave of Depth, with which it unleashes
a massive tsunami that swallows up everything
in its path.
English.76:
A Wizard Digimon expelled from the heavens of the 
Digital World. A certain DigiCore is sealed within 
the nine beads of its necklace. It's usually calm 
and collected, but if even one bead of its necklace 
is lost, Shaujinmon transforms once again into a 
terrifying Digimon. It uses its special move 
Kouyoujou: Hydro Descent to strike its astonishing, 
super-heavyweight staff "Kouyoujou" on the 
ground, shattering it and releasing a raging current.
English.77:
A Digimon resembling a kamaitachi—a mythical 
weasel-like creature—with a blade for a tail. This 
tail moves with a will of its own, allowing Reppamon 
to handle even surprise attacks from the rear. That 
will doesn't always line up with Reppamon's, though, 
so this Digimon has been observed quarreling with 
its own tail during battle. Reppamon enjoys combat 
in wooded areas, making good use of its claws and 
tail to climb nimbly among the trees. Thus, one must 
exercise considerable caution when battling Reppamon
in wooded areas. Its special move Rolling Tackle is a
forward-rolling charge.
English.78:
A Dark Dragon Digimon known as the "Deep 
Crimson Dragon." Having Digivolved into a wilder, 
more ferocious creature, the childishness from 
its time as Guilmon is now gone. Although it's 
a Virus Digimon, Growlmon may become loyal 
depending on how its Tamer raises it, perhaps
even fighting for justice. Its roar is mighty enough 
to shake the ground, and Growlmon uses it as 
an aggressive display to intimidate the enemy
before battle. It has the special move Exhaust 
Flame, which unleashes a powerful blast of fire 
with an explosive roar.
English.79:
A Mutant Digimon that's the Ultimate form of the
space warrior Starmon. SuperStarmon made its
debut dressed in a dazzling costume uniquely
suited to its own exacting standards. Since it's a
superstar, it tries to hide its identity by wearing
sunglasses, but this doesn't make for a very
effective disguise. Its special move is Haley Storm, 
which rains meteors down onto its opponent.
English.80:
One of the Olympos XII, this Digimon is a genius god
boasting the greatest speed in the Digital World.
Merukimon's unrivaled speed cannot be seen with
the naked eye, and so any recordings of it are said to
be of its afterimages. It hates staying still and is
always wandering the Digital World, making it a
difficult being to encounter. It uses its special
move Thousand Fists to approach the enemy at an
almost instantaneous speed before unleashing an
incredible rapid-fire barrage. Merukimon is also an
accomplished shaman, allowing it to use Spiritual
Enchantment, cleaving the air with its beloved blade,
Aztec and summoning demons from another dimension.
English.81:
Impmon is a Rookie Digimon that looks like a devil
child. It loves to pull pranks, relishing the thought
of watching its victims struggle. Rumor has it that
whenever Impmon appears, electrical appliances
briefly go haywire, so if your screen ever shakes or
freezes, it might be because Impmon is pulling a
prank. But as much as Impmon delights in mischief
and malice, it's not one to meekly bow down before
the strong. It puts on a brave face and stands up to
them instead. Deep down, it's actually quite lonely.
Impmon's signature move is Summon, which calls
forth fire and ice elementals.
English.82:
HippoGryphonmon is a Mythical Beast Digimon 
that resembles a chimera. It's said to Digivolve 
into Gryphonmon, but beyond that, little more 
about it is known. HippoGryphonmon isn't as 
intelligent as Gryphonmon, as it's generally more
bestial, with a ferocious personality to match. 
Its special move is Heat Wave, spewing out a 
stream of scorching hot air.
English.83:
A fused Digimon with the head, wings and forelegs 
of a Bird Digimon, the body of a Beast Digimon 
and a serpentine creature on its tail. While capable
of flying through the skies with its wings, it usually
stays in deserts or mountain caves. Gryphonmon's
a difficult foe to beat, and it uses its incredible power
and agility to toy with its opponents. Making use of
these strengths, it's employed across the Net to
prevent illegal access and to safeguard confidential
information. Its special move Supersonic Voice emits
super-high-frequency sound waves that destroy an
enemy's data structure.
English.84:
A Holy Beast Digimon said to be an Ancient born 
at the advent of the Digital World, Chirinmon 
possesses strength akin to a Mega Digimon
despite being Ultimate itself. While immensely 
powerful, it deeply despises conflict, and never 
engages in cruelty. Its compassionate personality 
causes it to treat all things living in the Digital 
World with affection, but on the other hand, doesn't
hesitate to punish any who indulge in pointless
violence. Using its special move Wind Cutter Sword,
it swoops down in an instant to run the enemy
through with the horn on its head.
English.85:
The king of Undead Digimon, it was resurrected 
through the dark arts, obtaining mighty powers 
in the process. Originally a malicious computer 
virus that demolished all the data it absorbed, 
Myotismon gained the ability to reanimate the
data it destroyed as malignant viruses. 
Myotismon has an extremely cruel and cunning 
personality, and is an insidiously difficult Digimon 
to destroy. However, it can only make full use of 
its powers at night. During the day, Myotismon 
is apparently reduced to only half-strength. 
Its special move Night Raid commands a swarm 
of bats to ambush its foes.
English.86:
A Holy Knight Digimon and member of the Royal 
Knights. Kentaurosmon is an outlier among the 
mostly humanoid Digimon of the Royal Knights,
possessing an atypical bestial form. The defensive 
strength of the Red Digizoid armor encasing its body
makes damaging this Digimon no mean feat, even
for Mega Digimon. Six legs offer Kentaurosmon
superior mobility, allowing for instantaneous
movement in spite of its large frame. It uses its
special move Bifrost to fire an incandescent arrow
of light from the holy crossbow Múspellsheimr on
its left arm, or Odin's Breath to control the weather,
generating a cryogenic blizzard with the holy shield
Niflheimr on its right arm.
English.87:
An Angel Digimon with six shining wings and a
body clad in divine white cloth. This being of
absolute goodness is said to bring happiness.
Angemon remains utterly composed in the face
of evil, attacking relentlessly until its foe is
annihilated. Legend has it that Angemon has
often descended at the head of a host of other
Digimon of the same species when the Digital
World was in crisis. It's also said that Devimon,
who was lured to the Dark Side, was originally of
the same species. Angemon's special move is
Heaven's Knuckle, with which it pummels its foe
with a shining fist of gold.
English.88:
A Holy Knight Digimon and member of the Royal 
Knights, Omnimon was fused from the Virus Busters
WarGreymon and MetalGarurumon through the
will of those who wish for good. Omnimon is
able to draw on the qualities of both Digimon
to the fullest extent under any circumstance,
making it a capable and versatile fighter. Its
left arm is in the shape of WarGreymon, with
a sword and shield, and its right hand takes 
the shape of MetalGarurumon, equipped with 
a cannon and missiles. The cloak on its back 
deploys automatically when it needs to avoid
enemy attacks or to fly. Omnimon's special 
move is Supreme Cannon, fired from the 
MetalGarurumon-shaped cannon on its right 
arm. Omnimon's left arm is equipped with the 
invincible blade, Transcendent Sword.
English.90:
A Digimon resembling a young dinosaur. Although
Guilmon is still a Rookie Digimon, it possesses a
carnivore's brutality and the great potential as a
fighting species that all Digimon naturally possess
The mark on its abdomen is called a DIgital Hazard,
and is inscribed on any Digimon with the ability to
cause serious damage to computer data. Still, if
used for the sake of peace, this ability could
potentially make this Digimon a guardian of the
Digital World. Guilmon can use its signature move
Rock Breaker to destroy even stone with its rugged
front claws.
English.91:
An extremely unusual Insectoid Digimon with a 
humanoid shape. Stingmon possesses both the 
hard exoskeleton and the simple movements
characteristic of Insectoid Digimon. Excelling 
as an assassin, it prides itself on attacks that 
target vitals with agile movements and precise 
judgment, silencing the enemy with a single 
strike. Stingmon possesses a calm, cool and 
highly intelligent personality. It uses its fearsome
special move Spiking Strike to skewer foes with 
the spikes on its arms.
English.92:
A Digimon brimming with curiosity who loves to 
pull pranks. Gatomon may be small, but it's still 
a rare Sacred Digimon whose appearance belies 
its true power. It wears its Holy Ring on its tail, 
proving that it's a Holy Digimon, although it will 
lose some of its power if it ever loses this ring. 
Besides the Holy Ring, to protect itself, Gatomon 
also wears gloves with long, sharp claws copied
from the data of SaberLeomon. Gatomon's 
special move Lightning Paw uses its claws to 
attack the opponent.
English.93:
A Dark Angel Digimon clothed in jet-black garb.
Devimon was once a radiant Digimon of the Angemon
species, but it became a Dark Angel when it fell into
the distorted space of the Digital World known as the
Dark Area. The prominent Mark of Evil on its chest is
proof of this. Though it has a cunning and malevolent
personality, Devimon is also extremely intelligent.
It's said that any who stare into its glowing red eyes fall
victim to its mind control and become subject to its
whims. Devimon's special move is Death Claw, which
uses its two extendable arms to pierce its opponent.
English.94:
ShineGreymon is a Shining Dragon Digimon that 
fights using energy gathered from the raging heat 
of the sun. One of its special moves is Glorious 
Burst, with which it spreads its giant wings while 
concentrating the light energy inside them to the
utmost limit, then unleashes it all at once. It also 
has the ability to summon the GeoGrey Sword, a
weapon that has all of Gaia's power concentrated 
within its blade.
English.95:
A Beast Knight Digimon completely covered in 
Chrondigizoid armor. Due to the incredible speed
at which MirageGaogamon moves, its enemies feel
like they're seeing a mirage. MirageGaogamon's
special moves include Double Crescent Mirage, by
which it fires dual shockwaves from its hands that
resemble crescent moons, and Full Moon Blaster,
with which it charges up all the energy in its body,
then releases it in the form of a super-dreadnought
class blast from its chest cannon.
English.96:
A Mammal Digimon known for its large ears. Patamon
can use these to fly, but since it can only do so at
a little over 0.5 mph, its its walking speed is said
to be considerably faster. Even so, watching it
struggle to fly is an endearing sight, making it very
popular (although Patamon itself doesn't appreciate
such sentiment). Patamon is extremely obedient and
very good about doing what it's told. It can also use
its hidden holy power without a Holy Ring—a sign
that it's descended from an Ancient species of
Digimon. Patamon's special move is Air Shot, taking
a deep breath and then releasing a powerful blast
of air.
English.97:
A small Digimon resembling a bat. DemiDevimon
serves as a familiar to higher-level Digimon like
Devimon and Myotismon. Despite its low status,
it's rumored to have been responsible for tempting
Devimon, once an Angel Digimon, over to the
Dark Side. What DemiDevimon lacks in attack
power, it makes up for in malicious cunning,
and it's always causing trouble somewhere.
Fond of darkness and typically in the company
of higher-level Digimon, it's rare to see it by
itself. DemiDevimon's special move is Demi Darts,
which throws giant syringes at the enemy to
drain its blood.
English.98:
A giant Android Digimon that added beam cannons 
all over its body, sacrificing the strength of its 
metal shell. JumboGamemon's special moves are 
Megaton Hydro Laser, which shoots high-speed 
water currents from its mouth barrel that can 
penetrate anything, and Jumbo Crater, which
strafes with all of its beam cannons over 360 
degrees, leaving a crater in the earth in its wake. 
This embodies the very concept of offense as the
best defense.
English.100:
A brutal Beast Man Digimon formed when Lopmon
underwent Dark Digivolution due to anger and
hatred. Wendigomon isn't completely evil, and the
kindness it had as Lopmon still resides somewhere
deep in its heart. But the power of its rage overrides
this kindness, making Wendigomon devote itself
completely to destruction. In addition to its raw
power, Wendigomon has the ability to manipulate
time and space, and is able to warp by passing
through other dimensions as well as create
subdimensions of its own. Its special move is
Howling Destroyer, which creates a shockwave
capable of shattering even boulders.
English.101:
A High Angel Digimon with eight shining, silver 
wings. MagnaAngemon serves as a marshal of 
the Digital World, supervising and surveying the
many Angel Digimon within. Furthermore, it's 
the mouthpiece of the Essence of Light that 
attempts to preserve the order of the Digital
World. Though MagnaAngemon usually takes 
the form of a priest, when the Digital World is 
shrouded in the Essence of Darkness, it changes
into its Battle Mode to strike down evil.
In this Battle Mode, MagnaAngemon consigns 
the opponent to oblivion with the Beam Shield 
on its left arm and the holy sword Excalibur 
equipped to its right arm. MagnaAngemon's
special move is Heaven's Gate, which it uses 
to open a door into an inescapable pocket 
dimension, consigning its foe to oblivion.
English.102:
A martial artist Digimon discovered in the hinterland
of a mountainous Chinese province. 
Turuiemon has wandered the world in pursuit of 
its longstanding foes—viruses that exploit e-mail 
for malicious aims. It's blessed with exceptional
potential as a martial artist, though it has yet to 
develop its skills. Turuiemon is a practitioner of
Togaken, a fighting style of its own creation.
Its special move is Gauntlet Claw, which involves
a series of blows made with the Rabbit-Horned
Iron Claws on both hands. This combo attack
capitalizes on its rabbit-like agility and powerful
high leaps.
English.103:
A Crustacean Digimon that attached metal data that
had been dissolved into the Net Ocean to its body,
dramatically increasing its combat capability.
Crabmon attacks with the giant blades on its left
pincer and the powerful grip of its right pincer.
For defense, it relies on its spiny shell to damage
attackers, and is utterly self-confident in battle.
Crabmon is fully aware of the weak points of its
joints and underbelly, and thus rarely leaves them
exposed. It enjoys trapping its opponents, and is
something of a prankster. Crabmon's special move
is Scissors Execution, which launches its sharp
left pincer right for its adversary's throat.
English.104:
Susanomon is renowned in Eastern folklore as the 
ultimate god of destruction and the ruler of 
regeneration. It's said to appear when the Net 
experiences abnormalities, nullifying the existing 
system and building a new one in its place. 
Susanomon's special moves are Ama no Habakiri, 
which cleaves anything and everything under 
heaven with the blade of light released from its 
ZERO-ARMS: Orochi, and Yakusa no Ikazuchi, the 
ultimate technique by which it points its 
ZERO-ARMS: Orochi blade of light toward the 
heavens, transforming the blade into destructive 
lightning that then rains down upon the world.
English.105:
A hidden form of Gallantmon clad in shining crimson 
armor. Gallantmon: Crimson Mode unleashes its full 
power, heating its armored parts until they're red-hot. 
As a result, it can't stay in Crimson Mode for long. 
Gallantmon: Crimson Mode's chest contains a 
DigiCore with a Digital Hazard sealed within it that
causes wings of energy to radiate from its back 
when it releases the power in its body. It wields the
lance of light Gungnir and the sword of light 
Blutgang, which are energy weapons without form. 
Its special move Invincible Sword cleaves the enemy
with Blutgang, and Quo Vadis tears apart foes on an
atomic level with Gungnir before consigning them to
another dimension.
English.106:
A Mega + Digimon born from a mutation caused by
fusing massive numbers of In-Training Diaboromon.
Diaboromon have the ability to copy themselves en
masse, but each copy is inferior to the original. The
fusion of a large number of In-Training Diaboromon
together, however—instead of weakening them—
concentrated their abilities into this single, more
powerful entity. Armageddemon's special moves
are Black Rain, which scatters energy shells from its
back into the air to rain down in all directions, and
Ultimate Flare, which fires a beam of destructive
energy from its gaping maw.
English.107:
A feminine Dark Angel Digimon with a noble presence. 
LadyDevimon's Dark Side Power is strong, pure and
without equal. There are almost no instances of one
of these Digimon being successfully cultivated on a
personal computer. LadyDevimon's special move is
Darkness Wave, which releases countless, flying,
batlike creatures that burn the opponent to a crisp.
English.111:
A Digimon resembling a troublesome imp that
loves mischief. Crafty creatures devoid of courage,
Goblimon always move in groups, hiding in the
shadows of trees or buildings while waiting in
ambush. But if the situation goes south, they
scatter in all directions, fleeing at full speed.
Their intelligence, on the other hand, is above
average for Rookie Digimon. Goblimon's special
move is Goblin Strike, which hurls fireballs at
Mach speed.
English.112:
Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead,
this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental
"Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon
were discovered. The personality characteristic of the
Combat Species is particularly apparent in Dorumon.
It has a strong instinct for battle, biting and roaring
at anything and everything, though it apparently feels
a sense of attachment to something after biting it.
The strong life force data of the legendary "dragon"
was found to have been hidden in the deepest part
of its DigiCore during an experiment, and Dorumon
apparently has the potential to grow into a mighty
Digimon. Dorumon's special move is Metal Cannon,
which fires an iron ball from its mouth.
English.113:
A subspecies of Numemon whose entire body glitters 
gold, having incorporated data from gold mines into 
itself. GoldNumemon's special move is Goldurian Rush,
by which it hurls a stream of golden poop.
English.114:
A new type of Digimon only recently discovered.
Veemon is a surviving member of a species that
once thrived in the dawn of the Digital World.
This allows it to use Digi-Eggs to perform a type of
pseudo-Digivolution known as Armor Digivolution.
Of all its peers, Veemon is one of the best
Combat Species. It possesses hidden power, and
uses Armor Digivolution to bring out its explosive
abilities. Though a troublemaker and a prankster by
nature, Veemon also has a strong sense of justice.
Its special move is Veemon Headbutt, which knocks
down foes with a powerful blow with the top of its head.
English.115:
Huckmon went through strict training, refining an 
unparalleled combat sense and achieving mental, 
technical and physical strength in this form.
BaoHuckmon continues to train while aiming for 
even greater heights, accumulating combat 
experience through countless battles against
strong foes. The more this combat expert fights, 
the more it evolves. BaoHuckmon's desire to 
become a Royal Knight has only increased as it's
grown. It doesn't allow others to determine its 
best course of action, believing it should observe 
and decide on an approach for itself. 
With its special move Fif Cross, BaoHuckmon
cleaves its opponent with its sharp claws.
English.116:
SaviorHuckmon is a Digimon that has traveled far 
and wide. After repeated meetings and partings with 
other Digimon and surviving countless scenes of 
carnage, it finally Digivolved into this form.
SaviorHuckmon continues to join in the endless 
struggles that occur throughout the Digital World, 
seeking to bring an end to these hostilities and aid 
local Digimon who have suffered under the strife.
SaviorHuckmon walks on two legs despite both of 
them being blades, and now that its arms and tail 
have sprouted crimson blades as well, its attack 
style has become more offensive. The crystal in 
its chest serves as physical proof of its tireless 
efforts to grow stronger. SaviorHuckmon's special 
move Trident Saber uses the crimson blades on its
arms and tail to slice mercilessly through foes, 
even those covered in Chrondigizoid.
English.117:
A mythical Holy Bird Digimon that lives in the 
stratosphere over 130,000 feet above ground. 
Varodurumon has six giant wings, with the largest
pair having a nearly 100-foot wingspan. 
Referred to in myth as a guardian of the sky, 
legend has it that this ancient Digimon has existed
ever since the creation of the Digital World. 
Varodurumon's feathers constantly give off the 
holy light known as "Purge Shine," which serves
as a barrier that completely nullifies any attack 
made with evil intent. Its special move is 
Aurora Undulation, which amplifies the purifying 
light of Purge Shine to peak brightness before 
unleashing it upon its foes.
English.118:
"Chaosmon" is the codename used for Digimon that 
shouldn't exist—bugs in the Digital World's Central 
Dogma that should be absolutely impossible.
Chaosmon: Valdur Arm is believed to have been 
born from the DNA Digivolution of BanchoLeomon 
and Varodurumon, as traces of each can be seen 
on its arms. Its special moves are Bancho Blade, 
which unleashes an unstoppable strike from its
sword of the same name on its Bancho Arm, and
Aurora Blaster, which fires a purifying blast of 
light from its Valdur Arm.
English.126:
A Holy Knight Digimon and member of the Royal 
Knights. The Royal Knights are the highest-ranking 
Digimon when it comes to Network security, and no
Digimon has ever been able to crack their stalwart 
defenses. But given Gallantmon's Virus attribute, 
its role as one of the chief protectors of the Net 
inherently conflicts with its nature. This means 
there's always a chance, however small, that it 
may slip and become a threat instead.
Gallantmon is clad in holy armor made of 99.9% 
pure Chrondigizoid, and it wields the holy lance
"Gram" in its right hand while bearing the
holy shield "Aegis" in its left. Its special moves
are Lightning Joust, which unleashes a powerful
thrust from Gram, and Shield of the Just, which
fires a purifying beam from Aegis.
English.127:
KingEtemon is a supreme being, the self-proclaimed 
"King of Digimon" that stands out even among its 
peers. It even goes so far as to refer to itself as the 
"King of Kings." Dressed in its dashing Monkey Suit,
which prominently features the characters for 
"Great King" on its chest, KingEtemon struts about 
like a star (though other Digimon treat it as little 
more than a joke). KingEtemon's special move is 
Monkey Wrench, which puts on a performance
that robs opponents of their will to fight.
English.128:
The "King of Insects" governing all Insectoid
Digimon. TyrantKabuterimon only acts at
night, making a stronghold of the Under Forest 
deep underground below a dark forest. It can 
control any and all Insectoid Digimon at will, 
and almost never fights, itself. Its carapace is
composed of high-density Chrondigizoid that 
can't be damaged by the average Digimon. 
TyrantKabuterimon uses Shine of Bee to unleash 
an unblockable incandescent explosion from its 
entire body, instantly reducing all hostiles to ash. 
It also uses Bee Cyclone to summon subordinate 
insects that form an impregnable wall of bugs.
English.129:
A wicked god Digimon known as the "Sinful Priest 
of the Ocean Floor." Dragomon is thought to be 
evolved from a computer virus that infects ship 
computers, sending their bearings and routes 
off-course. Dragomon bundles its countless
tentacles into a humanoid shape, but its actual 
identity is a Digivolution of a strange Mollusk 
Digimon. Dragomon's special move is Forbidden
Trident, with which it hurls its trident with
tremendous strength. For its defeated foes, it
holds the rosary around its neck and adopts a
sort of mourning pose.
English.130:
An Ancient Fish Digimon with tough skin and 
enormous claws. This Digimon is discovered in 
the Net Ocean whenever computer networks
destroyed by malicious hackers are repaired.
Coelamon's body composition is very primitive, 
with fins developed into limbs. Based on these 
facts, it's thought that primordial Digimon born 
in the Net Ocean underwent various evolutions in 
order to come onto land, growing more numerous 
and differentiating into various types in the 
process. Coelamon's special move is Fossil Bite, 
which attacks enemies with its massive claws.
English.132:
Seadramon who survive the harsh environment 
surrounding the Folder Continent take on this form 
in order to continue living in the Digital World, 
where only the strong endure. Through this 
Digivolution, MegaSeadramon's body became a 
size larger, the shell covering its head hardened 
and a lightning-shaped blade sprouted from its 
forehead. It's also more intelligent than Seadramon, 
and will relentlessly seek out and destroy foes like a 
homing torpedo. MegaSeadramon's special move 
is Lightning Javelin, which fires a powerful bolt of 
lightning from the blade on its forehead. Its head 
shell contains a generator specifically to make 
this special move possible.
English.133:
A Seadramon-species Digimon Digivolved into an 
evil entity. WaruSeadramon controls the power of 
darkness with the blade-like horn on its forehead. 
This Digimon has grown even craftier and more 
persistent than MegaSeadramon when it comes to 
chasing down prey. WaruSeadramon's special 
move is Darkstrom, which swallows foes up with 
whirlpools composed of dark power.
English.134:
An Ultimate Android Digimon also known as a "Giant 
Growlmon." WarGrowlmon is huge, as this nickname
suggests, and the upper half of its body is composed 
of powerful Chrondigizoid metal. It can also fly
thanks to the twin vernier thrusters on its shoulders, 
allowing it to deal with threats both on land and in the
air. The muzzle-like restraint on WarGrowlmon's jaws 
is there to control its immense power. The cable-like 
Assault Balancer that can be freely extended from 
its back doubles as a weapon with which to pierce 
foes. WarGrowlmon's special move is Atomic Blaster, 
which fires the twin guns on its chest to destroy
enemies at the atomic level.
English.135:
This final form of Garurumon has been enhanced 
by turning most of its body into metal. Despite this 
process, MetalGarurumon hasn't lost any agility, 
and it can destroy its foes using the countless 
weapons hidden all over its body. The four laser
sights at the tip of its nose emit invisible beams, 
and MetalGarurumon makes use of a wide array 
of sensors, including those for infrared and X-rays, 
to analyze its targets. This makes it impossible to 
escape from MetalGarurumon, even in perfect
darkness. What's more, the mechanical arms 
extending from MetalGarurumon's back can emit
photoelectric beam wings, allowing it to fly through
Net Space at incredible speed. MetalGarurumon's
special move is Freezing Breath, with which it
breathes out a blast of air at absolute zero that
freezes everything it touches. This move instantly
suspends the vital functions of any living creature
it hits. It also possesses Ice Wolf Claw, which
annihilates foes by unleashing every weapon in
MetalGarurumon's arsenal at once.
English.136:
A Beast Digimon born through the fusion of data 
obtained by observing the sun. Coronamon has a 
strong sense of justice and a pure, simple-minded
personality. Its special move is Corona Flame, which
converts all of the stamina in its body into flame
power to shoot a fiery missile at the enemy from its 
forehead.
English.137:
A Beast Digimon known as the "Soaring Lion." 
Firamon is a helpful leader among Digimon that 
protects certain ruins in the Digital World. Its
special move is Flame Dive, with which it envelops
its body in flames and dive-bombs the enemy
from the skies above.
English.138:
Flaremon is a Beast Man Digimon. Although its
impressive mane and overwhelming presence may
make it seem intimidating, its strength of will makes
it brave any hardship for the sake of its comrades.
Its special move is Crimson Wave of the Beast King,
which concentrates fierce flame and a leonine
fighting spirit into its fist before unleashing a
lion-shaped energy blast.
English.139:
An Armor Beast Digimon that has Digivolved through
the Digi-Egg of Friendship. The Digi-Egg of Friendship
has the attribute of Thunder, allowing those who
equip it to move with the speed of lightning to face
off against their foes, then defeat them with
electrically-charged attacks. Lighdramon's special
move is Lightning Blade, which shoots an electric
sword from the lightning-imbued blade on its head.
English.140:
A Beast Man Digimon that Digivolved from Garurumon,
and can now walk on two legs. Becoming bipedal
reduced WereGarurumon's speed, but turned it into a
Commando-type Digimon with enhanced offensive and
defensive power, as well as a knack for tactics. Retaining
the leg strength of Garurumon, its kicks are extremely
powerful, and its jumping ability is among the best in
the world of Digimon. WereGarurumon is also
extremely loyal and will do anything if ordered by its
master, making it highly reliable. Its special move is
Wolf Claw, which slices opponents to shreds with its
sharp claws.
English.141:
An Armor Beast Digimon that has Digivolved with 
the Digi-Egg of Love. The Digi-Egg of Love has the
attribute of Wind, allowing those who equip it to 
spread their wings and soar through the heavens, 
like a gale whipping through the ether. When it 
comes to aerial combat, Halsemon outclasses 
enemy Digimon in speed and attack power. Its 
special move is Tempest Wing, which generates
massive tornadoes from its spinning body.
English.142:
An Armor Mutant Digimon that has Digivolved with 
the Digi-Egg of Sincerity. The Digi-Egg of Sincerity
has the attribute of Plant, allowing those who 
equip it to blend in with nature, hiding in wind like 
a floating leaf only to appear in the enemy's blind 
spot and land a precise attack. Shurimon is the 
epitome of a ninja. Named after its shuriken, its
special move is Double Stars, with which it hurls
the giant shuriken on its back at the enemy from
high in the air.
English.143:
A small, dinosaur-like Reptile Digimon 
that has developed the ability to walk 
on two legs. Since it hasn't fully matured, 
it still lacks strength, but its fierce 
disposition makes it reckless. Hard, 
sharp claws grow from its hands and feet, 
and it makes full use of them in battle. 
This Digimon shows much potential, 
promising Digivolution into a great 
and powerful Digimon. Its special 
move is Spitfire Blast.
English.144:
An Armor Insectoid Digimon that has Digivolved 
with the Digi-Egg of Knowledge. The Digi-Egg of 
Knowledge has the attribute of Earth, allowing 
those who equip it to manipulate the very ground. 
As its unique form suggests, Digmon never loses 
against other Digimon in underground combat.
Its special move is Gold Rush, which rotates the 
drills on its nose and hands at high speed to 
unleash a concentrated strike.
English.145:
An Armor Aquatic Digimon that has Digivolved 
with the Digi-Egg of Reliability. The Digi-Egg of 
Reliability has the attribute of Water, allowing 
those who equip it to demonstrate their true 
power underwater. Submarimon swims freely
through the vast oceans, and the skills it unleashes 
in underwater battles can only be rivaled by other
Aquatic Digimon. Its special move is Oxygen 
Homing, which fires super-compressed oxygen.
English.146:
An Armor Holy Beast Digimon that has Digivolved with 
the Digi-Egg of Hope. The Digi-Egg of Hope has a 
Holy attribute, allowing those who equip it to wield 
sacred power. This power allows Pegasusmon to exhibit 
absolute strength against evil beings. Its special move 
Silver Blaze, fires a holy beam from its forehead.
English.147:
An Armor Holy Beast Digimon that has Digivolved with 
the Digi-Egg of Light. The Digi-Egg of Light has the
attribute of Light, allowing those who equip it to purify 
darkness with luminescent power. Though Gatomon
isn't a descendant of an ancient species of Digimon, 
it's able to Armor Digivolve into Nefertimon by
awakening a dormant special ability within its data 
composition. Its special move is Rosetta Stone,
which summons an enormous stone tablet engraved
with ancient DigiCode inscriptions to attack foes.
English.148:
A High Angel Digimon with the appearance of a 
beautiful woman. Though previously classified as 
an Angel Digimon, the great power of its abilities 
makes it clear that it's a High Angel Digimon. 
Champion-level Angels tend to have six wings, 
while Ultimate-level Angels have eight wings. 
Angewomon is calm by nature, but doesn't tolerate 
wickedness, and will continue to attack until its foes 
are reformed. Due to its strength of spirit and great 
power, it's regarded as a goddess-like figure of the 
Digital World. Angewomon's special move is Celestial 
Arrow—also known as Heaven's Punishment—which 
fires a devastating lightning attack.
English.149:
An enormous Dark Dragon Digimon with eight
heads. Seven of these are fakes, however, with
only the black one in the center actually being
part of its body. Orochimon's origins date back to
long ago, when it wrought havoc in the Ancient
Digital World. Its strength was such that it drove
an entire area to the brink of destruction, until
it was sealed away by the servant of a being
seeking to maintain harmony in the Digital World
Orochimon's special move is Ame no Murakumo,
which transforms the end of its tail into a
sharp blade to rend its foes.
English.150:
A darker side of Gallantmon, in which its nature 
as a Virus Digimon has come to the fore. 
ChaosGallantmon's mind and spirit have been 
thoroughly corrupted, transforming it into nothing 
more than a "Digital Hazard" bent on bringing 
destruction to the Digital World.
ChaosGallantmon wields the demonic lance 
"Balmung" in its right hand, while bearing the 
demonic shield "Gorgon" in its left. In every way, 
it's Gallantmon's antithesis. ChaosGallantmon's 
special moves are Demonic Disaster, which makes 
a series of powerful thrusts with its demonic lance, 
and Judecca Prison, which releases a wave of 
corrosive dark energy from its demonic shield.
English.151:
A full-fledged Reptile Digimon, despite being covered
in fur. Gabumon is an extremely shy, timid creature
who always gathers up data left behind by
Garurumon to wear like a pelt. Garurumon's pelt
also serves to protect Gabumon, since other
Digimon fear the original owner. Gabumon's personality
makes a complete about-face when it wears the
pelt. Its special move is Blue Blaster.
English.162:
A Digimon with power over water, it bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. Lanamon has a sharp
intuition and an changeable mood, due perhaps to 
the fact that it used to operate mainly in the ocean 
area of a weather forecasting system. Its emotions 
are tempestuous, acting like a lovely young lady 
when in a good mood, and crying like a hysterical
baby when it gets upset. Lanamon uses few direct 
attacks in battle, relying instead on manipulated 
rain or other indirect methods of fighting. That 
being said, its battle strength swells during surges 
of emotion, with its combat prowess growing 
unfathomably strong when crying. Lanamon's 
special move is Rain Stream, which focuses 
torrential rain to crush the enemy.
English.163:
A Digimon with power over water, it bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. Half humanoid and 
half beast, Calmaramon can spin its tentacles at 
high speed for offense, or gather them together 
into a defensive wall, making for a versatile tool in 
combat. If it can't finish an opponent with its 
tentacles, Calmaramon withdraws into its mantle, 
increasing the power of its attacks as it takes on 
the form of a giant squid. This mantle is even more 
resilient than its tentacles, rendering external 
physical attacks against it harmless. Though 
Calmaramon is more accustomed to the seas and 
skies, it can skillfully maneuver its ten tentacles to 
move around on land like a giant hermit crab as well. 
Much like a witch, it's crafty and quick to anger. 
Its special move is Titanic Charge, which spins
its hardened mantle to drill into foes.
English.168:
A member of the Olympos XII, a god that presides 
over the heavens, and a Digimon that governs 
thunder and weather. Jupitermon always judges
good and evil on the battlefield, delivering divine 
punishment to the wicked. Such judgment is handed 
down indifferently, without emotion. Those who 
disagree with Jupitermon's decision can challenge 
it and overturn the judgment upon victory, but as of 
now, no one has ever accomplished this feat. It can 
clap the hammers on both arms together to summon 
small thunderclouds. It uses Punish Judge to strike 
an opponent with its hammer, engraving a mark on 
its body and postponing its punishment. When 
Jupitermon decides to execute said punishment, 
the sentence is carried out by striking that foe with 
extremely high-voltage lightning. It uses its ultimate 
special move Wide Plasment to change its body 
into ultra-high-voltage plasma. This inflicts divine 
punishment in the area around Jupitermon, 
disintegrating any and all it touches.
English.169:
An entirely changed version of Jupitermon, who is 
typically objective and in control of its emotions 
when dealing judgment, but has become unable 
to quell its anger when facing an enemy that has
committed an unforgiveable sin. Jupitermon: Wrath 
Mode summons its godly blade Keraunos with a 
loud roar, and its body grows dozens of times larger 
in size as armor and lightning envelop it from head 
to toe. Its rage is made evident by the violent 
lightning that surrounds it, yet the efficient calm of 
its movements exerts an incredible pressure upon 
its enemy. Jupitermon: Wrath Mode takes Keraunos
in both of its hands and slices its opponents apart
with a single swing in its Keraunos Divide attack.
It can also call upon the heavens to cast judgment
on its defeated enemy with Dios Thunder. If the
attack hits, the enemy is judged as guilty, and if
it misses, they're not guilty. Digimon judged as
guilty by the attack have their data completely
destroyed.
English.170:
Jupitermon's partner, and one of the Olympos XII. 
Junomon takes its place on the battlefield as 
Jupitermon's loving protector, and is constantly
seeking to predict, detect and root out insurgents 
who would defy Jupitermon's will. It has a solid grasp 
on all of Jupitermon's tendencies, perhaps due to its 
overwhelmingly affectionate nature and deep love 
of Jupitermon. Junomon's special moves are Needle 
Hive, which skewers foes with the katars on its arms, 
and Graceful Lance, which automatically attacks 
foes around it with its sentient lances.
English.171:
Another form awakened from the depths of 
Junomon's heart, one that is evil. Unceasing 
opposition to its beloved Jupitermon steals away 
the time the two of them spend together, causing 
Junomon to be consumed by envy. As the vitality 
gradually leaves its countenance, it's completely 
consumed by darkness instead. Eventually, 
Junomon reveals a new, masked face. Through this 
mask, Junomon perceives all Digimon around it to 
be evil and does everything it can to slaughter them. 
However, Jupitermon can't sense this form of 
Junomon, so it never has to face Jupitermon's
