judgment. Junomon: Hysteric Mode's special moves 
include Welcome Demise, with which it successively 
stabs the enemy with the lances of both arms, and 
Chain Lash, with which it wraps its enemy's entire 
body in chains and destroys it after forcing it to 
confess its sins.
English.172:
This compassionate Digimon governs the power of 
love, and is one of the Olympos XII. Even in the most
desolate wastelands, wherever Venusmon goes, 
beautiful flowers bloom and the earth around it is
renewed with youthful vigor. Many Digimon worship 
Venusmon because of its beauty and purity. By 
wearing a blindfold, it's able to perceive the world 
as it truly is with its mind's eye, seeing through any 
falsehood or deceit. Hiding its eyes also suppresses 
its aura of glamor, doubling as an act of consideration
and reducing the number of Digimon that would 
otherwise swoon in its presence. Venusmon has 
two small but constant companions, the bird Olive
and the scallop Hotan, and the three friends keep 
up an open and lively conversation. Since Venusmon 
is the Digimon that governs love, its every action in 
battle soothes its opponents' hearts. With LOVE 
YOU, it can make a foe fall unconscious by blowing 
it a kiss and making its heart skip a beat. If its bird 
Olive pecks an enemy on the head, it falls under the 
spell of Peace Fantasia, which can soothe the heart 
of even the most savage of beasts.
English.173:
One of the Olympos XII, and a Deity Digimon that 
possesses flame energy equivalent to the very 
sun's power. This awesome strength, capable of 
melting down and purifying any substance, is such 
that even Apollomon—with all its intense fervor 
and pride—can barely contain it. Apollomon's 
special moves are Sol Blaster, which unleashes 
an incandescent solar orb formed from the flame 
sphere on its back, and Phoebus Blow, which 
concentrates all of its latent power into a single
punch.
English.174:
This war god Digimon resembling a leopard man
is one of the mysterious Olympos XII, 
who possess abilities rivaling even the Royal
Knights, guardian deities of the Net. Each of the 
Olympos XII protects its own region, acting in 
the shadows and maintaining a neutral position 
during incidents in the Digital World. Marsmon 
well understands all hand-to-hand techniques 
in the world—including skills utilizing foul
play—and possesses absolute confidence in 
any one-on-one fight against those like itself. 
It relies mostly on wrestling moves, but its
focus on victory and glory means it will whip out 
hidden weapons like its Tria Knuckles or Metal 
Cothurnus when it finds itself on its back foot.
Even so, Marsmon brings its true power to bear 
when fighting with bare hands and feet. Its 
special move Corona Sanctions is a glorious
mid-air killing technique that clads Marsmon
in flames.
English.175:
The Virus version of WarGreymon, 
known and feared as the "Jet-Black 
Dragon Warrior." Despite being 
opposed to the values and beliefs 
of the Virus Buster WarGreymon, 
BlackWarGreymon is devoted to its own 
form of justice. Loathing cruelty 
and deceit, it looks down on Digimon 
it considers dishonorable—including 
fellow Virus-attribute types. How it 
became a Virus is a mystery, and it's 
worth noting that the "Brave Shield" 
on its back lacks the Crest of Courage. 
Its special move Dark Terra Force, 
though similar to WarGreymon's 
Terra Force, gathers all the negative 
emotions in the world and concentrates 
them into a single point before firing.
English.176:
One of the Olympos XII, Ceresmon is a gigantic 
bird Digimon that bears the forest Karpos Hulē,
renowned for its fruit celebrated as the sweetest
delicacy in the Digital World, on its back. With
a body composed of giant rocks and fertile soil,
Ceresmon in flight resembles a floating island
more than anything else.
Ceresmon Medium, which is Ceresmon's true
form, resides at the head of the island. Ceresmon
Medium possesses almost no combat ability and
rarely appears before others. However, on rare
occasions, it apparently shows itself to those it
trusts without bringing along the giant bird.
Ceresmon Medium has a gentle personality and
a heart overflowing with compassion. It offers
hungry Digimon fruits from Karpos Hulē, and
allows injured Digimon to take shelter in the forest
until they've recovered. However, if any prove
ungrateful for the bounty of nature, bring harm
to the trees or defile the land for sport, Ceresmon
Medium's nature shifts and it becomes a truly
frightful forest demon.
Ceresmon's special move is Island Freefall, with
which it slams its massive body directly into its
foe, sending powerful tremors and violent winds
surging in a wide berth around the crash site.
Ceresmon also has Burning Blood Shell, which
shoots a huge, scorching ball of magma from its
mouth.
English.177:
BlueMeramon is a Fire Digimon that burns hotter 
than a Champion Meramon. Its special move is
Cold Flame.
English.178:
This Digimon god of smithing is one of the Olympos 
XII. Vulcanusmon is responsible for creating most 
of the Digital World's best-known weapons,
including the infamous Beelzemon's beloved 
Berenjena. Vulcanusmon has the spirit of a true 
craftsman, along with an obstinate personality. It
takes the measure of all of its clients, and if it feels 
they can't master or won't treasure the weapon
they've requested, it denies them. Even when 
Vulcanusmon does agree to make a weapon, it 
aligns the quality of its work to its impression of the
wielder. Nevertheless, Vulcanusmon was so taken 
with Beelzemon's strength that it worked diligently 
to craft an exceptional weapon when it created 
Berenjena. Vulcanusmon prefers to be left in peace, 
working away with its eight arms, but can also 
leverage its skill as a craftsman in battle. With its 
special move Pinpoint Weapon Works, it makes 
masterful use of its fiery "Bomber Art" welder to 
instantly craft the perfect weapon for any combat 
situation. When it really wants to go all out, though, 
it uses Appropriate Works, which uses Pinpoint 
Weapon Works repeatedly to forge weapons for each 
of its eight arms. Despite all this, Vulcanusmon's 
own combat ability isn't particularly high, and it 
prefers to avoid battle whenever possible.
English.179:
One of the Olympos XII, this Digimon boasts that 
it's the heaviest drinker of the Digital World. 
Bacchusmon has a cheerful disposition and is
well-suited to looking after others. Day or night, 
it always looks to gather Rookie and Champion 
Digimon together to throw a party. Bacchusmon
has the ability to produce any form of alcohol 
inside its body, and if it takes a liking to another 
Digimon at one of these parties, it's known to
offer it the drink of its choice. Bacchusmon itself 
has a taste for fruit wines, with its favorite variety 
produced from the fermented fruits of Karpos 
Hulē, the forest carried on Ceresmon's back. 
Whenever Bacchusmon has a moment to spare, 
it begs Ceresmon to make it some fruit wine. 
Because of this, the pair are on very good terms, 
and are often seen together. Bacchusmon's special
move is Cook of the Abyss, with which it wraps its 
arms around a foe, alters its compositional data to 
a suitable finger food and then eats it. Bacchusmon 
also has Party of the Heavens, with which it 
produces a form of alcohol laced with poisons
that can cause drowsiness and paralysis and then 
blasts enemies with the concoction to stupefy them.
Furthermore, the poison data that it produces is 
one subject of the Crack Team's research. There 
are a number of credible rumors that speculate
that Bacchusmon's poison data is linked to the 
development of bacteriological weapons and
high-profile assassination plots.
English.180:
A Digimon that rules over the realm of the dead and 
uses fear and violence to terrorize evil. Plutomon, 
shrouded in deep shadow, stalks through the land 
in search of villains and criminals who deserve to 
be sent to the realm of the dead. Plutomon delights 
in chewing up evildoers with its mouths filled with 
rows of sharp fangs, and lets out a sinister chattering 
noise as it seeks out its prey. The combination of this
and its fearsome appearance frightens even good 
Digimon. Plutomon's abilities all have the disquieting
power to fling villains down to the realm of the dead. 
In one of those moves, Hell's Gate, a giant mouth
appears from the darkness and swallows enemies 
whole, and their data is broken down into scraps. 
The Haggard Cluster move has the fangs of its chest 
release a darkness that absorbs and vaporizes any 
substance in its path. Plutomon shares the goal of 
punishing evil with Jupitermon of the Olympos XII. 
However, there's a longstanding animosity between 
the two because Jupitermon doesn't approve of 
Plutomon's cruel methods.
English.181:
A Deity Digimon and member of the Olympos XII 
that resembles a woman. Mervamon is the form 
of Minervamon that has amassed experience and
achievements over time, and it has a much calmer 
and more mature personality compared to its 
previous form. It has come to pursue elegance 
and charm—observed in abundance in both its 
mannerisms and conduct—and exudes sensuality 
into its surroundings. It even seeks charm in battle, 
performing a refined, graceful dance to fascinate 
those who behold it. That's why more than a few
Digimon become fans of Mervamon upon observing 
this dance. The Love Poison sprayed from the mouth 
of the Medullia on its left arm bewitches any who 
inhale it, letting Mervamon wring the life out of them. 
Madness Merry-Go-Round DX is a spinning slash 
with its greatsword Olympia Kai and Medullia, 
creating a tornado that instantly tears any foe it
touches to shreds.
English.182:
MetalGarurumon (Black) is a 
Virus-attribute MetalGarurumon 
equipped with freeze weapons all 
over its body. It has a terrifying 
personality, and when the laser sights 
in its nose pick up a target, it chases 
it down relentlessly without regard 
to whether it's friend or foe before 
blasting it with missiles. Its special 
moves include Garuru Tomahawk, 
which fires a huge missile called 
the Freeze Bomber from its chest, 
and Ice Wolf Claw, which fires all 
the weapons on its body at once 
to wipe out its foes.
English.183:
A Deity Digimon with the upper body of a human 
and the lower body of a mountain goat. Aegiomon
is usually affiliated with the same musical troupe
as Sirenmon, reveling in the music by playing the
Syrinx flute hanging from his waist. He loves peace,
and although he dislikes fighting, an unknown
quantity of power dwells within him, and he
demonstrates exceptional combat prowess when
fighting to protect something he cares about.
Aegiomon plays Attract Echo on his Syrinx to draw
the listener's attention, stealing its sense of self and
making it unable to see anything but Aegiomon as it
remains fixated on the tune. This gives other Digimon
the chance to escape or pursue said listener.
Aegiomon's special move is Stun Beat Blow, which
strikes the opponent and discharges the electricity
in Aegiomon's body through his arms, numbing the
enemy's nerves and rendering it unable to move.
English.184:
A Deity Digimon that synthesizes the abilities of 
various species, using a human body as its base. 
This synthesis is said to have resulted from the 
pursuit of the ultimate goal of omnipotence, 
dramatically changing this Digimon's form to match
its environment. This form is based on
Dragon-species data, which would ordinarily lie 
dormant within its body, centered around the crystal
in its chest, but Aegiochusmon manifested this
data onto the surface of its body, establishing it as
armor. This armor is a power suit that's not only for
defense, but which also acts as muscle, dramatically
increasing attack power. Aegiochusmon uses its
special move Bolt Break Knockdown to perform a
punch rush with fists coiled in lightning produced
from its horn, or Lightning Pile to drive a pile-shaped
bolt down on the enemy from above, driving them
into the ground. If this move pierces the enemy once,
subsequently released piles then connect without 
fail, no matter where they're thrown.
English.185:
A Deity Digimon that synthesizes the abilities of 
various species, using a human body as its base. 
This synthesis is said to have resulted from the 
pursuit of the ultimate goal of omnipotence, 
dramatically changing this Digimon's form to 
match its environment. This form is based on
Evil-species data, which would ordinarily lie 
dormant within its body, centered around the 
crystal in its chest, but Aegiochusmon: Dark has
allowed the Evil data to proliferate throughout its 
whole body. The malevolence of Evil types bubbles
forth in both mind and body, causing it to treat 
everything it sees as prey to be hunted. A virus lurks
within the red electricity discharged from its body, 
making this special Digimon a Vaccine-attribute type 
that also creates viruses. It injects the viruses it 
generates into the wounds it inflicts on enemies, 
making for a terrifying attack that destroys victims 
from within. Aegiochusmon: Dark uses its special 
moves Triangler to mince foes with three scythes 
and Plasmadness to shoot dark electricity gathered 
in both hands.
English.186:
A Deity Digimon that synthesizes the abilities of 
various species, using a human body as its base. 
This synthesis is said to have resulted from the 
pursuit of the ultimate goal of omnipotence, 
dramatically changing this Digimon's form to 
match its environment. This form is based on
Angel-species data, which would ordinarily lie 
dormant within its body, centered around the 
crystal in its chest, but Aegiochusmon: Holy has
spread this data throughout its body, and its heart 
is as clear as a pool of reflective water. Using the
shields on its hands, it can channel the 
overwhelming vaccine welling up from within into 
weapons such as short swords or a defensive 
barrier that no Virus data can penetrate.
Aegiochusmon: Holy's special moves are 
Lightning Shower, which rains a barrage of short 
swords down on foes from the sky, and 
Circlet Defense, which generates a defensive 
barrier that repels an enemy's attack. The attack 
is reflected back with an added jolt of electricity, 
making for a powerful counter.
English.187:
A Deity Digimon that synthesizes the abilities of 
various species, using a human body as its base. 
This synthesis is said to have resulted from the 
pursuit of the ultimate goal of omnipotence, 
dramatically changing this Digimon's form to 
match its environment. This form is based on
Android-species data, which would ordinarily lie 
dormant within its body, centered around the 
crystal in its chest, but Aegiochusmon: Blue has
concentrated this data primarily into the upper 
left side of its body. It comes equipped with a 
power-unlocking mechanism characteristic of 
androids, and a lock-on capability that ensures
targets never escape. Aegiochusmon: Blue can 
even detach its giant left arm, known as its 
Mechanization Powered Arm, to seek out and
attack a locked-on enemy before reattaching the
arm again. Its special move is Penetra-laser,
which fires a beam from the fingertips of its
Mechanization Powered Arm. When the arm
is attached to Aegiochusmon: Blue's body, it
can use Powered Ignition, which gathers energy
into its palm to unleash at its foe in a charging
blast.
English.188:
A Deity Digimon that synthesizes the abilities of
various species, using a human body as its base.
This synthesis is said to have resulted from the
pursuit of the ultimate goal of omnipotence,
dramatically changing this Digimon's form to
match its environment. This form is based on
Plant-species data, which would ordinarily lie
dormant within its body, centered around the
crystal in its chest, but Aegiochusmon: Green
has affixed the Plant data around its arms and
upper body. Due to its Plant-type base, its body
is dramatically lighter than other forms.
Aegiochusmon: Green is capable of firing sturdy
thorns from the busters equipped to both arms. It
uses these for offense, defense and tricky
maneuvers that utilize them like grapples on
various surfaces. This form is best known for its
agile movements that utilize its equipment and
airy frame. Aegiochusmon: Green's special moves
are Bramble Bite, which summons demonic thorns
that bite into the enemy, and Plant Zone Cradle,
which unleashes countless thorns from its body
to surround foes over a wide area, tearing them to
ribbons.
English.189:
Ceresmon Medium, Ceresmon's true form, resides
at the head of the island on Ceresmon's back.
Ceresmon Medium possesses almost no combat
ability and rarely appears before others. However,
on rare occasions, it apparently shows itself to those
it trusts without bringing along the giant bird.
Ceresmon Medium has a gentle personality and a
heart overflowing with compassion. It offers hungry
Digimon fruits from Karpos Hulē, and allows injured
Digimon to take shelter in the forest until they've
recovered. However, if any prove ungrateful for the
bounty of nature, bring harm to the trees or defile the
land for sport, Ceresmon Medium's nature shifts and
it becomes a truly frightful forest demon.
English.190:
Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead,
this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental
"Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon were
discovered. Ryudamon is covered in Japanese-style
armor that boasts high defense, yet its movements are
quite nimble, allowing it to jump in and fight at brazenly
close range. The more it fights, the more it cultivates
combat prowess. Ryudamon possesses gallantry, a
samurai spirit and a soul that renders it unafraid of
powerful enemy Digimon. The data hidden within
the deepest part of its DigiCore during the experiment
contains such fierce combat data as warlords and
dragons from Japanese mythology, and Ryudamon
is thought to possess the potential to grow into a
mighty Digimon. Its special move is Iai Blade, with
which it leaps up to the opponent to fire an iron
blade from its mouth at point-blank range.
English.191:
A Beast Dragon Digimon with sturdy Japanese-style
armor covering its whole body. Ginryumon is lighter
than it appears, drifting gracefully through the air and
fighting while parrying enemy attacks with its smooth
and extremely tough armor. It has the courage to fend
off enemy attacks with its own body, and the insight to
accurately perceive said attacks right before they land.
Ginryumon specializes in attacks with outstanding
penetrative ability, and is unflinching in the face of any
enemy Digimon. Because of the antiquated interface
on its forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the
Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon."
Ginryumon's special move is Metal Armor Blade,
which impales its foe with an iron lance launched
from its mouth.
English.192:
A Beast Dragon Digimon that soars freely through the
skies clad in armor of elegantly-shimmering scales.
Hisyaryumon's form is the result of the interface on
its forehead unlocking the data that lay dormant
within its DigiCore of dragons and generals—filled
with ferocious combatinstincts—from Japanese
myths. The orbs it clutches are the souls of its lost
companions. The orb in Hisyaryumon's right hand is
the soul of Kinryu, while the orb in its left hand is the
soul of Kakuryu. It's said that each orb contains the
data of a DigiCore hidden within it. Hisyaryumon's
special move is Legendary Dragon Blade, which
transforms it into a giant steel blade to slice the
enemy in half with a single stroke.
English.193:
An imaginary Digimon born from the daydream of a 
DigiCore. The interface on Ouryumon's forehead 
miraculously unlocked the creative power of its 
own DigiCore, causing it to Digivolve into this form. 
Perhaps because this DigiCore already contained 
such fierce combat data as warlords and dragons 
from Japanese mythology, the form it dreamed up 
was that of a dragon warrior clad in imposing 
Japanese-style armor, wielding a sword in each 
hand. The blade in Ouryumon's left hand is called 
Gairyu Sadaijin, while the one in its right is named 
Gairyu Udaijin. The blades extending from the 
wings on its back are called the Gaiba Daimeijin. 
Ouryumon's special moves are Eiseiryuojin, which 
unleashes an attack from the blades in both hands, 
and Golden Armor, with which it rages forward with 
the destructive force of a mighty river overflowing 
its banks.
English.194:
A large Digimon equipped with a veritable cache 
of firearms. Many Digimon refer to Gundramon 
as one of the "Three Musketeers," along with
MagnaKidmon and BeelStarmon, due to their 
highly-developed marksmanship. It's also a 
member of the Crack Team, and is suited to 
combat much like Machinedramon. Faster than
Machinedramon, though, Gundramon has all 
the mobility it needs to quickly get into firing 
position. The acrid smell of gunpowder has 
soaked into every bit of its fully-metallic body,
as is appropriate for such a bitter and hard-boiled 
Digimon. Gundramon's special moves are Der 
Blitz, which fires at an opponent's vitals with
the twin six-shooters in its hands, and Gewalt 
Schwärmer, which fires off a volley in all directions.
English.195:
Referred to as "Beelzemon Lady" due to its 
appearance, this Digimon brandishes twin pistols 
with flair. These beloved Rizoma de Loto guns are
like little sisters to the Berenjena, Beelzemon's 
signature pistols. BeelStarmon opens up to anyone
without hesitation—particularly gunslinger Digimon, 
with friends like MagnaKidmon even using the 
nickname "Beelko." Still, it's on bad terms with the 
solitary Beelzemon, keeping its distance despite 
recognizing the Evil King Digimon's abilities.
BeelStarmon is clad in a jet-black leather suit, 
and wears a scarf that can transform into weapons, 
armor, wings or anything else the situation warrants. 
Its special move is Fly Bullet, which homes in on 
the enemy's vitals with shots from its Rizoma de
Loto. It also uses Hurricane Screw Shot to spray
bullets from the guns hidden in the heels of its
boots with a whirlwind kick.
English.196:
A British punk Digimon born when a notorious 
British hacker injected all of his knowledge into 
a computer virus, thereby causing it to mutate.
Pukumon may be small, but its rebellious 
personality is second to none in the Digital 
World. It always picks fights, no matter how 
much stronger or weaker its potential opponent 
may be. Although Pukumon is the type to settle 
disputes with a slugfest, its special move Needle
Squall acts as a trump card by launching all the 
super-hard thorns on its Chrondigizoid head 
at once.
English.197:
A Giant Bird Digimon clad in golden armor. The 
armor covers Eaglemon's entire body, and is 
made of Chrondigizoid, allowing it to repel any 
attack. Although its origins are unclear, some 
speculate that Eaglemon is the Digivolution of 
Parrotmon, an Ultimate-level Digimon. It's said 
that Eaglemon's duty is to eliminate any alien 
elements that invade the Digital World. It uses its 
special move Kaiser Phoenix to ram the enemy
with its full-metal body, or Mystic Break to shoot
a white ray that reduces the enemy to ash.
English.198:
Resembling a steam-powered locomotive, this 
Machine Digimon lives to stay in motion. Locomon's
purpose is to carry data across the Digital World's 
Net. In the Digital World, where a large quantity of 
data must be moved around, transporting said data 
as quickly as possible is the ultimate reason that
Vehicle-species Digimon like Locomon exist. There 
are times, though, when the older-model Locomon 
has run off the rails in its pursuit of ever-greater 
speeds. And although its movement is confined to 
the tracks, there are occasions when it's generated 
rifts in space-time by continuously running in loops.
Locomon can also use its special move Wheel Grinder
to spin and then throw its spiked wheels.
English.199:
A Dark Beast Digimon in the form of a "Spider 
Queen" that appears in Greek mythology. As a 
Digimon of both impressive intelligence and cunning,
this queen rules over all Dokugumon. Arukenimon 
specializes in transforming into a humanoid form,
letting it approach potential prey while its guard is 
down. Short-tempered and ferocious, its nature 
elicits a sense of trepidation from a great many 
other Digimon. Arukenimon's special move is 
Spider Thread, which mangles enemies with
sharp wires.
English.208:
Dracomon is a Dragon Digimon of an old bloodline
said to trace back to the progenitor of all Dramon-
species Digimon. It possesses physical capabilities
difficult to even imagine given its small size, with
its speed and power ranking among the very best
of all Rookie Digimon. Though extremely fierce by
nature, it also has a softer side it only shows to
those it deems worthy of its trust. Despite having
wings, they're not fully developed, so Dracomon is
unable to fly. One of its other defining characteristics
is its drive to collect "shiny things,"and it has an
odd attachment to gems and certain types of metal.
If it's particularly fond of some shiny object, it
will eat it. Its special move is Baby Breath, which
it uses to breathe out a blast of hot air.
English.209:
Coredramon with green bodies are said to have 
Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Green 
Malachite, a precious gem mined from forest
regions thickly wooded with trees over 100 years
old. Coredramon (Green) isn't skilled at flying,
but has highly-developed leg muscles, and is
capable of running at speeds seemingly impossible 
for a creature of its size. Its special move is Green 
Flare Breath, with which it breathes out scorching 
green flames. Green Flare Breath penetrates deep
beneath surface texture data to damage the enemy's
DigiCore directly.
English.210:
Wingdramon is a Sky Dragon Digimon that uses its 
large, highly-developed wings to fly freely through 
the air. Since its wing scales have the ability to 
nullify gravity, it doesn't even need to flap its wings
to stay aloft. As a result, it hardly ever bothers to
land, spending most of its life in the air. It's believed
to be capable of flying at speeds exceeding Mach 20,
meaning very few Digimon could likely survive an
aerial battle with Wingdramon. Wingdramon's special
move is Blaze Sonic Breath, with which it breathes
out a blast of scorching hot air faster than the speed
of sound.
English.211:
An Earth Dragon Digimon with huge arms on its back. 
These arms, which are said to have transformed from
wings, allow Groundramon to dig through the earth 
efficiently. It usually lies hidden in tunnels it's bored 
deep underground, and seldom shows its face on 
the surface. Groundramon likes living in veins of
rare Huanglong Ore, and in fact the scales covering 
its body are very likely composed of the same 
material. Its personality is quite brutal, and most 
who encounter it wind up losing their lives. 
Groundramon uses its special move Scrapless 
Claw to crush enemies with its back arms.
English.213:
A Dragon Man Digimon covered in Chrondigizoid 
scale armor. This form can only be achieved by 
those who complete the Trial of the Four Great 
Dragons—a test that Dragon Digimon alone can 
undertake. Slayerdramon carries the telescoping 
greatsword Fragarach, and has mastered 
Ryuzanken, an ultimate sword style of its own 
making with three forms. There's the first form, 
Tenryu Slash, with which it spins its body to 
accelerate the blade, driving it downward to 
bisect its foe from top to bottom. The second 
form is Shoryu Slash, which tempers a dragon 
wave with Slayerdramon's blade, unleashing it in 
an upward motion to mow down the enemy with 
sword pressure alone. The third form is Koryu 
Slash, which coils the Fragarach around the
opponent after stepping in close, shaving away 
at its entire body with the wrapped blade.
English.214:
A massive Machine Dragon Digimon said to exist to 
destroy all things on the face of the earth. 
Whenever it Digivolves, Breakdramon successfully 
incorporates construction equipment design data 
into itself through hacking, obtaining power and 
abilities outclassing other Machine Digimon. 
However, its outstanding mechanical abilities come 
at the cost of reducing its organic parts to a 
practically negligible amount, robbing it of intent 
and emotion. As such, Breakdramon isn't afraid of 
damaging its own body, and is feared as the ultimate 
dragon of destruction that continues to wreck havoc 
until it crumbles to dust. Breakdramon's 
Destroyed Rush spins its left and right shovel arms 
at high speeds to rend the earth. Its Infinity Bowling 
activates all of the drills on its body, unleashing them 
in a volley capable of smashing even mountains.
Wherever Breakdramon goes, it leaves nothing in its 
devastating wake.
English.215:
A Holy Knight Digimon and member of the Royal 
Knights, the holy defenders of the Digital World. 
Examon has an absurdly high data mass, so it could
never be rendered on traditional digital devices. Its 
discovery only became possible when the latest
digital devices finally proved powerful enough to 
render it. It has massive, sentient wings referred to
as "Caledfwlch," along with a giant lance called 
"Ambrose." Examon's special move Pendragon's 
Glory unleashes a powerful laser beam from Ambrose.
Examon can also use Dragonic Impact to plunge
down from the exosphere to slam into foes while
its body is still hot from the friction of reentry into
the atmosphere.
English.217:
DarkSuperStarmon is a Digimon steeped in 
darkness born from observational data of black 
holes. It apparently has a past so grim that it's 
given up all its hopes and dreams, donning 
sunglasses so that no light can reach it. Its 
special move is Dark Explosion, which involves 
attacking with the shards of a supernova.
English.218:
Coredramon with blue bodies are said to have
Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Blue
Diamante, a precious gem that can only be mined
from mountainous regions with the highest of
peaks. Coredramon (Blue) has developed strong
wings to survive amid the steep slopes, and is
capable of flying at great speed. Its special move
is Blue Flare Breath, with which it breathes out
scorching blue flames. Blue Flare Breath breaks
down a foe's surface texture data, leaving the
DigiCore of a Digimon hit by this move exposed
and open to attack.
English.219:
A Reptile Digimon that aims to become the greatest
swordsman of the Digimon world. Kotemon is a hard
worker that silently endeavors to train in unseen areas.
It never removes its face protector, so its bare face
is a total mystery. Although Kotemon is cowardly
and prone to crying, it cares for its friends deeply
and has a strong sense of justice, and occasionally
even displays a stalwart side. With its special move
Hothead, it engulfs its bamboo sword in flames
before aiming for the head of its foe.
English.220:
An armored warrior Digimon that was once the data 
of a video game protagonist, but then Digivolved
after being infected by a computer virus. Numerous 
battles with other Digimon have rendered Musyamon's
appearance into that of a pathetic battlefield deserter, 
but that's only proof of its fearsome battle prowess 
and vitality. A savage warrior that's survived endless 
battles—that's Musyamon in a nutshell. The demon
sword Shiratori-maru in its right hand is engraved with 
a forbidden spell that absorbs the life force of those it 
cuts, and is said to only grow sharper with every 
thousand Digimon it slashes down. Musyamon also 
has a special move called Kirisute Gomen that it 
unleashes from its Shiratori-maru. One day, it will
settle things with Leomon, crossing its beloved blade 
with Leomon's.
English.222:
Originally a Virus-attribute type, Dobermon is a 
Hunter Digimon that changed into a Vaccine type 
as a result of mutation. Like Snimon, however, it 
remains quite vicious despite its Vaccine status, 
living only to hunt down Virus Digimon. Dobermon 
is beyond the control of the average Tamer. Its 
special move is Grau Lärm, with which it lets out a
howl that prevents its opponents from using their 
abilities.
English.223:
A Dark Beast Digimon known as the "Watchdog of Hell."
The claws on Cerberusmon's limbs are tough enough
to easily slice through low-purity Chrondigizoid. Its
body is also protected by a hard organic shell, and has
the ability to heal any damage instantly. The pieces of
armor on each shoulder possess wills of their own,
and are able to instantly sense attacks coming from
any direction and report this to Cerberusmon. It emits
incandescent flames with its special move Mad Dog Fire.
English.224:
Cerberusmon: Werewolf Mode is a mutant form
of Cerberusmon, the Digimon known as the
"Watchdog of Hell" that lives in the Dark Area. It
transformed into its current form to prevent the
spread of data created from human malice that
permeates the Internet in the form of both images
and text, because it fears this data will have an
adverse effect on the Digital World overall.
As a result of its transformation, its data was
rewritten so that its shell-covered body can now
walk on two legs and its arms can chew up any
tainted data it finds. With its special move Inferno
Divide, it can blast foes with firebombs at point-blank
range while it holds them in place in the jaws of the
massive heads on the ends of its arms. It also has
Mad Dog Fire, which unleashes a blast of scorching,
hellish flames that reduce all things to ash. The
destructive power of this attack is leaps and bounds
beyond the power of the unmutated Cerberusmon's
move of the same name.
English.225:
A Wizard Digimon resembling a mounted warrior. 
Zanbamon is a valiant general that leads the 
Musyamon Corps. Regardless of its high rank,
Zanbamon is always at the head of its force, and 
enjoys charging directly at its foes. Its lower half 
has fused with its horse in order to improve mobility
on the battlefield, allowing it to wield its sword
without fear of losing its balance even during 
the harshest of battles. One of Zanbamon's special 
moves, Vorpal Blade, unleashes a powerful blow with 
the massive sword in its right hand, Ryuzan-maru. 
The force of this strike is so intense that it slashes 
through the opponent's armor no matter how it tries 
to defend itself. Zanbamon's other special move is 
Mystic Flame, an attack performed with the magical
sword in its left hand. Quickly swinging this thin-bladed
weapon produces a cross-shaped shockwave that
slices through the enemy.
English.226:
An Undead Digimon wrapped head-to-toe in bandages 
like the mummies of ancient Egypt. Mummymon's 
ability to summon and control the lingering
spirits (residual data) of terminated Digimon has 
earned it the alias of the "Necromancer." Its taciturn 
and expressionless nature makes it hard to read, but 
any who attack it will face an exhaustive onslaught 
from the weapon it brandishes. If cornered, this 
dangerous creature will start firing off its beloved 
gun "Obelisk" willy-nilly. Mummymon uses its
signature move Snake Bandage to wrap the bandages 
of its arms around the enemy and constrict them like 
a snake.
English.227:
A Mega Wizard Digimon with a sinister golden sheen. 
Said to have Digivolved from a Mummy-species 
Digimon, Pharaohmon ruled over many areas of
the Ancient Digital World with absolute authority. 
It controlled many Digimon during the genesis of
the Digital World, and the fact that Pharaohmon was 
able to build the mysterious ancient ruins scattered
around the Digital World in a few days is proof of 
that dominion. It uses its special move Necromist 
to steal the will of hostile Digimon, then releases 
a fear gas that gradually dries out their flesh. Those 
who succumb to this attack face one of two fates: a 
full invitation to the world of the dead, or servitude 
under Pharaohmon as an undead creature.
English.228:
A Composite Digimon fused from three Digimon. Each 
existed as a separate Digimon, but a computer ran 
amok after getting hit by a powerful electromagnetic 
storm, bugging out and fusing them together into
Deltamon. A Digimon with three heads and two tails, 
it specializes in three-stage attacks utilizing these
physical features, making it capable of taking on 
three Digimon at once. Still, each part of it was once 
a fiendish Digimon, so while they share a mindset 
for destruction, they have no spirit of cooperation, 
and are usually on bad terms. Deltamon uses its 
special move Triple Forces to unleash energy from 
all three mouths in a single blast.
English.229:
Kimeramon is a Composite Digimon. Every part of its 
body, including its hands, legs, torso and tail, was 
made by combining various parts from other
Digimon. As for the reason behind its creation, that 
remains shrouded in mystery. Though Kimeramon is 
similar to Machinedramon in that it was constructed 
from various parts of other Digimon, the nature of 
the relationship between the two has yet to be 
discovered. Perhaps Kimeramon was a prototype 
for Machinedramon, except that it used organic parts
instead of metal ones. Or perhaps Kimeramon was 
created specifically as a countermeasure against
Machinedramon. What is clear, however, is 
Kimeramon's frightful instinct for combat, along 
with its immense destructive power. It can fire a 
deadly heat ray, Heat Viper, from its four arms. 
This is a horrifying technique that cruelly tears 
apart anything hit by the beam with all the force 
of Kimeramon's ire.
English.230:
Millenniummon is the ultimate Composite Digimon, 
formed when Machinedramon and its overwhelming
strength fused with Kimeramon and its data from 
various powerful Digimon. It's said to be unbeatable, 
but if only the reason for the fusion of this Digimon 
could be determined, it might serve as a clue 
regarding how to defeat it. Its special move, Time
Unlimited, compresses time to create a pocket 
dimension in which it traps its foes for all eternity.
English.231:
A Digimon that resembles a "baku," a being in
Japanese folklore that eats dreams. Believed to
have been born from a medical computer that
monitors brainwaves, Tapirmon seems to feed on
human REM sleep data. In the latest round of
research, it was also found to possess the ability
to erase nightmares and computer viruses. Since
it can also return those nightmares and viruses to
a benign state, it's believed to be a Holy Digimon.
The Holy Ring it wears on one of its forelegs seems
likely related to both its special abilities and Holy
nature. Tapirmon's special move is Nightmare
Syndrome, which releases all of the nightmares it
absorbed at once to terrify its adversaries. This is
the same special move as that of the Perfect
Digimon, Digitamamon, but how the two might be
related remains a mystery.
English.232:
A Deity Digimon that looks like a mix between a bird 
and a fish. Cheerful by nature, Sirenmon is always 
seen singing happily in the air or sea. Its beautiful 
voice has a miraculous range of eight octaves, from
ultra-low to ultra-high pitches. Sirenmon's song can 
bring peace to even the most devastated battlefields. 
They say a resplendent Digivolution awaits it in the 
future because of all the good deeds it's performed 
by healing those who listen to it. Sirenmon sings 
Symphony No. 1 in a high soprano that seeps into 
the listener's heart, paralyzing their will and leaving 
them at the Digimon's mercy. It sings the solemn
Symphony No. 2 in a low bass that transforms into 
a heavy, low-frequency vibration, crushing the
enemy from the insides of their ear canals and 
leaving them unable to even stand. Symphony No. 3 
turns its voice into note-shaped bullets that it then 
fires at the enemy. These shots have a mysterious 
property, ricocheting on impact to always hit other 
foes as well. Each of these techniques increase in 
power for every creature that sings along with 
Sirenmon, turning even the weak into a great 
strength.
English.233:
An Evil King Digimon said to be the final form of 
Myotismon. Unlike VenomMyotismon—who pursued 
power in excess, becoming a bestial creature lacking 
intelligence—MaloMyotismon has retained its 
intellect, successfully surpassing VenomMyotismon 
in every aspect. With an atrocious and coldhearted
personality, it will use any means at its disposal to 
satisfy its desires. The organic cannons on its 
shoulders are parasites known as "Sodom" and
"Gomorrah." MaloMyotismon uses its special move 
Pandemonium Flame to launch super-high 
temperature beams from Sodom and Gomorrah.
English.234:
A Beast Digimon resembling a small bear, wearing
its trademark backwards cap. Although timid at
times, Bearmon gets along well with other Digimon,
and even possesses uncommon pluck and stamina.
Once a battle starts, it continues to fight no matter
how many hits it takes, making for a reliable ally.
The ability for melee fighting it possesses is so
strong that it needs to wrap its fists with leather
belts so it won't injure itself with the destructive
power of its punches. With its special move Bear
Fist, Bearmon leaps at its opponent's chest to
drive home a full-force blow.
English.235:
Grizzlymon is a Beast Digimon that might seem
ferocious thanks to its large frame, not to mention
its deadly claws and fangs, but it has the honest
and straightforward spirit of a true martial artist.
It has the combat sense to match, too, relying not
only on attacks but moving with a speed that belies
its great bulk to avoid and deflect enemy strikes as
well. Grizzlymon never starts a fight, but when
angered it will draw itself up onto its hind legs
and lash out with its heavyweight bear claws,
"Kumazume." Grizzlymon's strength is such that
just with this one strike it can critically injure most
Digimon. Apparently, WaruMonzaemon wears its
Bear Claw in imitation of this attack. Grizzlymon's
greatest special move, Maul Attack, turns the
force of an enemy's move against it, striking
where it's vulnerable to defeat it in a single blow.
English.237:
Though Astamon is an Ultimate-level Digimon, its 
power exceeds that of a Mega Digimon. As a noble 
of the Dark Area, it leads a force of demonic 
Digimon. Astamon is cruel to its enemies but also 
kind to its allies, and many demonic Digimon are 
drawn to its service because of its personal
charisma. The bullets Astamon fires from its 
beloved machine gun, "Oro Salmón," have a will 
of their own, and will pursue their targets literally 
to the farthest corners of hell. Astamon's special 
move, Mad Dog Fire, fires all the bullets in its Oro 
Salmón in a deadly barrage.
English.239:
A giant Undead Digimon produced when some of 
the fossil data for the largest land mammal was 
counterfeited and recreated. Lacking intelligence 
and emotions, SkullBaluchimon moves entirely by 
reflex according to the nerve data running through 
its body. As a result, it continues to attack without 
reason or mercy until it can no longer move. The 
cold, black vapor endlessly overflowing from
SkullBaluchimon's DigiCore is said to fill any 
Digimon with the fear of death—perhaps a curse 
wrought from its forced reanimation from a
corpse's data. Its special move is Grave Bone, 
trampling the enemy beneath its giant feet and 
burying it within the earth.
English.240:
A Mollusk Digimon discovered in a virus that a 
malicious hacker used when trying to crash a rival's
computer. Octomon is an obsessive collector,
sporting claws at the ends of its tentacles that it 
obtained from Devidramon's data, and covering
itself in Digi-Treasure that it scavenged from the 
depths of the Net Ocean. Many Fujitsumon, which 
are a small type of shellfish Digimon, have attached
themselves to the pot that Octomon wears on its
head. These Fujitsumon have highly-developed
senses, and it's believed that they are part of a
symbiotic relationship with Octomon, warning it
when they sense danger. Octomon's special move,
Spurting Ink, fires out a blast of highly-poisonous
ink.
English.241:
A super-small Machine Digimon with red eyes that 
act as photosensors. Choromon's constant restless
movements make it seem very cute, but they're
just because of its simple programming making it
react to bright light. In dark places, it can't move at
all. For reasons unknown, it discharges electricity
from the tip of its tail when it's in a good mood. It
uses its move Jamming Powder to emit metal
particles and temporarily confuse its enemy's AI. It
then takes advantage of this temporary confusion
to flee.
English.242:
A small, In-Training Digimon wearing a metal helmet.
The two horns on the helmet contain antennae that 
can transmit all sorts of radio waves or sounds. 
Kapurimon has batlike traits, emitting ultrasonic 
waves from its mouth and recognizing objects ahead
of it from the rebounding waves, instead of relying
on its weak eyesight. This allows it to remain active 
no matter what time of day or night it is. Kapurimon 
uses its special move Howling Hertz to make its two 
horns resonate. Anyone hit by this attack has their 
hearing paralyzed, even large Digimon.
English.301:
Megadramon is a Black Dragon Digimon said to 
possess the greatest and most terrible power of 
all the Ultimate-level Dragon Android Digimon. It 
was artificially modified by an unknown individual 
who programmed it to destroy everything. It's 
practically the living embodiment of a computer 
virus. Capable of breaching a high-security 
computer network with ease, Megadramon then 
effortlessly mods or destroys the host computer. 
Its special move Eradication Attack fires countless 
organic missiles from its arms.
English.302:
An Android Digimon with more than half of its body
mechanized. The MetalGreymon of File Island was
able to dramatically prolong its vital functioning
through self-modification, but its biological parts
couldn't withstand the strain and turned blue. By
contrast, this Ultimate-level MetalGreymon is a
successful Digivolution from a Greymon, and is an 
extremely powerful Android Digimon. MetalGreymon's
attack power is said to be as powerful as a nuclear
warhead, capable of completely obliterating lower-
level Digimon. Its special move Giga Destroyer is an
attack that fires bionic missiles from a hatch that
opens in its chest.
English.303:
The prototypical Insectoid Digimon, Tentomon has 
a hard carapace but a low level of aggression.
Tentomon has one claw on each of its forelegs, and
four claws on its middle and hind legs. Its middle
legs in particular are highly dexterous, similar to
human hands. Though other Insectoid Digimon of
Tentomon's Digivolution level are consumed by a
strong fighting spirit, Tentomon retains a love and
appreciation for nature at this stage. Exhibiting a
fondness for relaxation, Tentomon stops to smell
flowers and nap in the shade of trees. Even so, it
does have the special move Super Shocker, which
involves using its wings to shoot out amplified
bolts of static electricity.
English.304:
Even for a newly-discovered Digimon, Kabuterimon
is highly unusual. Though it's unclear how it came
to be an Insectoid type, it's understood to have
the power of an ant and the defense system of a
beetle. As you would expect from an insect, it only
thinks about survival, and has no other intelligence
whatsoever. Hostile toward Virus Digimon, Kabuterimon
attacks on sight without mercy. Its head is made
of metal, granting it impregnable defense. Its special
move is Electro Shocker.
English.305:
A Digivolution of Kabuterimon discovered in a 
tropical area of the Net. Approximately 1.5 times 
the size of Kabuterimon, MegaKabuterimon is quite 
large for an Insectoid Digimon. It has dramatically 
increased the power of its horn, which is the species'
primary weapon, as well as grown muscles at the
bases of its forelimbs, improving its hand-to-hand
combat ability. MegaKabuterimon is renowned for its 
chivalrous nature, and is well-known for protecting 
weaker creatures. Its special move is Horn Buster, 
by which MegaKabuterimon stabs opponents with 
its giant horn.
English.306:
The ultimate Insectoid Digimon, HerculesKabuterimon 
Digivolved by combining data from both the
Kabuterimon and the Kuwagamon species. Possessing
a giant horn as well as huge pincers,
HerculesKabuterimon is said to perfectly compensate
for the weaknesses of these two species with opposing
dispositions that it Digivolved from. Its body glitters
gold, and having both regained and improved upon
the ability to fly it lost as MegaKabuterimon,
HerculesKabuterimon zooms around the Digital World
at supersonic speeds. There are few who can rival
HerculesKabuterimon in this Mega form. 
HerculesKabuterimon uses its special move Giga 
Blaster, an upgraded version of Electro Shocker.
Nothing can survive a direct hit from this attack.
English.307:
A Baby Bird Digimon with arm-like wings. Biyomon
can use these to dexterously grip objects, though
this limits its ability to fly. It spends most of its
time on the ground, but can escape into the air
when danger draws near. Since it's similar in flying
ability to Patamon, Biyomon sees Patamon as a
rival. Biyomon's dream is to one day Digivolve into
Birdramon and fly freely through the sky. Its
nightmare is becoming Kokatorimon, who can't
fly at all. Possessed of an inquisitive mind, it likes
to peck at the sprout growing from Tanemon's
head. Biyomon's special move is Spiral Twister, an
attack of spectral flames.
English.308:
A Giant Bird Digimon wreathed in blazing flames. 
Like Meramon, whose body is also shrouded in 
crimson flames, Birdramon is a Digimon formed 
from the Internet's defensive Firewall. Birdramon 
flies through the sky using its massive wings. 
Despite not having a combative nature, Birdramon 
nevertheless launches frenzied counterattacks in 
the face of enemy assaults. Birdramon's special 
move is Meteor Wing, flapping its wings to send 
feathers shooting down like meteors.
English.309:
A Bird Man Digimon with large talons and wings that 
allow it to fly freely through the sky. Garudamon 
values order and justice above all, and is also known 
as the nature-loving Guardian of Wind and Land.
Even among Bird Digimon, Garudamon is worshiped 
as a Digimon that only a select, highly-intelligent, 
combat-adept few can Digivolve into. Whenever the 
Digital World is in chaos, Garudamon is said to 
appear, resolving the source of the disorder and 
guiding things back to a more peaceful course. 
Garudamon is also close friends with the hero
Leomon, who possesses the same spirit. 
Garudamon's special move is Shadow Wing, with 
which it sends forth a vacuum blade at incredible
speed to slice opponents to shreds.
English.310:
A Holy Digimon with four gleaming golden wings. 
The leader of all Bird Digimon, Phoenixmon is said 
to rule over all Sacred Digimon as well. Just as 
Magnadramon is the ultimate Beast Digimon, 
Phoenixmon is the ultimate Bird Digimon. Since 
it has not one but two Holy Rings, which draw out
holy power and serve to identify Holy Digimon, 
Phoenixmon evidently possesses immeasurable 
power. Phoenixmon's special move is Starlight 
Explosion, with which it flaps its four godly wings 
to rain down golden particles of light. Anything hit 
by this attack is said to be cleansed of all evil.
English.311:
A previously unknown Digimon that suddenly 
appeared in the Digital World. The self-proclaimed 
"King of Digimon," Etemon's combat strength is
unimaginable. Rumors say it manipulates the 
mysterious Monzaemon from behind the scenes. 
Clad in a reinforced monkey suit that withstands any 
and all attacks, Etemon bounds all over the world 
for unending battles. It uses its special move 
Love Serenade to break the enemy's heart and 
sap their fighting spirit.
English.312:
There once was a supremely strong Digimon referred 
to as the "King of Digimon." It sought out strong
opponents, embarking on a journey of brutal 
encounters. Although it obtained valuable combat 
data, the constant battles left it with severe physical 
damage. It then researched its own weaknesses 
from the data it gained in battle, completely coated
the surface of its body with Chrondigizoid metal—a 
substance used by metal Digimon—and was able 
to reinvent itself as the ultimate battle machine, 
MetalEtemon. Despite having maximized its combat 
abilities, though, it still uses a petty special move, 
Banana Slip, to trip up its opponent. An invincible 
fighter that uses both high-level combat techniques 
and dirty tricks has been born.
English.313:
A nasty Digimon shaped like a glittering piece of
golden poop. Sukamon was born from the accumulation
and mutation of data scraps thrown away in the trash
can of a computer desktop. It loves dark places, and
being a pile of scrap data, it's just as disliked by other
Digimon as Numemon. Sukamon's intelligence and
attack power are both nonexistent. Its small rodent
partner Chuumon can't fight, but is as crafty as they
come, and always entices Sukamon into doing
wicked deeds.
English.314:
A Carnivorous Vegetation Digimon with long vines
and a gaping maw. This fiendish brute emits a sweet
smell from its mouth to lure in smaller Digimon,
then ensnares them with its long, tentacle-like vines.
Still, Vegiemon lacks any offensive power, making it no
match for large-scale Digimon. When it grows, it will 
flower and bear fruit.
English.315:
A Seraph Digimon with ten golden wings and clad 
in glittering silver holy armor. Seraphimon is the
greatest of all Angel Digimon, reigning over all of 
its brethren. Its true face and identity are hidden
from public view behind a mask. Even so, it's the 
closest being to those embodiments of good known
as "gods." It's said that Seraphimon will descend for
a final battle against wicked beings, purifying them all.
The Digimon Creepymon, which fell to the Dark Area
and became an Evil King Digimon, is said to have
originally been a Seraphimon. Seraphimon's special
moves are Strike of the Seven Stars, which fires seven
orbs of high-temperature light at the opponent, and
Testament, an ultimate technique that induces a
big bang in exchange for its life.
English.316:
A Slime Digimon covered entirely in a tough material
called Mithril Hair. Dodomon exhibits an aggressive 
nature right from birth, and even though its fangs
haven't grown in yet, it likes to threaten foes by 
opening wide and pretending to bite them. Because 
of this behavior, these Digimon are often taken out 
by others, making Dodomon quite rare. When an 
enemy approaches, Dodomon attacks by shooting 
Little Iron Beads from its mouth.
English.317:
A newborn Digital Monster. Dark peach fuzz covers 
the surface of Botamon's slimy body. This new 
addition to the Digital World can't fight, but it can 
spout Acid Bubbles from its mouth in an attempt
to threaten foes.
English.320:
This Digimon baby uses its translucent body to float
along the Net Ocean like a jellyfish. Possessing the 
most primitive structural makeup of any Digimon
discovered to date, it garners attention from Digital 
World anthropologists and Digimon fanatics alike. 
They hail it as a "missing link," potentially capable of
unlocking the mystery behind Digimon generation. 
To protect itself from foes, Poyomon shoots 
Acid Bubbles from its mouth.
English.321:
A Digimon that fuses the data of small pet animals 
such as cats and dogs. Wanyamon is unexpectedly 
swift, so caution is warranted to prevent its escape. 
Even so, it gets quite attached if you fawn over it like
a pet. Its special move is Smile Fang, going suddenly 
from an innocent-looking pose to a surprise chomp 
attack.
English.322:
A small Digimon whose body has grown a size bigger,
its peach fuzz having fallen off. Koromon can move
around vigorously, but combat is still beyond its
capabilities. It blows Bubbles from its mouth to 
intimidate foes.
English.325:
A small Digimon with four limbs growing out of the
bottom of its body (head?). These limbs, which are
highly unusual on an In-Training Digimon, give 
Tokomon a unique and extremely cute look. 
However, that cuteness can be deceptive, and 
anyone who reaches out to pet Tokomon may be
in for a surprise as it quickly opens its mouth and 
bites down with its rows of sharp teeth. Tokomon 
has an innocent personality, though, and doesn't 
mean any real harm.
English.326:
A Dinosaur Digimon with skin hardened into a
protective carapace around its skull. Aggressive
by nature, Greymon uses its sharp claws and
colossal horns as lethal weapons. Taming it earns
you an intelligent ally of unmatched strength. Its
special move is Mega Flame, with which it shoots
searing flames from its mouth, incinerating all.
English.327:
The ultimate Android Digimon with 
more than half of its body mechanized. 
MetalGreymon (Virus) has braved 
countless battles, only surviving 
due to the mechanization of its body. 
To successfully Digivolve into 
MetalGreymon (Virus), a Greymon must 
face several mighty foes and defeat them 
in battle. Its attack power is said to 
be as powerful as a nuclear warhead. 
MetalGreymon (Virus) fires bionic 
missiles from a hatch that opens in its chest.
English.328:
A mysterious Digimon that appeared when negative 
thoughts were amassed by the power of darkness. 
No one knows Apocalymon's true nature, and it 
can't even be analyzed to see if it truly is a Digimon. 
The reason for its appearance is uncertain, but it 
seems to desire the purging of the chaotic Digital 
World back into nothingness. One theory states 
that its coming was foretold in ancient prophecy. 
Its special move Darkness-Zone unleashes an 
endlessly-expanding darkness that returns all to 
the void. Those caught in this darkness lose all 
sense of direction, disappearing without a trace.
English.338:
One of the Ten Legendary Warriors that saved the 
Ancient Digital World, possessing the attribute of 
Steel. A Mega that existed in the far-distant past, 
AncientWisemon is the wisest being in the Digital 
World. Due to the Akashic Records that chronicle
the superior wisdom of ancient times, there's 
nothing outside of AncientWisemon's comprehension.
Not only does this sage possess knowledge from
time immemorial, but it also discerns events of the
distant future. The mirror that comprises its body is
rumored to be linked to the netherworld.
AncientWisemon's abilities have been subsequently
passed down to Mutant Digimon. Its special moves
are Laplace's Demon, which imprisons opponents
for all eternity in a netherworld located by using its
vast wisdom, and Elder Sign, by which it summons a
powerful demon from the netherworld.
English.341:
A Machine Digimon that protects computer network
firewalls. Guardromon used to fight off anyone
attempting to breach a firewall alongside
"Net Keeper" Giromon, until malicious hackers
infected it with a virus to make use of its impregnable
defensive abilities. These hackers now use
Guardromon to protect themselves from a certain
Vaccine justice group. Since Guardromon's basic
programming only involves commands to defend,
it has no problem repelling invaders regardless of
its new role. It uses its special move Destruction
Grenade to pursue invaders to the ends of the
earth and destroy them.
English.342:
Andromon is an Android Digimon with a humanoid 
shape. It's powerful enough to take out any Digimon 
of less than Ultimate level with a single blow.
Developed as a prototype for Android Digimon, 
Andromon was created as a machine-based model 
at the same time Boltmon was made to be an organic
one. The same techniques were then appropriated 
for use in other Digimon, including MetalGreymon 
and Megadramon. Since Andromon is a prototype, 
it lacks emotions and has no will of its own, acting 
only in accordance with its programming. It uses its 
special move Spiral Sword to fire an energy blade 
from its arm.
English.343:
A Sea Beast Digimon that can move on land and
that's covered in temperature-regulating fur. This
short, white fur grows longer and turns brown as
Gomamon ages. A busybody and a troublemaker,
Gomamon loves to get involved in every situation.
The streak of red fur running from its head down
its back moves in accordance with its mood, bristling
when Gomamon is angry. Its claws are sharp
enough to cut through solid ice with ease, and
anyone who underestimates Gomamon is in for a
rude awakening. Its special move is Marching Fishes,
with which Gomamon commands a loyal squad of
small fish to attack.
English.344:
A Sea Beast Digimon discovered in a computer at
an arctic research facility. Ikkakumon's thick pelt
and sturdy body are made to withstand polar
temperatures. The sharp horn growing from its
head is made of Mithril, a rare metal, and the skin
beneath its pelt is just as hard. Ikkakumon's clawed
limbs are capable of emitting blistering heat at will.
As a result, Ikkakumon can always maintain a firm
foothold when walking on ice, even if unable to
move quickly. In combat, Ikkakumon will threaten
opponents with a bold roar, much like a lion's.
Its special move is Harpoon Torpedo, with which it
fires the horn on its head at the enemy, as the horn
can be regrown.
English.345:
A powerful Sea Beast Digimon Digivolved from
Ikkakumon that learned to walk on two legs.
Zudomon protects its tempered muscles with armor
fashioned from the skins and shells of defeated foes.
Similarly, Zudomon carved its own horn into a saw
blade after losing the ability to regrow it. But the
most powerful weapon in Zudomon's arsenal is its
Thor's Hammer, made from Chrondigizoid dug up
from the ancient ice. Zudomon's special move is
Vulcan's Hammer, with which it blasts opponents
with the powerful shockwave and flying sparks that
result from swinging Thor's Hammer down.
English.346:
A Mega Beast Man Digimon that rules over the 
chilly arctic regions of everlasting permafrost. 
Vikemon's fur resembles ice crystals, and is said 
to be as hard as Chrondigizoid. The morning 
star Mjölnir that Vikemon carries on its back can 
shatter mountains in a single blow, distorting the 
atmosphere itself. It leads an army of Ikkakumon 
and Zudomon, and fights with all the ferocity of a 
demon in battle, although it's also thoughtful and
compassionate to its subordinates. Vikemon uses 
its special move Arctic Blizzard to freeze its foes 
by lowering the temperature of the surrounding 
atmosphere to absolute zero, then shattering 
them with Mjölnir.
English.347:
An Aquatic Digimon with a serpentine body. 
When attacked, Seadramon will wrap its long body 
around the enemy and squeeze them until they 
suffocate. Fundamentally lacking any kind of 
intelligence, Seadramon swims through the Net 
Ocean wherever its instincts take it. Its special 
move is Ice Blast, with which it breathes out from 
its mouth at absolute zero, instantly freezing the 
water and blasting it at its opponent.
English.348:
A Vegetation Digimon with a tropical flower growing
on its head. Though it Digivolved from Tanemon
in a reptilian fashion, it's a rare type of Digimon
classified as a Vegetation Digimon based on its
appearance and characteristics. During the day,
Palmon opens its flower and leaf-like appendages
to enable photosynthesis. Its root-like feet are
usually buried in the ground absorbing nutrients,
but it can also use them to walk. The flower on
Palmon's head gives off a sweet scent when it's
happy or enjoying itself and a foul stench when
it's angry or feels threatened. The latter is so bad
it can send even larger Digimon running. Palmon's
special move is Poison Ivy, with which it entangles
its foe in highly poisonous vines. Anything hit by
this attack is paralyzed.
English.349:
A Vegetation Digimon resembling a giant cactus. 
Its ability to store nutrient data inside its body 
allows it to survive for extended periods even in 
barren desert regions. As is obvious from its 
facial expression, it's usually impossible to tell 
what Togemon is thinking, since it spends most 
days staring blankly into space. But if provoked 
enough, its demeanor becomes violent and 
unhinged. Togemon's special move is Needle
Spray, with which it hardens the needles on its 
fists and unleashes a flurry of punches.
English.359:
A Pixie Digimon born from beautiful flower petals. 
At first glance, Lillymon looks like a small child, but 
it's in fact an Ultimate Digimon with immeasurable 
power. Possessed of a mercurial and tomboyish
personality, it's said to open its heart to human girls 
of the same disposition. Lillymon can also be a 
crybaby, and becomes inconsolable once it starts 
sobbing, making this one of the harder Digimon to 
tame. But Lillymon will also offer a helping hand 
to the small and the weak. Able to fly using the four
leaf-like wings on its back, a gentle breeze is said to 
follow in Lillymon's wake. Its special move is Flower 
Cannon, with which it extends both of its arms, turns
the flowers on its wrists into the mouth of a cannon
and fires an energy bomb.
English.361:
Salamon is a young, Sacred-species Digimon with
distinctive floppy ears. Since it's still a child, it isn't
able to make full use of its holy powers, and has
yet to realize its destiny. As a result, its nature is
fundamentally unstable, and it's capable of becoming
either good or evil. There will likely come a day,
however, when Salamon will awaken to its destiny
as one of the Virus Busters. After all, it was born a
sacred Digimon. Salamon is also an experimental
Digimon created by Digimon researchers, and since
it was modeled after a human pet, it looks a great
deal like a real animal. Its special move Puppy Howl
involves letting out a supersonic screech that can
paralyze foes.
English.363:
A Digimon that looks like an ancient dinosaur that 
existed in the prehistoric world. Tyrannomon mows
down everything with its two powerful arms and 
massive tail. It possesses intelligence and a docile
personality, however, and is easy to tame. This makes
Tyrannomon a hot commodity among beginning 
Tamers, many of whom raise theirs with care. One 
could say it represents what Digimon are all about. 
It uses its special move Fire Breath to exhale flames 
the same color as its deep crimson body.
English.364:
An Android Digimon that remodeled its body to 
obtain extensive power. Just like Megadramon was 
remodeled for anti-air use, MetalTyrannomon 
was remodeled into a Digimon for anti-ground 
interception. Any and all attacks rebound off of its
strengthened body, and it possesses a terrifying 
attack power, busting through even the sturdiest 
armor with its tough chin. It uses its special move 
Nuclear Laser to fire an energy beam from its left 
arm.
English.365:
A Mythical Dragon Digimon that gained Veemon's 
original power and Digivolved to Champion. 
ExVeemon is the pure breed of Veedramon, which 
is said to be a derivative species. Attacks with its 
developed arm and leg strength are capable of
shattering a mountain of boulders without a trace. 
It's feared for this destructive power, but in truth it
has a strong sense of justice, and doesn't use its 
might recklessly. ExVeemon's special move Vee 
Laser fires an energy beam from the X-shaped 
mark on its chest.
English.367:
An Insectoid Digimon with giant pincers on its head. 
Like Kabuterimon, Kuwagamon possesses combat 
abilities far surpassing those of its kin inhabiting 
File Island. While Kuwagamon enjoys the protection
of its strength and sturdy shell, it uses the power of 
its pincers to squeeze the life out of any foe it catches.
It has a completely hostile relationship with the
Vaccine-attribute Kabuterimon. It can use its
special move Scissor Claw to easily cut through
tough objects.
English.368:
A Digimon shaped like a hermit crab inhabiting the 
depths of the Net Ocean. Shellmon has a turtle-like
appearance when inside its shell, but its body is 
actually soft like a mollusk. Its body gets bigger and
bigger as it develops, and it switches dwellings each 
time until it's the size of a small mountain. Also, 
Shellmon has the custom of settling into anything it 
can push its whole body into. Its low intelligence and 
belligerent nature mean that anyone who encounters 
it needs to stay on guard. Its special move Hydro 
Blaster fires liquid at high pressure.
English.369:
An Armored Dragon Digimon with a rhinoceros-like 
horn growing from its snout. When fully grown, this 
horn measures half of Monochromon's body length.
The hard substance that covers its horns and half
its body is as hard as diamond. They say there's
nothing its horn can't pierce. Monochromon is known
to excel at both offense and defense. Although it's
herbivorous and comparatively docile, once it's
angered, it will unleash fearsome counterattacks
with its tank-like body. Its special move Volcanic Strike
is a powerful flame projectile.
English.370:
An Ice-Snow Digimon whose body is covered in 
snow and ice crystals. In spite of its chilly 
appearance, Frigimon actually has a warm and 
gentle personality. This Digimon calms the hearts 
of those who observe it through its sweet gestures 
and calm movements. Frigimon itself hates the idea 
of fighting, and is ill-suited to other Digimon who 
enjoy combat—Meramon in particular. It unleashes 
its special move Sub-Zero Ice Punch from its sizable 
frame.
English.371:
A hairy Rare Animal Digimon covered in a thick 
white coat. It lives in remote snowy regions, making
sightings quite rare. In spite of the various reports
of Mojyamon encounters, no evidence has 
confirmed its existence, and so for a long time this 
Digimon has been considered to be a mere fantasy. 
Mojyamon is a gentle creature that never shows 
any hostility, but even so, it treats its den and 
territory as sacred grounds, and doesn't forgive
any who invade its holy land. It hurls a massive 
icicle formed instantly from water in the atmosphere 
with its special move Icicle Rod.
English.372:
A half-human, half-beast Digimon resembling 
a centaur. Centarumon's body is protected by a 
sturdy substance emitted from inside its body, 
and its right arm is fused with its weapon. It blows 
highly concentrated gas from the ducts sticking 
out of its back to move around at near-sonic 
speeds. It excels in attack, defense and speed.
Pride means everything to Centarumon, and it 
hates being ordered or bound by anything with a 
passion. Its special move Hunting Cannon is fired
from the cannon fused to its right arm. This attack 
is almost impossible to evade, but it consumes 
massive amounts of energy, so Centarumon
avoids battles as much as it can.
English.373:
A Digimon that moves through the earth at high 
speeds with the giant drill on its nose. Drimogemon 
stays deep in the ground, so only a rare few ever 
meet it. It's docile and easily embarrassed, yet it 
enjoys a good prank, often taking Garurumon's
favorite bone it buried in the ground and hiding it 
someplace else. Its special move Drill Spin attacks 
foes with its giant drill.
English.374:
An Ultimate Digimon that has the appearance of a 
Digi-Egg and is the alpha and omega of all Digimon.
Digitamamon is the apex of Digivolution, and 
supposedly Digivolves not from a normal Digimon,
but only by fusing with data from another dimension. 
Its egg-shaped exoskeleton renders all attacks
useless. Its special move Nightmare Syndrome is a 
ball of darkness.
English.375:
An unidentified Digimon that invaded from an 
other-dimensional Digital World. Nanimon went by 
the nickname of "Oyaji" in the other dimension, and 
was kept as a digital pet. It loves alcohol and violence, 
but once it invaded this Digital World (the details of
which are still fuzzy), it Digivolved into an active 
creature. Inspired by the survival-of-the-fittest nature 
of the Digital World, it threw itself into battle. Its true 
power remains unknown. That being said, Nanimon
has made it through many battles and evolved into its
supreme form.
English.376:
An upgrade to Gekomon, with an antenna that looks 
like a feudal lord's topknot. ShogunGekomon was
supposedly first created in a karaoke machine's 
scoring system. It has two horns on its shoulders 
that play a melody, and it can sing several registers 
lower than Gekomon, giving off a lordly (?) air. Its 
special move Musical Fist uses its vocal chords and 
horns to create an ultra-low frequency wave that
corrupts the data of its foes. However, these 
ultra-low frequencies seem to actually improve the 
health of some opponents.
English.377:
A high-level Wizard Digimon from the Digital World
of another dimension. In its home Digital World of
Witchelny, it mastered the magics of fire and earth
(advanced programming languages) and aims to
become a great mage, but has first come to the
Digimon World for training. Wizardmon is a little
mischievous but also shy and always keeps its
face hidden. Its special move is Thunder Cloud,
which conjures up a storm cloud to launch a
powerful lightning attack.
English.378:
It seems like a typical Bird type at first glance, but 
this odd Digimon has lush vegetation sprouting from
its back. Much like Kiwimon, Deramon has plantlike 
qualities and can't fly. It's extremely prideful and
believes itself to be a noble being, but is secretly 
ashamed of not being able to soar the skies. Still, 
its Digivolution to Ultimate means it boasts considerable
battle power. The crown atop its head and its
glittering gold beak are points of pride for Deramon.
Its special move Royal Nuts fires strange objects
akin to eggs or nuts from the thicket on its back.
English.379:
Cherrymon is a Digimon further Digivolved from 
Woodmon, gaining a high degree of intelligence 
and power. Known as the "Lord of the Deep
Forest," it's a terrifying Digimon that lures those 
who wander into the depths of the dark forest 
ever farther inside so they can never leave again. 
Its body produces a hallucinogenic mist to lure 
Digimon deep into the forest. It then uses its 
branch-like tentacles and vines to capture its 
enemies and draw nourishment from them. 
Should you ever encounter an old Woodmon, it 
may be best to defeat it before it can Digivolve into
Cherrymon. Cherrymon's special move Cherry 
Bomb makes use of the forbidden fruit growing in 
the thick branches on its head.
English.380:
This Mutant Digimon is a desktop computer trash 
icon that has come to life through Digivolution. 
Unlike Sukamon, who formed from a mutation of 
discarded data, Garbagemon is the garbage can 
itself. Filth-species Digimon were thought to be the
weakest type before Garbagemon's appearance, 
but now that convention has been turned on its 
head. Its can is like a black hole, and those sucked 
into it disappear from the Digital World without a 
trace. Its special move Poop Bazooka is a vile
attack fired from a bazooka Garbagemon made 
from empty cans.
English.382:
An Armor Holy Knight Digimon that has Digivolved 
with the Digi-Egg of Miracles. The Digi-Egg of 
Miracles has the attribute of Metal and is made of 
the super-metal Chrondigizoid, allowing those 
who gain its power to overcome any crisis.
Magnamon has immense defense capability and 
attack power that's at least on the level of a Mega 
Digimon, and is also a member of the Royal
Knights. It uses its special move Plasma Shot to 
fire a ball of pure plasma, and Shining Gold Solar 
Storm to explode condensed air into a golden 
laser beam that sweeps away surrounding foes.
English.383:
The Mega form of Tyrannomon, having Digivolved by 
fighting a string of intense battles from the time of 
the Digital World's creation. After surviving many long 
years in a harsh environment as MetalTyrannomon, 
RustTyrannomon's cyborg body has turned red with 
rust. In battle, it specializes in rapidly overwhelming 
enemy forces, and is capable of leveling an enemy 
base by itself. RustTyrannomon is a natural predator 
that hunts other Digimon, capable of consuming 
hundreds if not thousands of them in a short span 
of time. Its special moves are Terrors Cluster, with 
which it lowers the cannon on its back to fire a huge 
electromagnetic blast, and Rust Breath, which 
belches a streaming flame the same deep-crimson 
color as its body. Rust Breath also causes anything it 
touches to corrode. When it comes to hand-to-hand 
combat, RustTyrannomon overwhelms its opponents 
with some of the highest raw power and destructive 
capabilities of all Android Digimon.
English.385:
The strongest Digimon in the Digital World, with
a one-hundred percent metal body. Since it
consists of a combination of parts from countless
other cyborg Digimon, all of the other cyborg
Digimon produced so far are thought to have
been merely prototypes for the sake of its 
completion. Machinedramon is strong enough
to overwhelm other Digimon and boasts
incredible processing power, but as a pure
Machine Digimon it lacks a will of its own. Instead,
someone has implanted a program loaded with
malicious intentions into its DigiCore. This
malevolent DigiCore provides Machinedramon
with unlimited power. Its special move Infinity
Cannon fires super-dreadnought class energy
blasts from both cannons.
English.387:
This Slime Digimon looks like a mere bit of sea-green
froth at first glance, but it's actually a totally
autonomous creature with a plethora of expressions.
Pabumon's delicate surface means it has practically
no defense or prowess in combat. It creates infinite
tiny foam clones from the pacifier-like object in its
mouth. This ability was originally used to develop
computer viruses, but Pabumon's lack of life force
made for poor implementation. Life is fleeting for this
adorable Digimon baby. It uses Adhesive Bubble Blow
to release bubbles from its body to bind enemies,
giving Pabumon a chance to escape.
English.388:
A soft-bodied Digimon with highly elastic skin, 
Motimon uses the protrusions beneath its body to
waggle its way around. The name "Motimon" comes
from its resemblance to a mochi rice cake when it 
puffs up its body in excitement. Despite its appearance,
Motimon possesses a surprisingly high degree of
intelligence, and so is believed to have developed
from a computer's dictionary feature. Capable of
understanding human language, Motimon can
occasionally be seen altering the shape of its
body in an effort at communication. Motimon uses
its mochi-like Elastic Bubbles to restrict opponents'
movement.
English.389:
An Amphibian Digimon that walks on four legs.
Betamon is a docile Digimon with a mild
temperament, although it doesn't hesitate to
unleash its special move Electric Shock when
angered, attacking its enemies with over a
million volts of electric current.
English.390:
Lucemon is an Angel Digimon resembling a child,
