said to have descended from on high long ago in
the Ancient Digital World. It appeared in a time of
chaos, and is said to have ushered in a new era of
peace and order. However, due to Lucemon's
subsequent rebellion, the world was then plunged
into a long, dark age. Despite having the appearance
of a child, Lucemon is wiser and more powerful
than an Ultimate Digimon. It's said that in the
modern era, Lucemon's abilities have been passed
down to and divided among the Three Celestials
Lucemon's special move is Grand Cross, which
fires a collection of ten super-heated spheres
of light arranged into the shape of a cross as if
they were planets in alignment. This attack is
even more destructive than Seraphimon's special
move Strike of the Seven Stars.
English.391:
A Beast Man Digimon with the appearance of a
golden fox. The relationship Renamon has with
humans is directly apparent, and its In-Training
form can Digivolve into a Digimon of high
intelligence if raised properly. Calm and
collected at all times, it trains in order to keep
its cool in any situation. Renamon's tall, slender
form stands out among Rookie Digimon, and it
prefers the speed of its many techniques over
power when it comes to fighting the enemy. Its
special move Diamond Storm hurls razor-sharp
wood chips at the enemy.
English.392:
A Larva Digimon with a timid, cowardly personality.
Wormmon is a descendant of the same ancient
species as Veemon, so it can perform a special
Armor Digivolution. Exceedingly weak on its own,
Wormmon stands little chance against larger
Digimon. But with the power of the Digi-Eggs, it
can Armor Digivolve and display incredible power.
Like a larva maturing into an adult, Wormmon will
one day Digivolve into a Champion of great might.
This Digimon is the very embodiment of future
potential. It uses its special move Sticky Net to
shoot viscous webs that bind the enemy.
English.393:
A Vegetation Digimon resembling a great withered 
tree. Made of normal wood, Woodmon catches 
Digimon that pass by and absorbs their energy to
survive. It can also use its root-like limbs to move. 
Brutal by nature, it attacks without rest when
angered. Woodmon's sturdy wooden trunk boasts 
high defense, but it's extremely weak against flame 
and particularly Fire Digimon such as Meramon 
and Birdramon. It uses its special move Branch 
Drain to extend its branch-like appendages, pierce
the opponent and absorb its energy.
English.394:
A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese 
folklore. The attacks from Ogremon's frighteningly
well-developed muscles bring tremendous destructive
power to bear. Extremely intelligent but just as
temperamental, this rage-driven being wreaks all
the havoc it can. Belligerent to a fault, it will boldly
challenge even opponents with significantly higher
battle strength compared to its own, and this has
earned it the moniker of the "Digimon Hunter."
The bone club Ogremon wields in its right hand
was earned from defeating SkullGreymon in battle.
It unleashes its special move Pummel Whack by
swinging its massive arms.
English.395:
A Mysterious Beast Digimon in the shape of a giant
fox with nine tails. Kyubimon is feared as a beast
that brings destruction and decay, but in ancient
times it was hailed as a bringer of peace. A Renamon
with particularly strong abilities and a wide range of
experience is said to Digivolve into a Kyubimon.
This Digimon lacks attack power, but possesses
incredible spiritual energy and specializes in spells.
The blue flames burning on its four limbs apparently
allow Kyubimon to gallop through the heavens.
Its signature move Fox Tail Inferno creates and
controls will-o'-the-wisps.
English.396:
A savage Beast Dragon Digimon possessing the 
temperament of both beast and dragon, this 
heavyweight creature makes most Digimon flee at 
the mere sight of its shadow. Dorugamon can be 
ferocious like a wild beast in battle, but the dragon 
intelligence at its disposal means it's usually quite 
docile. Because of the antiquated interface on its 
forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the 
Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon."
Dorugamon uses the special move Power Metal
to shoot a large iron ball from its mouth and crush
its foe.
English.397:
A mythical Ancient Digimon that, even in the vast 
expanse of the Digital World, is said to have only
existed on the Folder Continent. Veedramon is 
extremely valuable to Digimon Tamers and rarely 
encountered, even on the Folder Continent. It's said
that only one Tamer has ever been able to win this 
Digimon over. Other than the V-shaped mark on its
chest, for which it's named, not much is known
about Veedramon or its surrounding ecosystem. It's 
sometimes mistaken for a dog for some reason. It
has extraordinary attacking power for a Champion
Digimon, exhibiting strength even outstripping that
of an Ultimate when the chips are down. It uses its
special move V-Nova Blast to shoot out a
high-temperature heat ray from its mouth.
English.398:
A guardian of time that governs computer timers. 
Clockmon manages all "time" and "space" on
computers and across the Net, and can move time
forward and backward freely between the years 
1900 and 1999. It always maintains a neutral 
stance due to this incredibly dangerous and
terrifying ability, refusing to take part in conflict 
between Vaccine and Virus Digimon. Many think 
that if Clockmon were to lean toward either side 
of this equilibrium, the Digital World itself would 
collapse. It uses its special move Chrono Breaker 
to destroy the very time that flows in the enemy's 
body.
English.399:
An Amphibian Digimon that mesmerizes those around
it with a cry altogether too pleasant for its strange
appearance. The chords Gekomon plays with the
three holes at the end of its tongue and the
improvisations created on the horn wrapped around
its neck can control its opponent's feelings. Rumor
has it that it's born when a hit song is created in
composition software, making Gekomon a kind of 
status symbol among musicians the world over. Its 
special move Symphony Crusher destroys the enemy's
insides with ultra-high frequency vibrations.
English.400:
AeroVeedramon is a further-Digivolved form of 
Veedramon that's become capable of flight. Only 
the strongest of the Veedramon line can Digivolve
into AeroVeedramon by making it through countless 
battles, and since Veedramon is a rare species to 
begin with, AeroVeedramon is practically a legend. It 
also gained more than wings in the process of 
Digivolving, and now boasts increased offensive and 
defensive capabilities. Its special move Dragon 
Impulse unleashes a shockwave in the shape of a 
dragon.
English.401:
A Digivolution of Kuwagamon, evolved into something
even more sinister than a Kabuterimon-type Digimon.
The predominant improvement is its defense, which
Kuwagamon lacks. Okuwamon's ability to detect foes
with its antennae has been boosted, and its pincer
attacks have augmented precision. Furthermore, it's 
clear that its most prominent characteristics aren't 
only its survival instinct, but also its destructive impulse.
Truly a Digivolution steeped in aggression. Its special
move Double Scissor Claw is an upgraded version of
Scissor Claw that's able to slice through even the
hardest diamond.
English.402:
A Black Dragon Digimon developed at the same time 
as Megadramon. A combat dragon fully armed with 
further modifications, Gigadramon's existence is the
epitome of a fiendish computer virus. Its special
move Eradication Gears unleashes infinite organic
missiles.
English.403:
GrapLeomon is a martial artist Beast Man Digimon. 
After taking in data from various fighting games, it 
developed its own super moves that it uses to crush 
opponents. By spinning the turbines on its arms and 
legs at high speeds, GrapLeomon is able to unleash 
a wide variety of techniques. To keep them spinning, 
though, it must channel its fighting spirit directly 
from its DigiCore into them all at once, which 
requires exceptional force of will. It's only because 
GrapLeomon has inherited the data of Leomon, the 
"King of Beasts," that it's able to spin its turbines at 
such incredible speeds, using a sheer, singlehearted 
devotion to justice. Its special move The King of Fists 
spins the turbines on its arms so quickly that it's able 
to distort gravity with a single blow.
English.404:
This skeleton Digimon is nothing but skin and 
bones—minus the skin. Singularly fixated on 
fighting, it extended its life through combat
instinct alone, even as its body rotted away, 
eventually becoming SkullGreymon. Without a 
scrap of intelligence or reason left to restrain its 
instinct, SkullGreymon's existence is a threat to 
other Digimon. Its special move is an organic 
missile fired from its spinal cord. The latest 
research suggests that this attack eventually 
evolved into Oblivion Bird, which adds a new
tracking function and dramatically upgrades both 
power and range.
English.405:
A Taoist Digimon that uses all the skills of faith to 
defeat opponents. Taomon is particularly talented 
at using curses and talismans. It's also a master of 
dark implements, keeping various weapons hidden 
in its sleeves. This Digimon doesn't say much and 
usually resides in the dark. Taomon can also change 
talismans into familiars known as shikigami. It uses
its special move Talisman of Light to paint a Sanskrit 
character in midair while chanting before hurling it 
at the enemy. Any enemy hit by the Talisman of 
Light is annihilated in a gigantic explosion.
English.406:
A Digivolution of Meramon wreathed in intense 
blue fire. The flames erupting from SkullMeramon's 
body burn hotter than Meramon's, thus the blue 
coloration. Its attack and defense capabilities have 
increased several levels, and it wields supreme
destructive power in addition to the might of its 
flames. Fire Digimon are weak against Water and 
Ice-Snow types to begin with, but any interaction 
on their part with SkullMeramon is like water 
sizzling off a heated stone. SkullMeramon uses its 
special move Heavy Metal Fire to melt the heavy
metals in its body and spit them at the enemy.
English.407:
DoruGreymon is a massive Beast Dragon Digimon 
also known as "The Final Enemy." Its form is the 
result of the interface on its forehead unlocking the 
dragon data lying dormant deep within its DigiCore, 
filled with the powerful life force of that mythical
beast. With its overwhelming size, it's able to utterly 
crush any Digimon daring enough to oppose it, and 
its power enables it to repel an attack from 
Nightmare Soldiers with a single flap of its wings. 
DoruGreymon is also highly intelligent, and since it 
only rarely reveals itself, simply being able to find it 
is extremely difficult. Its special move Metal Meteor 
unleashes a supermassive iron sphere more than 
ten times its own immense size, wiping out its foes 
all at once.
English.408:
A Dragon Man Digimon DNA Digivolved from an 
ExVeemon and a Stingmon. It retains many 
elements of Dragon types, with the power of a
dragon and the iron-wall defense of an insect's 
carapace. More than just powerful, Paildramon also 
uses quick and agile moves to finish off opponents. 
It's very loyal, and will unquestioningly lay down its 
life for its master. Paildramon uses its special move 
Death Parade Blaster to fire an energy wave from 
two biological cannons extending from its waist.
English.409:
A proud Beast Man Digimon with a strong sense of 
justice. Some Leomon Digivolve into IceLeomon 
when, in the process of their daily training as 
champions of justice, their bodies become infused 
with the power of cold in the frozen land of the 
Digital World's Ice-Snow Area. IceLeomon's body 
and will have been tempered by the freezing cold, 
and it doesn't falter in the face of any attack. Its 
special move Fist of Ice is a punch infused with 
the power of cold.
English.410:
A Pixie Digimon that controls magic. Piximon can 
recite words in an advanced programming language 
from another dimension, allowing it to create 
wonders akin to magic. This mysterious Digimon 
can appear anytime, anyplace and in any space. 
While small, it possesses a special skill that allows 
it to seal off the abilities of its foes and pulverize its 
opponents with a single, powerful strike. Piximon 
loves a good prank, and enjoys making computers 
run amok with the beloved spear "Fairy Tale" it always 
wields (not that it bears any ill will). Its special move 
Pit Bomb compresses a computer virus, generating 
a super-powerful explosion. Piximon uses terrifying 
attacks, despite its appearance.
English.411:
An Alien Digimon shaped like a creature from the 
far reaches of outer space. Still, rumor says it was
born of a plant seed. Vademon possesses terrifying
offensive power belying its massive head and
octopus-like lower frame. The abduction beam fired
from the ray gun in its hand is fearsome, but its
special move Unidentified Flying Kiss is even more 
so, as it makes fools of its opponents.
English.412:
A Mutant Digimon Digivolved in a cruel environment. 
Mamemon's cute exterior conceals a terrifying
destructive power. Apart from one other Digimon, 
it might be the most powerful species. The gigantic 
hands on its small body are detachable, and are
capable of becoming powerful bombs. Its nickname
is the "Smile Bomber."
English.413:
An Android Digimon that Digivolved to become even 
more powerful than the "Smile Bomber" Mamemon. 
Its cuteness hasn't changed, nor have the painful
consequences facing those tricked by its appearance. 
90% of MetalMamemon's body has been mechanized.
The tremendous destructive force of its special move
Energy Bomb fired from the Psycho Blaster on its
left arm can fell a foe with certainty.
English.414:
A Giant Bird Digimon resembling a parrot. 
Parrotmon is a strange bird from another Digital 
World that wandered in through a rift in space-time. 
The claws on its feet are extremely powerful. Highly
intelligent and calm, Parrotmon doesn't relish combat,
but once angered, it flies out of control. Its special
move Mjölnir Thunder creates an electrical current
in the feathers sprouting from its head and then
uses them to call down lightning on its opponent.
English.416:
One of the 13 Royal Knights, who are said to be
the highest-ranking Digimon when it comes to
Network security. Although Alphamon itself is a 
Holy Knight, it's said to act as a deterrent to other 
Holy Knights. It typically prefers to remain hidden, 
and is widely known as the "Aloof Hermit," 
identifiable by the blue cape that flutters around it. 
The position it occupies in the Royal Knights is 
known as the "Empty Seat." In battle, it has the 
ability to access Alpha inForce, an ultimate power 
that can instantly reverse what would otherwise 
be a lost cause. Its special moves are Blade of the 
Dragon King, which involves drawing out light 
gathered in the center of a magic circle, then using 
it to pierce a foe, and Soul Digitalization, which 
involves spreading the wings on its back to take 
flight, then creating a giant magic circle in the sky, 
which it uses to summon a legendary monster 
from another dimension.
English.417:
UlforceVeedramon is a legendary Holy Knight Digimon 
appearing only in a prophecy passed down from the 
Ancient Digital World. The appearance of the Royal 
Knights, the holy defenders of the Network, was 
written of in this prophecy, and it's said the members 
of the Royal Knights will all gather because of this 
prophecy when the Digital World faces its greatest
crisis. Even among the Royal Knights, 
UlforceVeedramon's speed is exceptional, such that 
it's impossible to follow its movements. It has 
V-Bracelets on both arms, and is clad in armor made 
of Blue Digizoid, an extremely rare metal, allowing it 
to shoot through the sky and blast across the earth. 
Its special move is The Ray of Victory, with which it 
fires a beam of energy from the V-shaped armor on 
its chest to wipe out foes.
English.419:
This Fighter Mode form is the result of the Ancient 
Dragon Digimon Imperialdramon: Dragon Mode
unleashing all its power and transforming into a 
legendary Dragon Warrior. By changing from its
unwieldy Dragon Mode to this humanoid form, it 
became a Mega Digimon with high intelligence. Its 
attacks are said to hold the power to destroy planets. 
Imperialdramon: Fighter Mode's special move 
Positron Laser fires the weapon equipped to its right 
arm. It also uses Giga Death to insert the Positron
Laser into the dragon face on its chest before
unleashing a destructive energy wave with all the
energy stored in its body. This strike holds ten times
the power of Mega Death in Dragon Mode.
Rumor has it that a separate, more powerful mode
can be achieved when it awakens to perfect justice.
English.420:
The Dragon Warrior Digimon, Imperialdramon: Fighter 
Mode, powered up into this legendary Holy Knight
(Paladin Mode) by obtaining the power of the Holy 
Knight Omnimon. This is the final, strongest form of
Imperialdramon, foretold of since ancient times, that 
descended upon the Ancient Digital World during a
great calamity in order to save it from complete 
destruction. All details of that time are shrouded in
mystery. Continued research into Digimon and the 
Digital World should eventually shed light on the 
subject. Imperialdramon: Paladin Mode uses its
special move Omni Blade to cleave the enemy in two 
with its ultimate sword, resetting and neutralizing its
component data.
English.421:
A Super Angel Digimon that is the ultimate form of 
all feminine Angel Digimon. Together with Seraphimon 
and Cherubimon, Ophanimon is one of the Three 
Celestial Digimon who guard the area known as the 
Kernel (or Domain of the Gods) in the heart of
the Digital World. Ophanimon represents the merciful 
and compassionate aspects of the gods, serving as 
the holy mother of the Digital World, while Seraphimon 
is the unforgiving marshall of the gods and Cherubimon 
is the steadfast defender of the gods and wisdom. 
Each has its own role to play. Ophanimon's special 
moves are EDEN's Javelin and Sefirot Crystal.
English.422:
Machinedramon, a Digimon made from the parts of 
countless Cyborg Digimon, possesses unimaginable
powers, and as such was apparently considered a 
successful experiment. Chaosdramon, with its 
crimson metal body, is an even more advanced
version of Machinedramon. Its frame is made from 
Red Digizoid, a rare metal made by re-refining the 
virtual super-metal Chrondigizoid to increase its 
hardness. As a result, it's capable of repelling all 
manner of attacks, and destroying absolutely
anything. Its special move Hyper Infinity Cannon 
fires super-dreadnought class energy blasts from 
both of its cannons.
English.423:
The supreme form of the Kuwagamon species. 
Particularly evil even for an Insectoid Digimon, an 
encounter with GranKuwagamon in the Digital 
World spells doom. Since it normally lives deep 
within the forest and is only active at night, it's also 
known as the "Demon of the Deep Forest." It's 
HerculesKabuterimon's greatest rival, and the two 
are locked in an interminable struggle. 
GranKuwagamon's special move is Dimension 
Scissor, which cuts through everything around it, 
including space itself.
English.424:
An Ancient Beast Digimon said to be capable of 
Mach-speed movement. Even so, details of this 
Digimon are veiled in mystery. One theory even 
posits that this may be a Leomon turned feral. 
SaberLeomon's speed allows it to dodge even the 
swiftest attacks with ease. It's known as the ultimate 
Digimon due to the tremendous destructive power 
afforded by its two developed fangs and sharp claws. 
SaberLeomon's special move Infinity Arrow hardens 
the countless hairs on its mane before firing them at 
the opponent. These hairs are venomous, paralyzing 
anything they come in contact with. Howling Crusher
is a fearsome technique with which SaberLeomon 
eviscerates the enemy using its giant claws.
English.425:
A Digimon with the role of a priestess that acts to 
execute the will of the gods. Like Taomon, Sakuyamon
uses Taoist skills in battle, and can command
God Beast Digimon. It always carries four pipes
on its belt, in which reside four pipe foxes. The pipe
foxes can be used for attacking, gathering information
and more. It uses its special move Amethyst Mandala
to strike the ground with its Kongou Shakujou staff,
creating a purifying field that exorcises evil.
English.426:
HiAndromon is a Mega Android Digimon created by 
upgrading and completing the unfinished Andromon. 
It features a higher percentage of Chrondigizoid 
parts in the composition of its body, which alone 
should make it clear that HiAndromon has a level of
offensive and defensive power that Andromon could 
never match. The addition of Chrondigizoid parts 
to the incomplete bio-synapse circuits responsible 
for Andromon's thought processes has given 
HiAndromon the ability to think for itself and pursue 
its own objectives. Its special move is Atomic Ray, 
which involves joining its hands to fuse the neutronic 
energy from the blue neutron control turbine in its 
right shoulder with the atomic energy from the red 
atomic control turbine in its left shoulder and firing a 
beam of light to obliterate foes.
English.427:
Piedmon is an odd-looking and elusive Wizard 
Digimon shrouded in mystery. Wizard Digimon are 
strange beings, so different from Evil-species and
Undead types that they may as well be from another 
dimension. Piedmon's true identity is unknown, as 
are the reasons for its sudden appearance. The 
very reason for its existence is a mystery, and it's 
currently unclear how to learn more about it. 
What is quite evident, however, is that it possesses 
incomparable power. Anyone who encounters 
Piedmon can do little but curse their own fate. 
Piedmon's special move is Trump Sword, with
which it teleports the four swords stuck through the 
magic box on its back so that they suddenly 
reappear, skewering the opponent—an inescapable
attack.
English.428:
Puppetmon is a Mega Puppet Digimon made from the 
body of the dreaded Cherrymon. It's widely believed 
that a malicious hacker created Puppetmon from 
Cherrymon's data. Although Puppetmon may look 
like a simple marionette, it has a will of its own, and 
is fully capable of moving around by itself. 
Puppetmon is a liar with a twisted personality, and 
whenever a computer produces bad data, Puppetmon
is usually involved somehow. Its most powerful attack 
is the special move Puppet Pummel, with which it 
loads gunpowder into its revolver-shaped hammer, 
then smashes foes with it. Anything hit by this attack 
has to bear the brunt not only of the hammer blow 
but also the explosion created by the gunpowder, 
meaning most of Puppetmon's targets are utterly
destroyed.
English.429:
A prince of the Mamemon world that incorporated
data related to royal families from the Net.
PrinceMamemon partners with KingEtemon and
pretends to be a member of Digital World
royalty—hence its opulent appearance. While its
personality isn't so bad, it's instigated by KingEtemon
into thinking of itself as truly royal. Embarrassingly,
it even believes that the Royal Knights are its
subordinates. PrinceMamemon's special move is
Smile Warhead, which unleashes an intense headbutt
with an unwavering grin across its face. It boasts
tremendous destructive power belying its looks, as
one would expect from a Mega Digimon.
English.431:
A prototype Android Digimon built at the same time as 
Andromon. The flesh-based Boltmon has emotions,
unlike the machine-based Andromon. While quite 
powerful, Boltmon was difficult to control, went 
berserk and ended up consigned to oblivion. This 
tragic Digimon roams within the darkness of its grief, 
its very existence disavowed. Boltmon's special move 
is Tomahawk Stinger, with which it swings its gigantic
battle axe around with deft skill.
English.434:
This final form of Seadramon is completely covered 
in the ultra-metal known as Chrondigizoid alloy. The 
fastest Aquatic Digimon out there, MetalSeadramon's 
metal body is capable of repelling any and all attacks. 
It was remodeled to be an aquatic interceptor Digimon,
completing the set of interceptor Digimon for
terrestrial, marine and aerial defense.
MetalSeadramon's special move is River of Power, 
which fires an energy blast from the cannon at the 
end of its nose.
English.435:
Lucemon's final form, with the appearance of a dragon 
that appears in Revelation. As foretold in that text, 
Lucemon: Satan Mode wears the Crown of the 
Seven Deadly Sins, and carries an orb of darkness 
known as Gehenna that nullifies any and all attacks. 
It's been said that the world will perish once Lucemon 
takes this form. However, Lucemon's true form, 
Lucemon: Larva, exists within Gehenna, and Lucemon: 
Satan Mode is actually no more than Lucemon's
shadow. For that reason, no attack on Lucemon: 
Satan Mode reaches the true form Lucemon: 
Larva. Lucemon: Satan Mode's special moves 
are Purgatorial Flame, a flame of destruction that 
purifies all, and Divine Atonement, an annihilating
beam fired from the seven crowns.
English.437:
A brand new type of Digimon. Three feelers grow 
from the top of its gelatinous, red body. Punimon is
incapable of fighting, instead relying on Acid Bubbles
to threaten enemies.
English.438:
A small Digimon with a single horn on its head, formed
by hardening one of Punimon's feelers. Having
Digivolved to be more animalistic than Punimon,
Tsunomon is covered in soft fur. Filled with a playful
spirit, Tsunomon loves to pull pranks, and has yet to
develop its instinct for conflict.
English.439:
An Evil King Digimon said to be sealed in the deepest 
parts of the Dark Area. Because of its immense power, 
Belphemon's data was put into Sleep Mode by the 
Digital World's systems. Belphemon: Sleep Mode 
can't attack directly due to this deep slumber, yet its 
snores alone inflict damage, making this Digimon 
difficult to attack. Its special moves are Eternal 
Nightmare, which unleashes attacks through peaceful 
snoring, and Lampranthus, which shoots black flames
from the chains coiled around its body. Eternal 
Nightmare is recommended for those suffering from
insomnia, as everlasting slumber is practically 
guaranteed.
English.440:
The counterattack Titan, born from the grudge of a 
Digimon felled by the Olympos XII in a contest for
supremacy over the Digital World. Also going by the 
alias "One-Man Division," Titamon harbors bottomless
grudge energy within its mighty body. It runs from 
battlefield to battlefield, all in pursuit of the heads of 
the Olympos XII. Titamon's huge arms are covered in a 
large quantity of skulls, each formed from strength 
data pilfered from fallen foes. Its gigantic Zanjintou 
sword is carved from the bones of SkullGreymon, and 
the rancor dwelling within the blade emits a low growl.
Titamon's special move Soul Core Attack slices 
straight through an enemy's armor and body, cleaving
its DigiCore directly with its blade. Damage taken 
from a direct hit can never be healed. Phantom Blade
runs a foe through with Zanjintou, plunging it into a 
hallucination that it remains pierced even after the
blade is pulled out. The pain of this stab only subsides
with the death of the enemy's spirit.
English.450:
A Digimon based on an imaginary creature found in 
the computer of a British cryptozoology research
facility, long spoken of in rumor by its researchers. 
Plesiomon hardly ever reveals itself, with such rare
occasions said to come only on foggy days with low 
visibility. The body of this mysterious creature shines 
with white light, impressing all who observe its 
elegance. Plesiomon's special move is Sorrow Blue, 
which unleashes a shrill, crystal-clear vocalization 
that plunges its listeners into a deep sadness, 
sapping them of their will to fight.
English.451:
An Android Digimon artificially created from a 
captured Vademon that had its body's compositional 
data analyzed and improved. Ebemon is rumored to 
have been produced using extraterrestrial technology 
at a site known as Area 51, but the truth remains 
shrouded in mystery. Its special move Brain Rupture 
involves firing a cracking program from the gun in its 
left hand into its opponent's brain to absorb the data
accumulated there. Planet Destroyer, by contrast, 
involves shooting out all the power Ebemon has 
amassed from the gun in its right hand. This move is 
said to be capable of instantaneously destroying an 
entire planet. Rumor has it that the country that 
created Ebemon is secretly researching Digimon so 
it can rule the Digital World.
English.452:
A one-eyed Dragon Man Digimon with an abnormally 
developed right arm. Once a brawny dragon warrior, 
Cyclonemon had its right eye crushed by the warrior 
Leomon, transforming it into a demon of revenge. 
It strengthens and grows its arm larger in order to 
defeat Leomon, and hunts for a chance at retribution.
Shedding its pride as a warrior, Cyclonemon is now
a maddened combatant who thinks only of slaughter,
all for the sake of revenge. Its special move is
Hyper Heat, which melts any and all things.
English.453:
The ultimate form of all God Beast Digimon. Thought
of as the heroic king of the sky, few have ever seen
Magnadramon, and its location is generally unknown. 
However, it's said that once, when a great dark power
arose in the Digital World, Magnadramon appeared 
as if from nowhere and reduced that evil to nothing 
with its immense strength. Its special move is Fire 
Tornado, which blasts its opponent with a radiant 
beam of pure justice. Anyone struck by this attack 
is instantly reduced to nothingness.
English.454:
An Android Digimon that guards the mysterious Royal
Base, a secret floating honey base. The antennae 
on Waspmon's head have excellent scouting 
capabilities, and it constantly patrols in search of
Digimon approaching the base, attacking any who 
even draw near. The propellers on its shoulders and
stabilizer on its back let it move rapidly in all 
directions as it defends against approaching foes,
driving them off with its powerful laser cannon. 
Waspmon's special move is Turbo Stinger, which 
fires its large-caliber laser cannon in a rapid burst.
English.455:
A Crustacean Digimon formed when a Numemon is 
smart enough to search out a shell to protect itself. 
This makes ShellNumemon slightly more intelligent 
than Numemon, but also much more skittish, causing
it to flee into its shell at the slightest provocation.
Its defense increases dramatically while inside its
shell, allowing it to withstand kicks, stomps and the
like. Its special move is Mature Poop, by which it
hurls gobs of poop it's accumulated in its shell.
English.456:
A Mutant Digimon with a gun barrel for a body.
Though the particulars of its genesis are completely
unknown, Deputymon's sense of justice makes it an 
active member of the Virus Busters, special Digimon
among Vaccine-attribute types with the ability to
eradicate and delete the "evil" will of Virus Digimon. It
also loves gambling—especially Russian roulette—and
its fairness is beyond reproach, allowing even Virus 
Digimon to get away if they win at this game. 
Deputymon's special move is Justice Bullet, which 
transforms Deputymon itself into a gun that unleashes 
a justice-imbued round.
English.457:
Dracmon is the Dark Area's biggest prankster. It
won't hesitate to risk life and limb if that means
successfully pulling off a prank. One time, for
instance, it nearly died when it decided to try to
draw doodles on the faces of all Four Sovereign
Digimon (whether it succeeded or not is unclear).
While technically a vampiric Digimon, rumor has
it that lately it's been so absorbed in pulling a
prank on the Royal Knights that it's forgotten all
about drinking blood. It's also said that anyone
that looks directly into the Eye of Nightmares
cast from the evil eyes on its palms are subject
to its mind control.
English.458:
A Mini Dragon Digimon incapable of flight, despite
the bat-like wings on both arms. Monodramon's
personality is rather rough—bordering on brutal,
and it gives the impression of a Digimon that enjoys
a good scrap. It's often found in the middle of most
Digital World brawls, causing even the likes of Ogremon
to get fed up with its persistence. Monodramon's
special move is Knuckle Beater, charging into the
enemy with staggering force before unleashing
its powerful claws in a straightforward strike.
English.461:
Revived from ancient times, Mammothmon 
continuously battled Virus Digimon until its whole 
body became consumed by viruses, reducing it to
this Undead Digimon composed entirely of bones. 
SkullMammothmon's survival instinct as a 
Vaccine-attribute type has only grown stronger after 
death. In order to keep fighting, it's shed all emotion 
and intellect that doesn't aid in the extermination of
viruses. As long as the DigiCore shining in its chest 
remains unharmed, SkullMammothmon can maintain 
vital activity even as a skeleton. The moment this 
exposed DigiCore is attacked, however, spells the 
end for this Digimon. SkullMammothmon's special 
move is Spiral Bone, hurling and spinning one of its 
vertebrae at high speed.
English.463:
A Vehicle-species Digimon similar to Mekanorimon, 
capable of leisurely flights through the sky. 
Blimpmon's soft balloon parts are protected by a
metal coating, but it appears to still be under 
development, as its left flank remains exposed.
Its signature move is Zeppelin Explosion, where it
fires cannonballs from the two cannons on top.
English.465:
An Airship Digimon that soars through the heavens.
The previously incomplete Blimpmon Digivolved into
MasterBlimpmon via improvements and remodeling.
Now complete, its formerly exposed balloon has
been equipped with armor. Its finalized armor has
reduced air resistance, increasing MasterBlimpmon's
cruising speed. This allows it to deliver its passenger
Digimon swiftly to the battlefield.
For its Zeppelin Circus move, MasterBlimpmon
shoots a bombardment of guided missiles from its
many gunports. During Daredevil Break, it crashes
at breakneck speed into enemy encampments,
ramming them with the drill on its bow.
English.466:
A Lesser Digimon that can run extremely fast, but 
only in a straight line. Dorimon hate to be tamed, so
many remain feral. Approaching it is dangerous, as 
it will charge in recklessly for a tackle. Dorimon's 
pointed ears are tough, acting as horns and inflicting
a modicum of damage when it tackles. That being 
said, it can't turn once it has gained enough speed. 
Dorimon's special move is Metal Drop, spitting metal
beads as it charges toward the enemy.
English.474:
A Dragon Man Digimon resembling a humanoid 
lizard. Dinohyumon lives in an untamed land where 
every member of its fierce battle dragon tribe has
the makings of a warrior. Its burly muscles allow it
to swing its greatsword "Akinakes" with ease.
Dinohyumon's special move is Lizard Dance, which 
employs dance-like movements to cleave through 
foes with Akinakes and the blades on its arms.
English.479:
A Machine Digimon born when the CAD data of
construction machinery leaked onto a server and
fused with Beast Digimon configuration data.
LoaderLeomon's mane is a pneumatic drill, and it
operates primarily in tunnel construction and
Chrondigizoit mining. Chrondigizoit mines are often
surrounded by hard layers of bedrock. In addition to
its power and stamina, it also boasts top-class
abilities for a Machine Digimon. Many LoaderLeomon
have stubborn personalities and take pride in their
work, but others simply treat them like belligerent
hotheads much of the time. One mine with the best
ore deposits in the world supposedly vanished as
the result of a fight between multiple LoaderLeomon.
LoaderLeomon's special move is Bowling Storm,
which unleashes its mane in high-speed rotation.
English.484:
An Insectoid Digimon resembling a jewel beetle that 
emits a rainbow radiance. JewelBeemon's prismatic
armor changes colors depending on the viewing angle, 
dazzling the enemy in addition to offering protection. 
This melee expert prefers beautiful battles. Its special
move is Spike Buster, with which it swings the
spear in its right hand at the speed of light and 
creates shockwaves.
English.489:
A final, legendary Digivolution, the end result of 
limitless potential realized through the deepened 
bond of an Agumon and its partner. The fortuitous 
courage of its partner becomes burning flame that 
erupts from its body, emerging as proof of their 
deep faith in each other. Having deepened its 
understanding of humans through this long 
relationship, its Digivolved form takes on an almost
humanoid appearance. Agumon (Bond of Bravery) 
uses its special moves Red Reamer to burn the 
enemy with high-density red lasers from its claw 
tips, and Gaia Brave to unleash the flame of
courage within it as a superheated energy bomb.
English.490:
A final, legendary Digivolution, the end result of 
limitless potential realized through the deepened 
bond of a Gabumon and its partner. The undying 
friendship of its partner becomes elegant armor 
that covers its body, materializing as proof of the
trust coursing through both of them. The photon 
wings sprouting from its back allow it to fly, but it 
can also transform into the shape of a motorcycle, 
the vehicle beloved by its partner, letting them ride
together. Gabumon (Bond of Friendship) uses its 
special moves Cool Edge to jettison its cowl parts
for an instantaneous strike, and Raddle Star to
unleash AI-equipped tracking weapons.
English.491:
The self-proclaimed strongest hand-to-hand fighter
in the Digital World, GreatGrizzlymon lives to
entertain those who watch its battles. Its
performance in battle captivates onlooking Digimon
and enlivens the battlefield. It's a hard worker that
never neglects its training so that it can live up to
the audience's expectations. Any fight with
PileVolcanomon, its eternal rival, is a big event that
draws in large crowds. Its special move is Spirited
Claws, by it which slashes its foes with its fiery claws.
English.492:
A Dark Beast Digimon that resembles a bear.
Although it's considered to be a Digivolution from
the Grizzlymon line, it's a mutant Digivolved
from Digimon with abnormal data. It's unknown
whether these data anomalies that create it are
spontaneous or intentional, and since its numbers
are small, its ecology and Digivolution conditions
remain a mystery. Callismon's enormous arms and
weapons make it highly effective in combat, and it
exhibits a ferocious nature that attacks hostile
opponents relentlessly until they fall. Its special
moves are Deep Forest, which degrades the
opponent's data by slashing with its sharp claws,
and Rodeo Bullet, by which it fires homing shots
from its three cannons.
English.510:
A Bulb Digimon with a big flower blooming on its head.
Yokomon moves by deftly manipulating its root-like
tentacles, and is able to float softly through the air,
albeit for short distances. A curious creature,
its restless movements are delightful to behold.
Yokomon tend to live in groups—from dozens to
hundreds.
English.512:
A Bulb Digimon with what appears to be a seedling
sprouting from its head. Tanemon Digivolved from a
Yuramon that landed on the ground after drifting 
through the air in search of the perfect environment.
Extremely skittish, it will use its four legs to quickly 
dig a hole so it can hide its body at the first sign of 
a threat. While Tanemon's body is hidden underground,
the seedling on its head makes it indistinguishable
from a plant, protecting it from harm. That being said,
this tactic proves ineffective against herbivorous
Digimon.
English.514:
Despite resembling an aquatic dinosaur infant, this 
playful Digimon can move as skillfully as a seahorse.
Bukamon is quick to flee when others draw near, 
however. Its skin still isn't fit for the high pressure 
and low temperature of ocean depths, so it can 
only spend limited amounts of time submerged in 
the deep.
English.515:
A small Digimon with feline traits. Fickle by nature,
Nyaromon has quite catlike behavior. While curious
and capricious in equal measure, it has a lonely side
as well. Nyaromon uses its special move Fox Tail to
whip the enemy with the wiry hairs on its tail.
However, not a single foe has ever been seen flinching
under this attack.
English.548:
A Mythical Beast Digimon based on mythical creatures 
of legend, with the wings of Pegasus and the horn of 
a unicorn. It travels across the Net in the blink of an 
eye with the large wings on its back, and stabs foes 
with the sharp horn on its forehead. A "wild" Unimon 
is as hot-blooded as any untamed horse, but once 
trained, the Tamer can handle it with ease. Its special 
move is Holy Shot, which belches an energy bomb 
from its large mouth.
English.564:
A Mammal Digimon with a strong sense of curiosity
and a love of mischief that it retained after its
Digivolution from Tsunomon. Elecmon fans out its
nine tails like a peacock in order to intimidate foes in
battle. Its special move is Sparkling Thunder.
English.567:
A small Digimon that can perform low-altitude flight 
with the ear-like appendages on its head. Pagumon 
can use these ears deftly like hands, often pulling 
down its enemy's eyelids or slapping their rear with
them mockingly. Particularly mean-spirited, it can 
often be seen teasing the likes of Koromon or
Tsunomon, chasing them around and around. 
Pagumon may even spit Poison Bubbles from its 
mouth to bully other Digimon.
English.569:
A Mammal Digimon with huge, sharp claws.
Gazimon is bipedal, an unusual trait for Mammal
types. The claws on its front limbs may have
developed while it used them like arms, causing
Gazimon to rely on its hind legs for ambulation.
Despite its small stature, this Digimon has an
exceedingly wild temperament, and never even
attempts to get along with humans. The claws
on Gazimon's forelimbs are extremely effective for
attacking, but are also surprisingly well-suited to
digging holes. Due to its mischievous nature, it
enjoys making pitfalls for other Digimon to fall
into. Gazimon's special move is Electric Stun Blast,
which belches out a poisonous gas.
English.573:
A Baby Bird Digimon Digivolved from samurai-related
data. Hyokomon trains tirelessly to master the way of
the sword and is also developing a secret technique.
When it comes to swordsmanship, it talks the talk,
but doesn't quite walk the walk yet. The next
Digivolution of Hyokomon will only happen when it
breaks out of its shell through endless sword training.
Its special move is Downward Cleave, utilizing its wings
and leg strength to jump up and swing its sword straight
down to split its foe in two.
English.574:
A Bird Man Digimon Digivolved through continuous
training with the sword. This led to acquiring mastery
over wielding two blades. Buraimon roams the
Digital World to continue its training and also
serves as a bodyguard, relying on its honed skills.
Seemingly willing to take on any job for a reward,
it's often treated as a thug. In reality, it's a gentle
soul that never takes a job that hurts the weak.
Buraimon's special move is Dual Swallow Reversal,
a cross slash performed quickly with two swords to
slice down a foe.
English.575:
A Deity Digimon Digivolved with honed swordsmanship
from many a battle, Butenmon wears crimson armor
and wields a greatsword. In its Ultimate form, it has
nearly perfected sword mastery. It possesses beautiful
sword technique and the power to shatter mountains.
A single Butenmon is said to be worth a thousand
warriors. Its special move is Sunburst Dance, which
cuts down foes in its path in a graceful motion that
looks like a dance depicting the sun.
English.576:
A super-mini Machine Digimon used for healing. 
Originally a Vaccine-attribute Digimon for repairing 
crashed computers, Datamon's thought processing 
circuits were corrupted after it was attacked by a 
strong Virus-attribute Digimon, causing it to go 
rogue. It will try—albeit poorly—to "rebuild" the data 
of correctly-functioning computers. Its forte is 
destroying any kind of data. No matter how strong
the Digimon, Datamon will easily destroy the data
that comprises its body. Its special move is Digital
Bomb, which fires an attack from its fingertips.
English.577:
A Goblimon whose duty it is to hear the will of the
gods and convey it to its clan. Shamamon conducts
a ritual in which it performs a strange dance, and
supposedly hears divine messages once its fervor
reaches its peak. Shamamon's clan uses this ritual to
foretell matters of import. Shamamon uses its special
move Shama Hammer to bonk the enemy on the head
with the large club it also uses in its ritual.
English.578:
A Goblimon raised in cold, snowy countries.
SnowGoblimon wears a warm hat and vest, so
cold places are no problem for it, and the skin on
the soles of its feet is thick enough to let it traipse
over snow without issue. SnowGoblimon's special
move is Snow Goblin Volt, which bats rock-filled
snowballs at its foe with all the fervor of a demon.
English.579:
A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese 
folklore. Fugamon is from the same clan as Ogremon, 
and shares its wild, battle-loving nature. Attacks 
unleashed from this Digimon's tremendous muscles 
hold terrible power, causing unadulterated destruction.
Fugamon's special move is Evil Hurricane, which
mows down everything with a swing of its bone club.
English.580:
A species of Ogremon that lives in cold regions. 
Hyogamon is extremely territorial, flying off the handle
and attacking anyone who takes even a step inside its 
domain (even getting into occasional clashes with 
Mojyamon over territory). Its special move is Snow 
Punch, which unleashes a chilling blow.
English.582:
A larval Digimon whose epidermis has yet to
solidify due to it living underwater. Otamamon
swims through swamps and rivers upstream of the
Net Ocean using its large tail, occasionally
clambering onto rocks with its developed forelimbs
to do vocal exercises. Unlike those of an average
organism, its hind legs are almost completely
undeveloped, acting as rudders in the stead of its
propulsive tail. Unlike other Rookies, this Digimon's
future Digivolution seems quite promising, but it's
extremely prone to mutation, so caution is
warranted when raising it. Otamamon's special
move is Lullaby Bubble, which sends opponents
into an eternal slumber.
English.584:
A reaper-like Digimon wielding a giant sickle and
chain. A Ghost Digimon more advanced than
Bakemon, once Phantomon possesses an individual,
their fate is almost certainly sealed. The eye-shaped
crystal hanging from its neck functions like
Mammothmon's crest, providing it with a second sight
that allows it to see over long distances. Phantomon
uses this ability to find those on the verge of death.
It's said that the inside of the cloth concealing its body
is connected to the Digital World of another dimension.
Phantomon's special move is Soul Chopper, which uses
its giant sickle and chain to slash its opponent's very
soul. Anyone struck by this attack is completely
obliterated, soul and all.
English.586:
A brutal Insectoid Digimon with massive wings. These 
wings allow Flymon to skirt through the air at ultrahigh 
speeds, creating sonic booms called "Howling Noise" 
in its wake that rob unlucky victims of their hearing. 
Its body is protected by a tough carapace, and it 
pinches foes with its huge talons before killing them 
with the extra-potent venomous stinger on its tail. The
Digivolution process of Insectoid Digimon is still 
unknown, but from its face, some have surmised that
Flymon originally Digivolved from a Kunemon-type 
creature. Its special move is Brown Stingers, which 
shoots a stinger from its tail that completely paralyzes 
the Digimon it pierces, turning it purple before ending 
its life. Incidentally, this nasty stinger can be regrown 
over and over again.
English.588:
An Ancient Digimon proved to have existed in ages 
long past, thanks to a multitude of evidence. The 
warming of the Digital World defrosted some
hyper-compressed data, causing Mammothmon to 
appear in icy areas where the thaw had melted. Its 
whole body is covered in thick fur, and although this 
Digimon possesses tremendous ancient power, it's
extremely susceptible to fire damage. The crest 
carved onto Mammothmon's face mask is a crystal
of super-ancient wisdom, and it possesses a second 
sight that allows it to see long distances. Its large
ears can discern sounds even in far-off places. 
Mammothmon's special move is Tusk Strikes, which 
stabs at the enemy with its two long tusks.
English.590:
An Undead Digimon whose muscles have rotted off. 
Raremon tried to prolong its life by mechanizing itself, 
but the process was unstable, causing the data 
composing its body to start falling apart. Even so, its 
machine parts grant this creature life, preventing its 
death and allowing it to survive in this awful state.
This crumbling form affords neither attack power nor 
intelligence, making Raremon act according to instinct
alone. Its body emits a stench awful enough to send 
In-Training Digimon running, and it won't fight
anything below Champion level.
English.592:
A cursed Digimon in the shape of a spider, whose 
entire body is infested with a computer virus. Even 
though a Spider-species type, Dokugumon was
originally a gentle and quiet Insectoid Digimon. 
One day, however, it was caught in a powerful
electromagnetic storm, and was infected with a 
computer virus that had been lurking around the Net. 
From that moment on, it became one big lump of 
venom—in other words, a nasty computer virus, 
corroding everything it touched. Dokugumon's 
eight-legged mobility is worthy of special mention, 
too. Even if the enemy runs from it at full speed, this 
Digimon will be right on its heels, pursuing it until it 
tires itself out. And then, as soon as it stops to take a
rest, Dokugumon uses Venom Blast on it, unleashing 
a dreadful, venomous attack from its fiendish fangs.
English.594:
A Sea Animal Digimon with fins on its feet with which
to paddle through water. Gizamon is more suited to
life underwater than on land, using its fins and strong
hind legs to swim quickly through aquatic areas.
On land, however, it bounces around like a frog.
Gizamon acts cowardly on land, but displays a
ferocious disposition once back in the water. Its
special move is Spiral Edge, which attacks foes with
its sharp-edged dorsal fins.
English.595:
An Ore Digimon with powerful defensive abilities,
having armored itself using ore data from its
surroundings. As spunky, mischievous and ambitious
as any young tough guy, Gotsumon leads around
groups of low-generation Digimon as it travels the
system. It also has a selfish side,and can be a real
handful when angered, rampaging like an erupting
volcano. The ore data Gotsumon uses for its armor
differs depending on where and how it was generated,
giving Gotsumon the potential to Digivolve into a
number of different forms. Gotsumon's special
move is Rock Fist, which shoots extremely hard rocks
from its head.
English.596:
A stuffed animal Digimon with a pumpkin for a head. 
According to urban legend, Pumpkinmon was created
when a computer virus commonly circulated around 
Halloween time suddenly mutated. The virus wasn't
malicious, so this Digimon never harms people, but 
Pumpkinmon is quite strong despite its appearance. 
As one look at their blankly staring faces will tell you, 
Puppet Digimon tend not to express emotion very 
clearly, and Pumpkinmon is no exception. Its special 
move is Trick or Treat, which manifests a giant 
pumpkin in midair with which to crush its foes.
English.597:
An experimental Digimon built in a laboratory as a 
Virus Hunter. Made of praying mantis data, Snimon 
chases after its target with machine-like precision. 
Its cold personality makes it feared by both Vaccine
and Data-attribute types alike. The scythes on
Snimon's arms are sharpened to points, allowing 
this Digimon to cleave cleanly through anything. It 
has no eyes, but the red feelers on its head act as 
sensors to accurately track the target's position. 
Snimon's special move is Shadow Sickle, which 
unleashes a supersonic slash invisible to the naked 
eye.
English.598:
A super heavy Dinosaur Digimon with giant horns 
growing from its shoulders. Tuskmon's foolhardy
personality means it will charge at and destroy every 
obstacle in its path, earning it the nickname of the
"Panzer Digimon." Specializing in charging tackles, 
Tuskmon has made countless Digimon fall before its
attacks. The stars on its arms represent the number 
of Digimon that Tuskmon has defeated (one hundred 
per star). If its horns break, it can shed them like 
shark teeth and bring new horns from the back to the 
front, making any attempt to destroy its horns fruitless.
Tuskmon's special move is Slamming Tusk, which
unleashes a super dreadnought-class punch.
English.600:
The true, Digivolved form of the king of darkness,
Myotismon. VenomMyotismon is a demon with the
lower body of a beast and an insect-like carapace
on its upper body. Having unleashed the full extent
of its hidden power, it yearns only for death and
destruction. Myotismon, retaining its reason,
intellect and refined conduct, is loath to reveal this
repugnant form. VenomMyotismon's special move
is Venom Infusion, which injects its opponent with
a destructive virus that completely destroys its
configuration data, causing it to cease functioning.
English.601:
A Digimon resembling a witch, who pursued its rival,
Wizardmon, from Witchelny, the Digital World of
another dimension. Witchmon mastered the magics
of wind and water (advanced programming languages)
in its home dimension Witchelny, but then pursued 
Wizardmon to the Digital World and now trains 
vigorously in order to get a leg up on this rival that
aims to become a great mage. Witchmon has a bit of 
a cruel streak, more than a bit of pride and loathes
both convention and established routines.
Witchmon's special move is Baluluna Gale, which
unleashes a cutting wind imbued with magic power.
English.602:
A Magic Warrior Digimon from Witchelny, the Digital 
World of another dimension. In addition to the
multitudes of magic (advanced programming language) 
at its disposal, Mistymon is also adept at the blade, 
possessing masterful swordsmanship. Well-versed 
both in chivalry and sorcery, it can even imbue its
sword with magic to attack. Its special move Blast
Fire is one such form of magic by which it covers
its sword in flames to slash with enhanced might.
English.603:
A Warrior Digimon extolled as the legendary hero of 
Witchelny, the Digital World of another dimension.
Ancient Witchelny was on the path to ruin, since its 
magic (advanced programming language) was still 
in its infancy and it lacked techniques to protect the 
land from invasion by outside forces. It's said that
MedievalGallantmon suddenly appeared and repelled 
invaders, and that it transcends time to exist to the
present day, although the truth of this is uncertain. It 
fights with arms created with magic, and wields
Dynas, the ultimate magic lance concealing the power 
of the wyvern. MedievalGallantmon is nicknamed the
"Whirlwind General" due to its governance over the 
Vortex Warriors, Digimon who fight with weapons 
made of wind magic, one of the four magic types (fire, 
earth, water and wind). Practically none have seen
MedievalGallantmon in the Digital World, but this 
Digimon is known as the "Warrior of Fantasy" due to
its armor covered with gorgeous decoration, and is
a solemn figure affixed with a coat of arms.
MedievalGallantmon uses special move Rage of 
Wyvern to fire energy from Dynas.
English.604:
A mythical Galaxy Digimon said to have appeared 
when an unprecedented crisis descended upon the 
Digital World of Iliad. The collision of the opposing 
forces of solar energy and lunar energy cause 
GraceNovamon to generate Big Bang levels of energy
within its body. It came into being when Apollomon 
and Dianamon of the Olympos XII fused together. 
As a result, GraceNovamon itself is believed to be a 
galaxy in its own right, and the full extent of its data is 
impossible to measure accurately. Its special moves 
are Eclipse Finger, which concentrates the energy 
amplified within its body into its hands, causing foes 
to melt when it touches them, and Calydon Arcus, 
which fires the eight Meleagros blades on its back to 
seek out and destroy its foes.
English.605:
A research data bank used to investigate and excavate 
ancient lifeforms was infected by a computer virus, 
which then incorporated data about these lifeforms 
into itself to Digivolve. Scorpiomon possesses a 
voracious appetite and predatory skills befitting a 
creature that stands at the top of an ancient food 
chain. It captures foes with the feelers growing from 
its head, then finishes them off with the sharp blade 
sprouting from its tail. If the tide of battle turns
against Scorpiomon, it can churn up the seabed with
its sharp feelers in order to hide. It uses the Radar Eyes 
protruding from its head like night vision goggles to 
ascertain foes, and then aims for a chance to strike.
Scorpiomon's special move is Stinger Surprise, which 
launches an attack from its crossed forelimbs.
English.606:
An Aquatic Beast Man Digimon clad in a wetsuit.
Cheerful by nature, Divermon can always be found
swimming in the Net Ocean. Underwater movement is
its forte, and it uses the underwater high-speed motor
on its back to engage in speedy combat. Divermon's
special move is Strike Fishing, which stabs the enemy
with its beloved harpoon, "Trent."
English.607:
A small Vegetation Digimon in the shape of a
poisonous mushroom. Tiny but potent poisonous
mushroom bombs growing from Mushroomon's
body cause all kinds of afflictions. Anyone hit by
one of these bombs could start laughing
uncontrollably, have their body go numb, lose
their memory, or worse. Mushroomon is extremely
ill-tempered and enjoys picking on the weak, but
also has a shy side, always hiding half of its face.
Its special move is Fungus Crusher, scattering
multiple mini-mushroom bombs at once.
English.609:
An extremely rare insect Machine Digimon that
was recently discovered. No insect Machine
Digimon had been discovered up to that point, and
so Kokuwamon's existence wasn't even considered
a possibility. Its stun gun-shaped head and arms
can discharge 100 megavolts of electricity when it
senses danger, so none can approach without
caution. Even so, Kokuwamon lacks any aggression,
sporting instead an accommodating nature that
seeks peace. Kokuwamon obtains nourishment
from electricity, and recharges itself with the two
limbs on its midsection. Its special move is
Mini Scissor Claw, which electrifies its pincers
to slice through even the sturdiest of objects.
English.610:
A mysterious Ancient Digimon said to have been 
hunted to extinction due to the proliferation of the 
Internet. The wings of this Bird Digimon have
completely degenerated, preventing it from taking 
flight. Kiwimon also bears some aspects of a 
Vegetation Digimon, with leaf-like objects growing
from its head that it uses to absorb nutrients through
photosynthesis. It has no way to defend itself aside 
from the hard shell covering its head, and its docile 
personality makes it an easy target. Kiwimon's special 
move is Pummel Peck, attacking with the ChibiKiwimon 
hidden in its body. The beaks of the ChibiKiwimon are 
just as hard as Kiwimon's, and they explode when 
struck. Even if this explosion chars them to a crisp,
ChibiKiwimon will always bounce back.
English.611:
A rare Digimon that, like Palmon, Digivolved in
reptilian fashion but is classified as a Vegetation
Digimon. The entirety of Floramon's face is shaped
like a flower, and it generally uses this petal-like
shell like a helmet to protect its head. When no
predators are around, or when in a good mood, it
will spread open the petals on its head and arms.
Floramon sees Palmon as a rival, and has a very
high opinion of itself. Its special move is Rain of
Pollen, which releases clouds of allergy-inducing 
pollen from the flowers on its arms. Anyone hit by
this attack—even a large Digimon—will be robbed
of both their composure and will to fight.
English.613:
A Virtue Digimon protecting the Zenith Gate that 
connects the Digital World to the outside world.
This gate is sealed by 360 doors, and ClavisAngemon
holds "The Key," a master key that unlocks them all.
The Key is special in that it can only be wielded by
this Digimon. Some suspect that ClavisAngemon itself
is a part of said key. The power embedded in The Key
could apparently collapse the very Digital World itself,
but is only used against foes who would destroy the
doors.
English.614:
A Great Angel Digimon that commands the Angelic Army
and takes the lead in battle. SlashAngemon doesn't fear
death when in the service of carrying out justice. 
From its twin arm blades to its metal wings, the 
razor-sharp body of this angel warrior was without a 
doubt born to battle wicked beings. SlashAngemon's 
signature move is Blade of the True, and its special
move is Golden Ripper, charging at foes with 
tremendous force to carve them up with the blades 
on its body.
English.615:
A power suit Digimon used by other, small-sized 
Digimon, making it the first Vehicle-species Digimon 
in the Digital World. Mekanorimon is unique in that 
it can't operate itself, and fails to function unless 
piloted by other Digimon. Given its Virus attribute, 
the Digimon controlling it can also be considered a
Virus Digimon. Mekanorimon is still in development,
meaning its DigiCore will overheat if it's used too 
much. Its special move is Twinkle Beam, which fires 
a beam from the linear lens embedded in its torso.
Any enemy hit by this beam loses control of their
body.
English.616:
A Dragon Man Digimon fortified with firearm 
contraptions all over its body. A wanderer traveling 
the Digital World in search of its scattered comrades, 
MagnaKidmon is a troublemaker that causes 
problems and gets caught up in incidents wherever
it ends up. Its self-centered personality often makes 
it single-minded, but its sense of friendship and 
obligation runs deep. MagnaKidmon befriends any 
local Deputymon it comes upon, mistaking them for 
its brethren. This trigger-happy creature loves
one-on-one combat, firing bullets indiscriminately 
once challenged to a duel. One of MagnaKidmon's 
special moves is Bind Red Trigger, which stabs the 
small machine guns attached to its hip-mounted 
magazines into the opponent, destroying it from 
within. Its ultimate special move is Happy Bullet 
Showering, which sends MagnaKidmon high into the 
skies with its winglike scarf to target the opponent 
with folded arms, pounding away at it with a mix of 
live ammo and plasma projectiles from its fingertips 
and gun muzzles on both legs.
English.617:
The result of a sudden transformation akin to 
mutation that occurred when a Digimon felled by 
MagnaKidmon became so obsessed with revenge 
that the data of its own negative thoughts overwhelmed
its DigiCore. To vent its rage at taking on an
appearance so similar to the Digimon it hoped to
destroy, AvengeKidmon has turned to mindless 
rampage, to the extent that its original goal of defeating
MagnaKidmon has left its thoughts. One of 
its special moves is Destruction Trigger, which pins 
an enemy underfoot before firing an explosive bullet 
into them at point-blank range from its gun leg,
regardless of the fact that this will injure AvengeKidmon
as well. The other is Misery Bullet Rain, which
launches its target into the air with a stream of
energy blasts from its fingers, then unleashes a
barrage of live ammunition while it's still in midair.
English.621:
An Android Digimon resembling a tank. Known as the 
"Mercenary Digimon," Tankmon will back up Vaccine 
and Virus Digimon alike if there's profit to be made. 
It pulverizes incoming enemies to dust with its 
heavyweight power and the heavy ordnance covering
its body. A conflict enthusiast, Tankmon heads in the 
direction of any strife that pops up. Wherever this
lone wolf goes, conflict is sure to continue unceasingly.
Tankmon's special move is Hyper Cannon, which
launches a super-powerful missile from the gun
barrel on its head.
English.622:
A Bird Digimon resembling a penguin found in the
computer of an Antarctic base. Since Penmon lives
in snow-covered regions, it doesn't do well in the
heat. It does quite well with humans, conversely,
and will happily waddle along behind them. Penmon's
wings have degenerated, so it can't fly or walk
very quickly. But when it slides across the ice on
its belly, it can reach speeds close to 40 mph.
When in the water, Penmon can use its small
wings to skillfully swim around. Its special move
is Super Slap, where it sneaks up on the enemy
to smack their cheeks as hard as it can with
both arms.
English.623:
A flightless Bird Digimon that's the spitting image
of Penmon. Raised in tropical lands to the south,
Muchomon lives a life of constant cheer. It overflows
with passion, dances to a samba beat and loves its
vivid, richly-colored pelt. Muchomon's special move
is Tropical Beak, pecking the opponent with its
colorful beak.
English.626:
Keramon is a Rookie Digimon that Digivolved from
Tsumemon. Now that its body has grown larger and
its mouth is bigger, it can devour more data.
Keramon is capable of consuming more than 100
megabytes per second, and most data is destroyed
the instant Keramon accesses it. Extremely playful
by nature, it thinks of its destructive acts as a kind
of game. Its special move is Crazy Giggle, with which
it unleashes a highly destructive beam of light from
its mouth as it laughs—if you can call it laughing.
English.627:
An Ultimate Digimon similar in appearance to a 
long-legged spider. In its normal form, Infermon has 
its limbs and head extended, but it can also take on 
a cocoon form where it draws its limbs inside its body. 
In cocoon form, its defense increases to the point 
where it can repel any attack, although this limits its
movement to a straight line. It can easily overcome 
the tightest security to infiltrate any network. Should
Infermon ever be released onto the Net, the world 
would be plunged into chaos. Its special move Spider
Shooter fires an energy bomb of incredible destructive 
power from the gunport in its mouth.
English.629:
Kuramon is an Unidentified Digimon that suddenly 
appeared on a computer network. A single Digi-Egg 
was born from the malice of humans abusing computers
and the aggression from conflicts unfolding over
networks. The Digi-Egg was the amalgamation of
humanity's destructive instincts, and the mysterious
Digimon born from it is incredibly dangerous. It
multiplies within a computer network like a virus,
causing minor network failures. Kuramon uses its
special move Glare Eye to produce a frothy substance
from its giant eye.
English.630:
Kurisarimon is a Champion Digimon that resembles a
chrysalis. In order to Digivolve into a more powerful
form, the Rookie Keramon temporarily enters a
chrysalis state to store up its energy. As a result, it
becomes completely unable to move, but its tough
outer hide protects it while the tentacles that grow
from its back allow it to attack foes. Keramon can
sometimes Digivolve directly into an Ultimate Digimon
without going through this Champion phase, but
Digivolving into Kurisarimon allows it to reach a
more powerful Ultimate form. Its special move Data
Crusher involves using the tentacles that extend from
its back to destroy an enemy's composition data.
English.631:
An In-Training Digimon that Digivolved beyond
Kuramon. The tips of its feelers are shaped like
talons, increasing its ferocity. Tsumemon corrodes 
data at frightening speed, causing networks to
malfunction. Its movement speed is just as fast,
making this Digimon difficult to catch once it's
Digivolved to this level. It uses its special move
Nail Scratch to rake the enemy with the talons on
its feelers.
English.632:
Diaboromon absorbs any and all data on the Net 
so that it can repeatedly Digivolve and grow larger, 
thereby draining the Digital World and bringing it to 
the brink of destruction. Having absorbed a vast
quantity of knowledge and data, Diaboromon sees 
itself as omniscient and omnipotent, and revels in 
carnage and slaughter. Out of the many Digimon in 
existence, it's one of the few with a definite purpose. 
Its ultimate goal is to hijack a military computer so 
that it can launch a nuclear strike and destroy the 
Material World, making it a terrifying Digimon. Its
special move is Catastrophe Cannon, with which it
fires a destructive energy bomb from the cannon in
its chest.
English.669:
A Digimon whose power over fire exceeds that of 
legend due to the unknown powers it obtained by 
fully inheriting the might of the Ten Legendary 
Warriors. Aldamon is a Demon God who transforms 
fear and anger into a righteous power to fight. Its 
violent behavior earns it many enemies, but its 
name reflects the fused form of a god in Hindu
mythology, combining the wildness of a beast with 
the intelligence of a human. In battle, it unleashes
attacks over incredibly large areas, melting and 
burning everything to a crisp. This aspect is a 
destructive power akin to the threat of a modern
nuclear weapon. Aldamon uses its special move 
Atomic Inferno to fire a rapid-fire stream of
super-hot bullets from the Rudriya Darpana
superweapons on its arms. It can also use its
Rudriya Darpana for melee, and specializes in
close-range combat.
English.670:
A Digimon whose power over light exceeds that of 
legend due to the unknown powers it obtained by 
fully inheriting the might of the Ten Legendary 
Warriors. Beowolfmon possesses both the instincts
of a beast and the intelligence of a human. 
A warrior of exceptional strength, it easily wields its
twin-bladed greatsword Trinität with just one hand. 
In battle, it always remains thoughtful and composed,
although as a warrior, it believes in the virtues of 
fighting for its friends and facing off against greater 
foes. Thanks to the long-distance missile pod on its 
left arm, the Roland 2, it excels at both long-range 
and close-range combat. Its special move is
Zweihänder, an attack with which it swings the 
greatsword Trinität down at near-lightspeed to cleave 
through foes.
English.675:
A transcendent Digimon with power over light, 
said to even surpass the might of the Ten Legendary
Warriors. Its special move is Starlight Velocity,
with which it accelerates to superluminal speed,
erasing anything that comes into contact with its
light.
English.676:
A Digimon with power over fire that bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. Agunimon's 
DigiCore is covered in the holy blaze of the Spiritual 
Fire, allowing it to control fire at will. A guardian 
deity, it's an avatar of the Firewall that defends the 
Net. Agunimon gets riled up easily, so its warrior 
side uses yoga breathing to encourage mental 
discipline. Agunimon also has a somewhat 
old-fashioned way of speaking, akin to that of a 
martial artist. It fights with Eastern martial arts in 
battle, focusing its spirit to a point to gather flames 
in one place and raise its attack power. Agunimon 
uses its special move Pyro Punch to shoot a flame 
dragon from its fire-wreathed fist.
English.677:
A transcendent Digimon with power over flame, said 
to even surpass the might of the Ten Legendary 
Warriors. The power of the nine dragon veins flowing 
through Gaia resides in EmperorGreymon's body. It 
has been prophesied that if it can harness that power, 
it will demonstrate unfathomable ability and rule over
Gaia. It wields the Ryuugonken, a sword with the souls 
of dragons sealed within, in order to control this 
power. Its special moves include Firedrake Strike, with 
which it unleashes white-hot, blazing arrows from the 
Ryuugonken, and Pyro Dragons, with which it releases 
the power of eight of the dragon veins of Gaia, taking 
the place of the ninth dragon itself and crushing foes 
with its huge sword.
English.678:
A transcendent Digimon with power over light, said 
to even surpass the might of the Ten Legendary 
Warriors. Specializing in super-fast movement, 
MagnaGarurumon is able to fly at near-lightspeed 
with its flight unit equipped. The laser sights on its 
chest rotate in-flight, locking on to air and ground 
targets from high in the sky for an all-out attack. It's 
all but impossible to escape from MagnaGarurumon. 
It uses its special move Machinegun Destroyer to 
unleash its arsenal onto locked targets before 
violently destroying the main target at high speed.
English.679:
A Digimon with power over fire that bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. BurningGreymon's 
skin withstands high temperatures, allowing it to 
move even through lava. This firefighter snuffs out
fires with its own instantaneous, explosive flames. 
Said to have sprung forth from research data on 
active volcanoes, it's thought to contain an unknown, 
immeasurable energy. The fire dragon of Hindu 
mythology, adversary to the thunder god Indra, is 
embodied in BurningGreymon's ferocious personality. 
BurningGreymon uses its special move Corona 
Blaster to fire a laser rivaling solar heat rays from 
the Rudriya Darpana superweapons on its arms.
English.680:
A Digimon with power over light that bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. The lavender parts 
all over Lobomon's body are made of Saint Amethyst, 
a crystal containing holy light. This light maintains an
extraordinary durability in the amethyst when one's 
heart is true, but the substance turns brittle the
moment negativity arises in the heart of any who 
wield it. Lobomon has a chivalrous spirit and puts its 
life on the line for what it believes in, and hates 
injustice. Taciturn and rarely concerning itself with 
others, many believe it to be an unfeeling creature, 
but this warrior is actually kind-hearted. Lobomon 
uses its special move Zwei Sieger to connect the twin 
swords Licht Schwert before cutting multiple 
opponents to pieces.
English.681:
A Digimon with power over light that bears the might 
of the Ten Legendary Warriors. KendoGarurumon's 
capability of moving at incredible speed is perhaps 
related to its discovery of a fiber optic network. 
Capable of dodging between bullets to close in on 
foes, it will mercilessly tear apart anyone it deems 
evil with its sharp claws and fangs. Possessed of a
righteous heart and all the determination of Garmr, 
the wolf said to have fought with Týr in Norse
mythology, KendoGarurumon has an intense hatred 
of evil. It will refuse to obey any with even a hint of 
wickedness in their heart, although once it swears 
loyalty to someone, it will never betray them. Its 
special move is Speed Star, with which it charges 
forward at light speed to cut through foes with the
Wing Blades on its back.
English.682:
A ferocious Digimon with amazing vigor and extreme
aggression. Even so, it's friendly to allies, and those
recognized by Shoutmon can establish a deep bond
that transcends species. Because passion is the
source of its strength, Shoutmon won't abandon
a battle no matter how much damage it receives,
contributing to its savage reputation.
English.683:
OmniShoutmon is the form obtained when Omnimon
bestowed a legendary Digivolution upon Shoutmon,
who had unleashed its soul's seething passion. In
addition to its intense fervor, its entire body is clad in
Omni inForce, a power it obtained from Omnimon,
so it emits a golden glow from its sharp new form.
OmniShoutmon's Flame Cannon transforms the
overflowing feelings of friendship in its heart into
firepower, releasing a hail of bullets that can not only
attack, but also become a wall of iron to protect its
allies. With Hard Rock Soul, it can concentrate its
fervent courage into flames that burst from its fists
to either punch enemies at close range or blast them
with fire from long range.
English.687:
A Mini Dragon Digimon with a cool white sheen.
Unfettered and hating shackles, Huckmon's
swashbuckling way of life is likely due to the
influence of Gankoomon's DNA. It faces the harsh
trials imposed by Gankoomon with composure.
Huckmon's lineage gives it a keen sense for battle,
and training supervised by the Sistermon siblings
makes it more than evenly matched in fights
against even Ultimate foes. Huckmon specializes
in nimble melee combat, using Fifth Rush to cleave
the opponent with its tough claws. It pursues its
dream to become a Royal Knight like Gankoomon.
English.688:
A Holy Knight Digimon and successor to the position 
of one of the Royal Knights. Together with Huckmon, 
who it hopes to make its successor, Gankoomon 
journeys all over the Digital World, quelling chaos 
and disturbances before they can get out of hand. 
Since it intends to make Huckmon succeed it as a 
Royal Knight, Gankoomon puts Huckmon through 
a series of severe trials. Gankoomon is stubborn, 
which leads it to be harsh on Huckmon, although 
this is in fact a reflection of its kindness, since it 
wants to make Huckmon the equal of any other 
Royal Knight. Hinukamuy is the projection from its 
body that, while it doesn't speak, helps Gankoomon 
without question. Gankoomon's special move is 
Quake! Blast! Fire! Father! This attack involves 
Hinukamuy delivering divine punishment in response 
to a shout from Gankoomon. It also uses Table Flip, 
with which it flips over part of the ground as if it
were a table made of Chrondigizoid.
English.697:
Zubamon is one of the Legend-Arms that can transform
its body into a weapon. The fabled Legend-Arms are
said to be capable of either saving the world in the
hands of an angel, or destroying it in the hands of a
devil. Zubamon possesses the data of the Twentiest,
and often shouts "I am the Twentiest!" without knowing
what that means. It dislikes anything warped or twisted,
and is in constant pursuit of its ideal of sharpness.
In battle and in jest, it's always trying to look sharp, and
days when it succeeds put it in a good mood. Though it
has its Twenty Dive attack that involves rushing headlong
at an enemy, Zubamon's true strength lies in its weapon
form.
English.698:
"I am the Twentiest! I won't stop! I'll keep on 
running!" With those words emblazoned on its soul, 
Zubamon Digivolved to ZubaEagermon. Its new form
